title: sprouts and carrots
directions: Trim the bottom of the Brussels sprouts and pull off any withered leaves.
Cook them in boiling salted water until tender, about 10 minutes.
Drain.
Slice carrots and cook in boiling salted water until tender, 8 to 10 minutes.
Grate 1 teaspoon of the colored zest from orange.
Squeeze 3 tablespoons juice.

title: "death by chocolate" cake(simple-quick-one pan cake!)
directions: Pour oil into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Tilt oil around to cover sides and bottom of pan.
Stir in rest of ingredients; mix well with a fork (right in cake pan!).
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes, until done (check with toothpick).
You may sprinkle powdered sugar on top to serve.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix in bowl with wooden spoon.
Batter will be very stiff. Drop on cookie sheet (greased) the size of walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 8 dozen small cookies (2 dozen to a cookie sheet).

title: wynnewood aunt's fruitcake
directions: Prepare tube pan.
Line pan with 2 layers of brown paper. Grease pan and paper thoroughly.

title: peach pie
directions: Put juice and pudding in bottom of cake pan.
Sprinkle jello over peaches, then dry cake mix. Cut margarine in slices and put over all. Punch holes in mix and pour water over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: punch
directions: Add ginger ale to other ingredients just before serving.

title: date filled cookies
directions: Combine shortening, salt and vanilla.
Blend.
Add sugar and cream well.
Add beaten egg and mix thoroughly.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Add to the first, alternately with milk, blending well.
Chill dough.
Roll dough 1/8-inch thick on floured board. Cut into 3-inch cookie.
Place one cookie on ungreased cookie sheet.
Add 1 teaspoon of Date Filling (recipe to follow).
Cover with another cookie.
Press together with a fork.
Prick top of each cookie with a fork.
Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes.

title: chili con queso
directions: Cube cheese and put in saucepan; stir in salsa.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Stir in cilantro.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: corn scallop
directions: Beat eggs until light, add corn, milk, flour and seasoning. Bake at 375 degrees for 45 minutes or until it puffs.

title: my favorite canape
directions: Remove the crust (if preferred) from slices of bread, at least 2 to 3 per person.
Spread with softened cream cheese.
Cover with 1 spear of asparagus and roll up.
May secure with toothpick. Chill and serve.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers, onion and salt; let stand for 2 hours.
Boil sugar and vinegar until sugar is dissolved.
When cool, it will be thick.
Drain and squeeze out all juice.
Place in freezer boxes. Pour syrup over pickles; freeze.
You may add celery seed and mustard seed to each box if you like.

title: sausage cabbage bake
directions: Pour chopped cabbage into baking dish.
Pour in water and drizzle with cooking oil.
Sprinkle sugar and salt and pepper to taste over cabbage.
Place sausage pieces on top of cabbage. Cover and bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes or until cabbage is tender.

title: bacon broccoli quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Brush crust with some of beaten egg and prick with fork. Mix all ingredients and bake in pie shell.

title: santa whiskers cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form 2 rolls.
Roll each in coconut. Wrap in waxed paper.
Chill.
Cut into slices.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes on ungreased pan.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender; cover and blend until smooth, about 30 seconds.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Butter dish; dust with Parmesan cheese.
In blender, add all ingredients; blend at medium until smooth, then at high speed for another 10 to 15 seconds.
Pour into dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, until brown.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Peel onions.
Cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Separate into rings. Sift flour, baking powder and salt into medium bowl.
Stir in egg, water, lemon juice and melted shortening, just until blended.
Fry at 375° for 2 minutes on each side.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Use cold water to make thin mixture of ingredients.
Heat and add 2 to 3 cups of water.
Cook until thickened.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayo, sugar and vinegar.
Mix all other ingredients and place dry mixture over.
Serve cold.

title: sausage balls(appetizers)
directions: Mix all ingredients well in a large bowl.
Roll into walnut size balls.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: peanut brittle candy
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and water until spins a thread.
Add butter, then peanuts.
Cook until peanuts begin to pop.
Add soda and stir quickly.
Pour in two buttered sheets.

title: south african dessert
directions: Bake biscuits on temperature that can says.
Make pudding from the directions on box.
Take biscuits out of the oven and pull apart.
Spread over a pan.
Pour pudding over biscuits.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over pudding.
Put in freezer for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mushroom stew
directions: Brown pork steak (cut up) in oil.
Add tomato sauce and water. Add all other ingredients.
Then simmer until all vegetables are tender.
Add mushrooms.

title: parmesan canapes
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; stir until well blended. Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Spread on bread rounds.
Put under broiler until lightly browned.

title: pasta and vegetable toss(low calorie and low-fat; makes 2 servings)
directions: In a 9-inch skillet, heat the oil.
Add onions, zucchini, carrots and garlic; cook over medium heat until onions are tender.

title: nut torte cake
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick.
Add sugar and beat until well blended.
Sift flour.
Measure required amount after sifting. Sift again with the rest of the dry ingredients.
Add alternately with cold coffee and vanilla to egg mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into batter.
Fold in nuts, reserving a few for the top.
Pour batter into 2 ungreased 9 inch cake pans and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 25 - 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole(club member: kristi mayfield)
directions: Boil chicken until tender. Remove chicken. Cook spaghetti, green pepper and onion in chicken broth until spaghetti is tender. Stir in chicken, salt, pepper, pimento, cheese and soup. Pour into greased baking dish. Bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Shape into loaf in a large baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: red cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Make a paste of coloring and cocoa.
Add to shortening and sugar.
Add buttermilk alternately with sifted flour and salt.
Add vanilla.
Add soda to vinegar and then add this to other mixture, blending instead of beating.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in two (8 or 9-inch) greased and floured pans in 350° oven.
Cool and split each layer in two and frost.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cinnamon and apples and put into unbaked pie crust.
Cut butter in flour and sugar with fork.
Sprinkle over pie and bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: green chili enchiladas
directions: In large
heavy pot combine tomatoes, chilies, soup, sour cream and 1 can of olives.
Heat over low heat.
Put 1 spoonful of meat and 1 spoonful of sauce into each tortilla.
Fold and place, seam side down, in a large baking pan.
Add any remaining meat to sauce and pour over tortillas.
Top with shredded Cheddar and remaining olives.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: "pfeffernuesse" cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add almonds and ammonia. Knead in flour. Roll into balls the size of a hickory nut. Freeze. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet (still frozen) in 300° oven until a delicate brown, 18 to 20 minutes or so.

title: salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender or food processor. Wonderful used with nice crisp selection of different greens.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Melt butter and peanut butter.
Mix ingredients and press into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Melt 12 ounce package chocolate chips and spread over top.
Cut into squares.
Do not bake.

title: velvet walnut fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 10-inch tube pan well. Sprinkle 1/2 cup chopped walnuts on bottom of pan.
Blend in a large bowl the cake mix, water, pudding, eggs, sour cream, water, oil and extracts.
Stir in 1/2 cup chopped walnuts and chocolate chips.
Pour into pan and bake 70 minutes; do not underbake.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Garnish with whipped topping.

title: country potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and boil.
While potatoes are boiling, melt butter in saucepan.
Mix in soup and sour cream.
Drain potatoes and mix in soup and sour cream mixture, then add grated cheese and chives.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or put in crock-pot.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add Heinz 57, Worcestershire sauce and garlic.
Roll in pecans.
Serve over crackers.
Delicious!

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and cube eggplant.
Cook in salted water.
Drain cooked eggplant and add 1/2 green pepper that has been sauteed in butter. Add eggs, soup and 1/2 cup cracker crumbs.
Place 1/2 of mixture in casserole, then a layer of sliced fresh tomatoes and a layer of sliced American cheese.
Add remaining eggplant mixture and top with cracker crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake in moderate oven until hot and bubbly, about 35 minutes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Put in bottom of casserole dish.
Put chicken over rice.
Heat other ingredients together until cheese melts and pour over chicken and rice.
Sprinkle with slivered almonds.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 10 generously.

title: pecan pralines(may also use for a frosting.)
directions: Combine sugar, soda, butter milk and salt. Cook over high heat 5 minutes, stirring constantly and scraping bottom of pan. Add butter and pecans. Continue cooking until candy reaches soft-ball (cook less time for frosting). Remove from heat and cool slightly. Beat until thick and creamy. Drop by tablespoon onto wax paper and let cool.

title: orange salad
directions: In a saucepan, combine pineapple and sugar and bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
When mixture boils, immediately add orange gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Cool slightly.
Stir in buttermilk.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in whipped topping and nuts.
Cool until mixture mounds slightly.
Pour contents into lightly oiled 8 1/2-inch mold.
Chill overnight or at least 8 hours.

title: butter drop cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add sifted dry ingredients and mix well.
Blend in vanilla, nuts, raisins or chocolate chips or whatever you desire.
Chill dough for 1 hour.
Drop by teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: fried rice
directions: Beat 2 eggs and cook in skillet like an omelet.
Brown hamburger with pepper, salt and soy sauce.
Add green onions and green pepper to drained fat from hamburger.
Cook until tender. Add rice and cooked egg.
Mix all together; top with 1/4 cup green onions, chopped fine.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Have oven preheated to 350°.
This is important.

title: mississippi spice muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix in applesauce and spices.
Sift together salt, soda and flour.
Add to the applesauce mixture and beat well.
Stir in nuts. Bake in lightly greased miniature muffin pans at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar before serving.

title: doughnuts
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup lukewarm water.
Combine ingredients.
Put enough flour to make a stiff sponge.
Then let rise until double in size.
Then work in more flour until you think enough.
Let it stand 15 minutes more. Cut and drop into deep pan of hot grease.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Saute onions and celery in margarine.
Add this to the rest of the ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Stuff turkey and bake, or bake in a baking dish at 350° for 1 hour.

title: unstuffed stuffed peppers
directions: Brown meat and peppers in an 8-inch skillet; drain.
Reduce heat; continue cooking 5 minutes or until green pepper is crisp-tender.
Add remaining ingredients; heat thoroughly.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Mix soda and vanilla with sour cream.
Add alternately with the flour to the butter mixture.
Mix well.

title: easy pork chop dinner
directions: Take 12-inches of foil and lay flat.
Peel and chop potato in bite size pieces.
Place in foil.
Lay green beans on top of potato.
Place chopped onion and butter on top of that.
Place pork chop on top of the potato and bean layers.
Season the chop with spiced and butter.
Wrap all of this up tightly in foil.
Place in 400° oven for 45 minutes or until done.
Your whole meal is in the oven cooking.
Other fresh vegetables work also.

title: wedding punch
directions: Prepare limeade as directed.
Mix with chilled pineapple juice.
Add ginger ale.
Spoon in lime sherbet.
Add cherries.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Make into 1-inch balls.
Brown and drain.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix together and put in baking dish.

title: fresh strawberry pies
directions: Mix cream cheese and Eagle Brand milk.
Fold in Cool Whip, then strawberries.
Pour in pie crusts. Chill.
Freezes well.

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: Mix together and spread on each tortilla.
Roll up and put in Saran Wrap and twist ends.
Refrigerate overnight or for several hours.
Slice and serve with hot sauce.
Poke a toothpick in each pinwheel.

title: caramel icing
directions: Brown 2 cups sugar.
Add hot water.
Stir until dissolved. Add condensed milk.
Let cook until well dissolved.
Add 1 cup sugar and cook until it forms medium hard ball in cold water.
Add vanilla, butter and nuts.
Yield: icing for 4 layers.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook macaroni per directions.
Mix all ingredients together and place in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: white fluffy frosting
directions: Put sugar and water on to boil until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
While these ingredients are boiling, beat egg whites until fluffy.
Take water and sugar off heat.
Add this to beaten egg whites.
Beat until it forms peaks.

title: quick potato soup
directions: Melt Velveeta cheese in the mixture. Serve hot.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread coconut and pecans in bottom of pan.
Prepare cake mix according to package and pour over coconut and pecans.
Mix margarine, cream cheese and sugar. Spread on top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand to firm up.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender; pour in pie crust.
Bake at 350°.

title: cake topping
directions: Mix together.
Spread on top of cake or pie, such as Dutch apple.
Bake.

title: cinnamon raisin biscuit
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Cut shortening until coarse crumbs form.
Add milk and raisins; mix well.
Place on lightly floured surface, knead gently 10 to 12 times.
Roll dough and cut out biscuits.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Place in oven for 10 minutes.

title: christmas morning egg and sausage casserole
directions: Mix eggs, milk, dry mustard and salt.
Break up bread in mixture.
Add sausage and cheese.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish and pour in the mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 325°.
Good served with fresh fruit and hot biscuits.

title: piggy apple
directions: Core apple; fill with peanut butter.
Attach raisins for eyes, marshmallow for nose, carrot stick for tail and apple triangles for ears using wooden toothpicks.

title: maple fluff fruit dip
directions: Stir brown sugar, sour cream and maple flavoring well until sugar is dissolved. Whip whipping cream well. Fold in other ingredients and refrigerate. Make day you use it.

title: spanish coffee cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, brown
sugar,
nutmeg,
salt and oil. Take 3/4 cup of mixture and
add
to
it
the chopped nuts and cinnamon.
Set aside.
To
remainder of first mixture add sour milk, soda and beaten egg.
Blend together and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle reserved
mixture
over
top.
Bake
at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: how to preserve children
directions: First, use care and get one, not too young, but tender and a healthy growth.
Make your selection carefully and let it be final. Otherwise they will not keep.
Like wine they improve with age.
Do not pickle or put in hot water.
This makes them sour.
Prepare as follows:
sweeten with smiles according to variety.
The sour, bitter kind are improved by a pinch of salt of common sense.
Spice with patience.
Wrap well in a mantle of charity.
Preserve over a good fire of steady devotion.
Serve with peaches and cream.
The poorest varieties may be improved by this process and kept for years in any climate.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Cook ground beef and onion in pan.
Drain grease and add chili powder, cumin and salt.
Cook 10 more minutes.

title: frosty peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, peanut butter, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into crust.
Drizzle with chocolate syrup.

title: spicy beef salami
directions: In a large bowl, thoroughly mix all ingredients.
Cover and chill for 24 hours.
Divide mixture into fourths.
Shape each into a compact 8-inch log and place each on a 12 x 8-inch piece of nylon net.
Roll up tightly; tie ends with string.
Place logs on broiler pan with a rack and bake in a 225° oven for 4 hours. Remove from oven and take off net.
Pat rolls well with paper towels to absorb excess fat.
Cool slightly, then wrap in foil and refrigerate or freeze.
Makes about 3 pounds.

title: macaroni baltimore style
directions: Cook macaroni until slightly tender.
Cook bacon until crisp; remove from pan and crumble.
Saute diced onion and green pepper. Add tomatoes.
Alternate layers of sauce, cheese and macaroni, winding up with cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour, or until bubbling.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cook bacon; break up and set aside.
Saute onion and green pepper until tender in a little butter or margarine.
Stir in the corn and bacon.
Spoon into a 1-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbly and heated through.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: hot dogs with salsa
directions: Cook hot dogs.
Warm buns then put the hot dogs in them.
Chop onion finely.
Cut tomatoes and discard the seeds.
Mix chopped tomatoes, onion, salt, pepper, and tabasco sauce in a large bowl for the salsa.
Put salsa on hot dogs.

title: holiday fruit bars
directions: Sift together and set aside flour, baking powder and salt. Beat eggs and sugar until thick and lemon colored.
Add chocolate morsels, nutmeats, raisins, dates, cherries, pineapple, cherry juice and grated rind.
Fold into flour mixture.
Pour into two greased waxed paper lined pans, about 9 1/2 x 5 1/2 x 2 3/4-inch. Bake at 340° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Yields about 4 dozen bars.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together in casserole dish. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chewy pralines
directions: Cook in large pot everything except vanilla and pecans.
Bring to a boil over low heat.
Stir constantly.
Cook until it forms almost a hard ball (243°) on candy thermometer.
Remove and add pecans and vanilla.
Pour into greased pan (13x9).
When cold, cut into squares.

title: shrimp and crab meat casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: fool's toffee
directions: In a small saucepan over medium-high heat, blend butter and brown sugar.
Heat to boiling.
Boil for 4 minutes.
Cover a 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan with foil and butter lightly.
Place a single layer of saltines on foil.
Pour butter mixture over crackers, spreading evenly.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes. Immediately sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Allow to soften and spread evenly over crackers.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Refrigerate until cool.
Break into pieces.

title: pirogi
directions: Mix together eggs, water, oil and 3 cups of flour, gradually adding remaining flour and salt.
Make 4 balls of dough.
Let stand 10 minutes, covered with a cloth, before rolling (turn once).
Roll thin on lightly floured board and cut into 2-inch squares.
Fill with potato filling (recipe follows).
Drop in boiling water, bringing water to boiling point a second time and cook 5 minutes.

title: thumbprint cookies(swedish tea cakes)
directions: Mix together butter or oleo and brown sugar; beat well.
Add egg yolk; mix in.
Add flour; blend well.
Make balls of dough. Roll in egg white, then roll in nuts.
Put on greased cookie sheet.
Make dent in each with finger and fill with jam.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from sheet while still warm.

title: butterscotch pecan cookies
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding, flour, oil and egg.
Stir in pecans. Dough will be crumbly.
Roll into balls.
Place 2 inches apart on a greased cookie sheet and bake at 350 degrees for 10 - 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool 2 minutes and remove from pan.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Peel, core and halve the apples.
For the dough, mix together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk. Mix and roll like pie dough.
Place apple half on a square of the rolled dough; add 1 pat of butter.
Sprinkle cinnamon and sugar over apple and roll dough around apple.
Place in pan.
Repeat for each apple.

title: mock corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake at 450° for about 15 minutes.

title: aunt nancy's oyster pie
directions: Cook carrots and potatoes until just slightly soft. Add celery and parsley and cook 10 min more.

title: passover treat matza brei
directions: Pour water into flat pan ;add crumbled matzas to soak and soften.
Beat eggs; add to matzas.
Melt butter in frypan.
Pour mix in pan; fry and stir occasionally
until thickened.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Serve with applesauce.

title: corn pie
directions: Beat eggs; add to corn.
Add milk, melted butter, salt, pepper and corn meal.
Bake in greased casserole in moderate oven for 25 minutes.
Set pan in boiling water to prevent overcooking.
Serves 6.

title: not just for breakfast bars
directions: In small skillet, slowly bring oil, honey and maple syrup to a boil.
Toss cereal and nuts in a medium bowl and add syrup, stirring until all pieces are coated.
Line an 8 x 8-inch pan with foil and spray with nonstick coating.
Press in mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Lift from pan, peel off foil and cut into bars.
Wrap each bar in plastic wrap.

title: crab dip
directions: First Layer:
Mix and spread cream cheese, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, mayonnaise and chopped onions.

title: pan seared salmon(with mushroom reduction)
directions: Heat 2 Tbsp. of the oil, add chopped scallions and saute in a large frying pan until nearly cooked.
Add garlic and saute until soft.
Add mushrooms and chicken broth.
Simmer until liquid is reduced by half.
Transfer to a small saucepan, but do not clean out the frying pan (any liquid still coating the side of the pan will add to the flavor of the salmon).

title: chicken eugene
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
Lightly spray 9 by 13 baking dish with cooking spray.
Wrap each chicken breast with 1 slice of ham, place in baking dish.
Mix cream of mushroom soup and sour cream, pour over chicken.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Combine brown sugar, butter, corn syrup and salt in a 2-quart glass bowl.
Microwave on High setting 3 to 4 minutes, stirring after each minute until mixture comes to a boil.
Microwave 2 more minutes; stir in baking soda.
Pour syrup mixture over popped corn and peanuts in paper bag; shake well.
Microwave on High setting for 1 1/2 minutes.
Shake bag well.
Repeat microwave and shake steps.
Pour caramelized popcorn into large roasting pan.
Cool and stir to separate caramel corn kernels.

title: zucchini bites
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a jelly roll pan or spray with Pam.
Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into pan; bake for 35 minutes, or until golden and set.
Let cool for 15 minutes.
Cut into bite size squares.

title: tuna rice casserole
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together; press into 9-inch pie plate. Drain tuna; break into pieces and place on rice mixture.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over tuna.
Mix last 6 ingredients well.
Pour over rice and tuna.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 40 minutes.
Remove cover.
Bake another 5 to 10 minutes.

title: swedish butter cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Press out onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 325° oven.
Do not overbake.
Should be very light.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and marshmallows.
Stir.
Cook until marshmallows and sugar melt.
When bubbles cover entire top of mixture, boil for 5 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat. Add butter, chocolate chips and salt and mix together.
Add nuts if desired.
Spread in buttered pan.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: poor man's cookies
directions: Place first 4 ingredients into a saucepan.
Simmer for 20 minutes, then cool.
Stir in the remaining ingredients until well mixed.
Pour into a greased and floured pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
While still warm, brush top with powdered sugar frosting. Cut into squares.

title: tupperware bread
directions: In Fix-N-Mix bowl, place flour.
Scald milk.
Cool with water, sugar, salt, beaten eggs and yeast.
Pour liquid in well.
Do not stir.
Seal and burp.
Wait until seal pops up.
Don't break seal. Melt butter or oleo.
Pour in bowl and mix.
Knead to consistency. Add more flour if necessary.
Seal and burp.
Wait until seal pops. Knead and roll in rolls or make into 3 loaves of bread.
Let rise in pan 20 minutes or longer.
Bake at 375° until brown and crusty.

title: old-fashioned banana pudding
directions: Beat whole eggs together.
Add milk and beat.
Mix flour, sugar and salt; add to eggs and milk.
Stir well.
Cook in double boiler until thickens.
Chop up bananas and add butter and flavoring to mixture in boiler.
Put a layer of mixture in bottom of bowl and add a layer of wafers and a layer of bananas.
Continue this way until all mixture is gone.
Top with slices of bananas and wafers.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery in margarine until soft; add mushrooms, mushroom soup, roll of garlic cheese and cooked broccoli.
Heat and serve.

title: coo-coo
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add corn meal.
Stir in onion and parsley.
When hot, add fish.

title: french toast casserole
directions: Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
(Be sure the butter coats the bottom corners of baking dish.)
Stir in brown sugar and cinnamon.
Place bread slices in double layer (one slice directly on top of each other) over sugar mixture.
Beat eggs and milk together.
Pour over bread slices.
Cover and let stand overnight in fridge.

title: norwegian waffles(as serves at t.m.y.)
directions: Mix dry ingredients together; lightly beat eggs and add with buttermilk and water to dry mix.
Mix well with a whisk and then add melted butter.
Stir into batter.
Makes about 15 waffles.

title: lemon pecan cake
directions: Save 1/2 cup flour and mix well with nuts and raisins.
Cream butter and sugar; add well beaten eggs.
Add flour and baking powder that have been sifted together.
Add lemon extract; add nuts and raisins, that have been mixed with the flour.
Pour batter in large Bundt cake pan.
Preheat oven to 250°.
Bake at 250° for three hours.
Let cool in pan.
You can put a glaze on cake if so desired.

title: pea and macaroni salad
directions: Chill macaroni and when cool, mix in vegetables.
Moisten with Miracle Whip.
Season with salt and pepper.
Mix cheese with salad. If you want, top with cheese in bowl or on salad plates.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Stir and cook the jello, sugar, corn starch, and salt until clear. Fill a baked pie shell with berries. Then pour the cooked mixture over the berries. Cool and serve with whipped cream.

title: peas and bacon
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon and saute onion.
Add flour and blend.
Add cream to make a white sauce.
Saute mushrooms in butter.
Add peas, mushrooms and bacon, broken into small pieces, to cream mixture.
Heat and serve.

title: jello cake
directions: Dissolve lemon Jell-O in 1 cup of hot water.
Let cool.
Add Wesson oil, cake mix and lemon flavoring, then add four eggs (beaten to the mixture).
Bake at 325° for 1 hour in a small tube pan which has been greased and floured.
When done, pour the following sauce over cake while warm:
2 cups confectioners sugar and 5 tablespoons lemon juice.

title: lasagne
directions: In
large pan brown beef and onion in oil Add tomatoes, tomato paste,
water,
parsley,
salt,
sugar, garlic powder, pepper and oregano.
Simmer uncovered stirring often, about 30 minutes.
Cook noodles as directed on package and drain.
In a 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish, spread about 1 cup of sauce, then a
layer
of noodles,
sauce
and
Ricotta cheese, Mozzarella cheese
and Parmesan
cheese.
Repeat with this filling until all
is
used. Bake
to 40 minutes at 350° until slightly browned and bubbly. Allow to stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: ribs
directions: Boil for 30 to 40 minutes; drain them.
Then put ribs in baking dish and brush often with barbecue sauce while ribs bake at 350° for an hour or until done.
Use favorite barbecue sauce.
Serves 4 people.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: In a bowl, beat egg yolks and stir in sweetened condensed milk.
Add lemon juice.
Put into pie shell.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Put ingredients into pie shell.
Bake for about 5 minutes. Take out of oven and place meringue on top of pie.
Bake until meringue is brown.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Cream potatoes and margarine, then add sugar and beat well. Add eggs and remaining ingredients.
Beat well.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Add topping and continue cooking 10 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken-peanut stew from ghana
directions: Carrots, zucchini and squash may be added as desired.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour together; add beaten eggs and butter.
Mix vanilla, chips and nuts; pour into flour/sugar mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese ball
directions: In small mixing bowl, beat together the cream cheese and salad dressing.
Beat in pimento and American cheese.
Add Worcestershire sauce and onion powder.
Chill at least 1 hour. Shape into ball.
Press chopped nuts over outside of ball.
Chill until firm.

title: sour cream chocolate sheet cake
directions: Combine flour, soda, sour cream, salt, sugar and beaten eggs in a large bowl.
Mix until smooth; set aside.
In a small saucepan, combine butter, water and chocolate; bring to a boil.
Add chocolate mixture to batter; mix together very well.
Batter will be thin.
Pour batter into greased 17 x 11 1/2 x 1 jellyroll pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool in pan on wire rack.

title: stromboli
directions: Combine 1 1/4 c. flour, yeast, sugar and salt in a bowl. Blend together. Heat water, milk and oil until warm. Add the egg and the warm liquid to the flour mixture. Blend well. Add remaining flour. Knead for 5 minutes until smooth and pliable. Cover and let rise for 1 hour. Roll out into a rectangle shape and layer with filling.

title: ambrosia
directions: *Jody Holladay uses green grapes in place of cherries.

title: millie's peanut brittle
directions: Boil sugar, water and corn syrup until it threads.
Add butter and peanuts;
cook slowly to 300°, stirring occasionally.
Add soda and vanilla.
(It
will
foam	up.)
Turn out on buttered baking sheet;
pull out thin as it cools.
When cold, break into pieces with knife handle.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all of ingredients together, except for butter and crackers.
Combine crackers and melted butter together and cover the top of casserole.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cucumbers with yogurt and garlic
directions: Mix yogurt, lemon juice, garlic powder, parsley, salt and pepper with a big spoon or a whisk.
Pour over cucumbers.

title: salsa dip
directions: Mix thoroughly and refrigerate at least one half hour.
Serve with corn chips.
Easy to make and easy to keep ingredients on hand and is delicious.

title: marinated cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and put in ice water and let stand.
Slice onion very thin into rings, then separate.
Slice pepper; slice chestnuts thin.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix first eight ingredients together. Add apples and nuts last. Bake 55 minutes to one hour at 350°. Cool 10 minutes before taking out of pan.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cut
flour, Crisco and baking soda in mixing bowl until it resembles
cornmeal.
Add
milk; roll out on floured board and cut
into
strips.
Let dry for 30 minutes before placing over your
boiled
and
deboned chicken.
Cook for 20 minutes without taking the lid off the pan.

title: breaded chicken tenders(chicken breast, veal or fish)
directions: *Amount of ingredients depends on the amount of meat you prepare.

title: hamburger steak
directions: Heat oil in electric frying pan or skillet.
Coat all pieces of meat with flour, salt and pepper.
Brown both sides of meat at 350°.
Remove steaks to platter and set aside.
Add 1 tablespoon flour to drippings in skillet, stir in.
Add milk and soup.
Mix well.
Put steaks back in gravy.
Reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Bake as directed and cool completely, then split layers in half.
(Yellow cake mix can be used.)

title: salmon appetizers
directions: Drain salmon and remove bones.
Combine salmon, cream cheese, picante, cilantro and cumin in a small bowl.
Spread about 2 tablespoons of mixture over each tortilla.
Roll each tortilla tightly.
Place tortillas, covered, in refrigerator for 2 hours. Remove from refrigerator and slice each tortilla into bite size pieces.

title: joe t.'s margarita
directions: Blend with ice for frozen margarita, or pour over ice.

title: cranberry orange relish
directions: Wash cranberries.
Peel oranges and chop rind in very small pieces.
Chop orange pulp and cranberries very fine.
Mix fruits with sugar.
This will keep in refrigerator for over a week without sealing or you may pour into hot sterilized jars and seal to keep longer.

title: carrot sheet cake
directions: Mix together dry ingredients and set aside.
Beat eggs and add oil.
Combine dry ingredients and egg mixture.
Fold in grated carrots and nuts.
Pour in sprayed jelly roll or sheet cake pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes; cool.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: cheese spread for hors d'oeuvres
directions: Melt cheese and add remaining ingredients.
Can be kept in fridge for a long time.

title: ground beef porcupines
directions: Combine ground beef, rice, onion, salt and pepper in bowl; mix well.
Shape into 12 balls.
Brown in shortening in heavy skillet; drain.
Add soup and hot water.
Simmer, covered, for 1 1/2 hours or until rice is tender.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: old fashion lemon sherbet
directions: Mix and freeze in hand-cranked freezer.

title: cheddar cheese ball
directions: Soften first 3 ingredients to room temperature. Add remaining ingredients. Beat until smooth. Chill for 4 to 24 hours. Shape into ball and roll in nuts.

title: cheesy chicken
directions: Mix bread crumbs with cheese, parsley, salt and pepper.
Mix butter and garlic.
Dip chicken breasts into melted butter; dredge in crumb mixture and arrange in single layer in 9 x 13-inch Pam sprayed baking dish.
Sprinkle remaining butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: english tea muffins
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: grandma belle's cupcakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add flour alternately with milk and flavoring.
Fold in fruit if using. Fill well-greased cupcake pans 2/3 full.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°. Cool and frost with Grandma Belle's Chocolate Frosting.

title: ice cream sandwich dessert
directions: Use a 9 x 13 pan. First layer ice cream sandwiches. Layer in order the ingredients given. Repeat layers again. Put in freezer. Slice and serve with a dip of Cool Whip and cherry.

title: zucchini casserole supreme
directions: Wash and slice zucchini; do not peel.
Put in layers in casserole, sprinkling each layer with soy grits and a little salt. Fill casserole and top with a few grits.
Pour in tomato soup, adding water, if necessary, to cover.
Cover and bake in moderate oven until done, about 1 hour.
Remove cover for last 15 minutes to brown.
Do not have casserole too full, because grits swell. Serves 6.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: *Note:
I use 1 cup black walnuts and 1 cup pecans for the 2 cups of nuts.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Saute onion in butter over low heat until golden.
In a large bowl, beat the egg slightly.
Add milk and stuffing; let stand for 5 minutes.
Add the ground meat, parsley, onion, salt and pepper; mix lightly, but thoroughly.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar and add the rest of the ingredients. Spread in 2 (8 or 9-inch) greased pans and spread with icing of your choice.

title: non-edible play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Cook in boiler or Dutch oven for 3 minutes on medium heat, stirring (mixture will be lumpy).
Knead while warm.
Store in airtight container.

title: frozen blueberry pie
directions: Have pie crust ready.
Defrost blueberries for 2 to 3 hours at room temperature.
In mixing bowl, combine berries and lemon juice.
Blend flour, cornstarch, sugar and salt.
Sprinkle a little over bottom of crust.
Stir the rest into berries.
Dot with butter.
Seal crust good and press down.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 1/2 hour more.

title: crab hot dish
directions: Mix altogether in a large bowl.
Use 1/2 of grated cheese. Save the other half for the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Mix together jam, dressing and soup mix.
Pour over chicken. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Remove chicken.
Stir cooked rice into juice.

title: heavenly cherry pie
directions: Combine flour, nuts and melted oleo.
Pat into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch Corningware dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese and sugar well; then fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over cool crust.
Then spread cherry pie filling over top.
Chill several hours.

title: oatmeal scotchies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In bowl, combine flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon; set aside.
In bowl, beat butter, both sugars, eggs and vanilla extract until creamy.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in oats and morsels.
Drop by level tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for
7 to 8 minutes for chewier cookies, or 9 to 10 minutes for crisper cookies.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and baking soda. Add remaining ingredients, mixing well. Pour into 2 well greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 min. Let pans cool 10 min. Loosen edges around pan.
Remove loaves and place on cooling rack. Let cool completly. Then wrap tightly. Can be frozen.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Mix all of this real good together and pour into 2 graham cracker pie shells.
Let stand at least 3 hours in refrigerator before serving.
Makes 2 pies.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Crush vanilla wafers.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs. Add milk and wafers, alternately.
Add coconut; beat well.
Add nuts; beat well.
Bake in tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 275°.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Put butter, sugar, molasses and egg into mixing bowl; beat well until creamy.
Sift flour, soda, salt and spices together.
Add to creamed mixture; blend well.
Form into balls.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Place about 2 inches apart on greased baking sheets.
Bake about 10 minutes.
Let cool a little before removing to cooling trays.

title: cream nuts
directions: Mix sugars and sour cream. Cook over low heat, stirring continuously, until sugar dissolves. Cook until mixture reaches medium-soft ball stage. Remove from heat. Add vanilla and nuts. Stir until coating begins to form on nuts. Turn out onto waxed paper.
Separate and cool.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage until tender; drain.
Pour into casserole dish. Cover with cheese sauce.
Sprinkle dry dressing mix on top.
Bake in a 325° oven until bubbly.

title: great pumpkin dessert
directions: In bowl, combine first five ingredients.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2 inch pan. Sprinkle dry cake mix over.
Drizzle with melted butter, add chopped nuts.

title: mini-franks in dilly buns
directions: Separate rolls into triangle shapes.
Cut each half to make a long, thin triangle.
Combine butter, curry powder, dill weed and mustard.
Spread thinly on surface of rolls.
Place a frank on triangle at broad end.
Roll the triangle around frank.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: balsamic chicken with peppers
directions: In large frying pan, saute five cloves of garlic in olive oil. Add chicken.
Season with parsley, rosemary, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until lightly browned.
Add balsamic vinegar and water.
Simmer an additional five minutes.
In a separate pan, saute peppers, onion and remaining garlic in olive oil until desired tenderness.
Serve pepper mixture over balsamic chicken.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Melt butter; mix first 4 ingredients.
Press into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Melt chips and peanut butter over low heat; pour over crust.
Chill.
When ready to serve, remove from refrigerator; cut at room temperature.

title: chicken loaf
directions: Combine chopped chicken with stuffing mix and add enough chicken broth to moisten well. Add beaten eggs. Bake in a greased loaf pan about 1 hour at 375°.

title: magic cookie bars(bar cookies)
directions: Heat oven at 350° (325° for glass).
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, melt margarine.
Sprinkle graham crackers into margarine and mix together.
Pat into pan.
Pour milk evenly over crackers.
Pour chocolate chips, coconut and nuts over top and press gently into crackers.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into bars.
Store in airtight container.

title: almond cookies
directions: Mix all but flour, baking soda and almonds together well, then incorporate the dry ingredients into the first mixture.
Batter will be very stiff.
Roll into 2 long rolls, about 1 1/2 inches in diameter.
Wrap in wax paper.
Chill in refrigerator overnight. Slice 3/4-inch thick slices; place on a greased cookie sheet. Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: bubble pizza bread
directions: Melt margarine in 8-inch round baking pan and rotate to cover bottom.
Combine tomato puree, onion, parsley, garlic salt, oregano and oil.
Separate biscuit dough and cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Drop into tomato mixture, tossing lightly with fork. Place pieces in buttered pan and distribute evenly.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 18 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 40 canapes.

title: easy pecan rolls
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put pecans in bottom; place frozen dinner rolls over nuts.
Sprinkle dry pudding over rolls.
Boil sugar and oleo and pour over rolls.
Cover with plastic wrap and let set on counter overnight.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Let set in pan 10 minutes before turning out.

title: cowboy stew
directions: Combine beef, onion, salt and pepper in a large heavy pot. Cook over medium heat until meat is cooked. Add water and potatoes to meat; cover and cook until potatoes are done. Add remaining ingredients and heat thoroughly.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Break
up lettuce and line a 9 x 12-inch or 9 x 13-inch pan. Cut up crisp celery. Sprinkle on lettuce. Chop onion as fine as possible. Sprinkle over celery.
Open and drain water chestnuts. Spread over onion. Spread evenly over all the frozen peas.
Mix the mayonnaise with the sugar.
Spread over the peas. Refrigerate, covered, overnight (or at least 5 hours). When serving, sprinkle with hard-boiled eggs and bacon bits.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix and pour into greased and floured pans.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
(Mixture will be thick.)

title: apple dumplings
directions: Combine sugar, water, cinnamon, nutmeg and red food coloring in a saucepan.
Bring to boiling point.
Add butter or margarine to hot syrup.

title: hawaiian cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage and drain.
Brown meat, onion and pepper; drain. Add the 4 spices.
Add rice and tomatoes; simmer.
Layer cabbage, ground beef mixture and cheese.
Make 2 layers.
Bake at 350° to 375° until bubbly and cheese melts.
Will feed 25 people (1/2 cup each).

title: banana-pineapple salad(very rich)
directions: Drain juice from pineapple.
Reserve juice and add to sugar, flour and egg.
Cook until thick.
Add butter and cool.
Dice pineapple chunks and add to sauce.
Add marshmallows and bananas, thinly sliced.
Whip 1/2 pint cream.
Fold cream into cooked salad and fruit mixture.
Pour into serving bowl.
If desired, sprinkle thinly chopped nuts over top.
Chill thoroughly.
(This rich dessert-like salad can be made a day ahead.)

title: chicken curry
directions: Simmer chicken 3 to 4 hours or until tender.
Remove chicken and reduce stock to 3 cups.
Cut chicken from bones in fairly large pieces; dredge in flour and lightly brown.
Saute onions in butter.
Add flour and pour in hot stock, stirring constantly. Add raisins, apples, chicken and seasonings.
Simmer about 10 minutes and add cream.
Serve on fluffy rice with curry accompaniments.
Serves 6.

title: fluffy pumpkin angel torte
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix as directed.
Remove 1 cup of batter.
Mix together pumpkin, cinnamon, ginger, cloves and the cup of batter.
Fold into cake batter.
Bake cake and cool. Split cake into 3 layers.
Mix the 1/4 cup pumpkin into Cool Whip. Frost each layer with Cool Whip mixture, then frost sides and top.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon.

title: goulash
directions: Fry hamburger.
Cook spaghetti in water (don't drain off water).
Add puree and catsup to hamburger.
Add red beans.
Add spaghetti.
Pour in flat pan.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes.

title: cheese meat loaf
directions: Chop onion.
Mix all ingredients well.
Shape in a loaf in a baking pan.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour, until browned.
Makes 6 servings.

title: ground beef stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add onions, garlic and mushrooms.
Saute until onions are golden brown.
Put in crock pot with remaining ingredients; stir thoroughly.
Cook 6 to 8 hours.
Serve over hot noodles or rice.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Combine milk, lemonade and Cool Whip (don't beat).
Place in graham cracker crust and freeze.

title: juanita's goulash
directions: Cook ground beef and onion; drain.
Add corn, peas, stewed tomatoes, tomato sauce and salt to ground beef mixture and simmer 1/2 hour or until vegetables are done.
Serves about 6.

title: potato rolls
directions: Heat milk, butter and salt.
Mix yeast and water, let set.
In bowl mix potatoes and eggs.
Add yeast and milk and beat with mixer.
Add 2 cups of flour.
Slowly add sugar and remaining flour with spoon.
Turn out on board, knead.
Put in greased bowl, cover lightly and put in refrigerator.
Will double in size.
Use later in day or overnight.
Dough may be used for dinner rolls or for cinnamon rolls.
Place in greased pans and bake at 350°.

title: pickled hot peppers
directions: In a large kettle, combine ingredients.
Boil 1 minute.
Add peppers.
Heat thoroughly.
Put in jar and seal.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into fourths.
Mix sugar with cinnamon; roll biscuits into sugar mix.
Turn, then place in a round 9-inch pan. Melt margarine and mix with remaining sugar mixture.
Drizzle over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Invert on serving plate, then pull apart and eat.

title: freak out
directions: Let ice
cream soften.
Crumble cookies; mix all ingredients. Freeze and eat.
Freak out!

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Halve and core peppers.
Mix other ingredients.
Place in peppers.

title: seafood enchilada(microwave)
directions: In mixing bowl, stir soup, onion and dash of pepper.
In another bowl, stir together half of the soup mixture, spinach, crab and cheese.
Set aside. Wrap tortillas in paper towels and microwave on High power for 30 to 60 seconds.
Place 1/3 of the crab mixture on each tortilla and roll up.
Place, seam side down, in greased 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch dish. Stir milk into reserved soup mixture.
Pour over enchiladas.
Cook, covered, on High 12 to 14 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Let stand 10 minutes. Garnish with cilantro, if desired.

title: chocolate and cream cheese dessert
directions: Blend first 4 items and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 300°.
Blend cream cheese, confectioners sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread over crust after it cools.

title: gary's cheese ball
directions: Mix first five ingredients and form into a ball.
Roll in chopped pecans.
Best with Chicken and Biscuit crackers.

title: cheese hermits
directions: Grate cheese.
Mix all ingredients together and make into small balls (about 1 teaspoon batter).
Place 1-inch apart on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: frozen punch
directions: Freeze all
but ale in 2 quart milk cartons until ready to use.
Have	ale
cold.
Put
frozen
contents
in a pot and crush slightly.
Pour in ale and mix.

title: buttermilk pancakes(low-fat)
directions: Place the buttermilk, egg whites, cottage cheese, maple syrup or honey and vanilla in a blender.
Process until smooth.
Add the flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Blend well.
Coat a nonstick frying pan with nonstick spray.
Heat on medium until hot.
Place about 1/4 cup batter into the pan for each pancake. Sizzle until lightly browned and cooked through, about 3 1/2 minutes on each side.

title: beef and potato loaf
directions: In a greased 2-quart baking dish, evenly arrange potatoes and 1 tablespoon onion.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and parsley.
Mix beef, evaporated milk, bread crumbs, catsup, onion, salt and pepper.
Spread evenly over potatoes.

title: baked pizza sandwich
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Grease a 9 x 12-inch pan. Cook the beef until brown.
Drain.

title: cubed round steak
directions: Cut steak into 1 inch cubes.
Add 1/2 cup flour and fry in hot oil.
Season with garlic salt, salt and pepper; cook to desired doneness.

title: lemon bread
directions: Combine all the ingredients except for the lemon juice and the additional 1/2 cup sugar and pour into ungreased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Then, mix 2 to 3 tablespoons of lemon juice with 1/2 cup sugar and pour over the finished baked cake.
Put back into the oven for 8 minutes more.
Very good!!

title: buster bar dessert
directions: Stir melted margarine in crushed Oreos.
Reserve 1 cup. Spread crumb mixture in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 smaller pans.
Spread ice cream over crumbs (works better if you just slice ice cream and place over crumbs).
Freeze a few minutes. Spread with chocolate fudge topping.
Top with peanuts and Cool Whip.
Sprinkle reserved crumbs on top.
Freeze.
Thaw at room temperature for 15 minutes before serving.

title: quick fudge
directions: Blend sugar and cocoa in large mixing bowl.
Add margarine and milk (do not stir).
Microwave 2 minutes on High.
Remove from oven; stir.
Mix in vanilla and nuts.
Pour in greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Refrigerate until set.
Cut and serve.

title: texas millionaires
directions: Mix sugars, Karo, oleo and 1 cup milk.
Cook to a rolling boil. Add remaining milk slowly.
Cook until soft ball stage is reached. Add pecans and pour up.

title: divinity
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water thoroughly, then cook until it forms a medium ball when dropped into cold water.
Pour 2/3 of syrup over beaten egg whites, beating constantly.
Cook other 1/3 of syrup until it forms a very firm ball, then beat it slowly into the first mixture, beating constantly, until creamy.
Add nuts and vanilla; mix.
Drop on waxed paper or buttered tin.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and beat thoroughly after each egg.
Add crushed vanilla wafers, pecans, coconut and vanilla. Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or at 325° for 1 3/4 hours.
Put water in pan on shelf below cake.

title: caramel flan
directions: Place sugar in a large, heavy skillet.
Cook over medium heat until sugar melts and forms a light brown syrup; stir to blend. Immediately pour syrup into a heated 8 1/4-inch round, shallow baking dish.
Holding dish with pot holders, quickly rotate to cover bottom and sides completely.
Set aside.
Preheat oven to 325°.

title: scalloped eggplant
directions: Peel and chop eggplant.
Cook in water until tender.
Drain and add salt and pepper.
Mash thoroughly.
Crumble the cornbread. Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Additional grated cheese can be sprinkled on top the last 10 minutes, if desired.

title: pashka(a russian orthodox easter feast favorite)
directions: Place the cream cheese in a large wire strainer set over a small mixing bowl.
Cover the cheese with a clean cloth and place a heavy weight on top.
Leave the cheese to drain for at least 1 1/2 hours.
Discard any liquid in the bowl.
Transfer the cheese to a large bowl.
With a wooden spoon, beat the butter into the cheese a little at a time and continue beating until the mixture is blended.

title: spinach souffle
directions: In a small heavy saucepan, melt margarine. Blend in flour. Cook until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat and gradually stir in milk.

Return to heat and bring mixture to a boil, stirring constantly. Cook 1 minute longer. Remove from heat. Stir in spinach, onion, nutmeg and pepper. Beat egg whites until stiff. Fold gently into spinach mixture. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Pour into a 1 1/4-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Serve immediately.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Sprinkle 1/2 cup cracker crumbs in a lightly greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Cover with half the oysters; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Dot with half the butter and cover with half the remaining cracker crumbs.
Repeat layers with remaining oysters, salt, pepper, butter and cracker crumbs.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter, syrup and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla. Mix well.
Add nuts.
Pour into 2 unbaked pastry shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Mix tomatoes (homegrown, canned or frozen) and homemade sweet pepper relish in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer for about 20 to 30 minutes.
Cook macaroni according to directions and drain.
Beginning with macaroni layer grated cheese, then tomato and relish sauce, about 2 layers of each.
Then cover with bacon in a 1 1/2-quart to quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until bacon is crisp.
Can be prepared the day before. If any is left over, cover to warm over.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Place in airtight container. Seal tightly.
Keeps for months.
Makes 2 gallons.
To use, add 1/3 cup mix to mug and fill with boiling water.
Stir well.

title: kielbasa simmered in beer and onions
directions: In a large heavy skillet, melt the butter and saute the onions over medium heat until translucent.
Add the kielbasa to the pan and brown it 3 to 4 minutes on each side.
Pour beer over the sausage and onions.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 25 minutes.
Remove kielbasa and onions from the pan and put them on a serving dish in a warm oven.
Reduce beer over high heat to 2 cups.
Pour over kielbasa.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cranberry delight
directions: Grease a 9-inch pie plate.
Spread berries over bottom of pie plate.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup of sugar over berries; add 1/2 cup walnuts.
Beat eggs, rest of sugar, flour and melted margarine together.
Pour mixture over berries.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese, then blend the jar of marshmallow cream together.
Use as a dip for any fresh fruit of your choice.

title: italian salad
directions: Break up lettuce into small pieces.
Add oranges.
Add sliced or whole black olives.
Add tuna.
Mix gently.
Add Italian dressing.

title: fruit and pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Stir together the mayonnaise or salad dressing, yogurt, marmalade and poppy seeds.
Fold into cooked pasta the strawberries, cantaloupe or honeydew, green or red grapes and green onions.
Cover and chill 2-8 hours.
Each 3/4 cup serving has 1 gram fat and 157 calories.

title: ham-macaroni salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise and mustard in a large bowl.
Add cooled macaroni, ham, onion, relish, salt and pepper; toss lightly until well blended.
Chill.

title: butterfinger pie
directions: Beat candy bars in a ziploc bag.
Mix cream cheese and small Cool Whip together.
Add crushed candy bars, reserving enough to sprinkle on top.
Pour into crust.
Sprinkle reserved candy on top.
Let set in refrigerator for at least 2 hours.

title: barbecue dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate at least one hour. Serve with pretzels, veggies, chips.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix together ground beef, oatmeal, onion, salt and pepper, egg and herbs and spices.
Form into balls and brown in skillet.
Place meatballs in crock-pot.
Add jar of chili sauce and jellied cranberry sauce.
Do not stir.
Start crock-pot on high.
After cranberry sauce melts, stir ingredients.
Cook on low for another 4 hours.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Makes 6 servings.

title: taco pie
directions: Spray pie pan with nonstick spray.
Preheat oven to temperature on crescent roll can.
Brown ground beef, drain.
Add seasoning and the suggested amount of water on package.
Let simmer while making a crust out of the crescent rolls.
Put a layer of crushed corn chips on top of crust, then place seasoned meat on top of chips. Put a layer of refried beans on top of meat, then a layer of sour cream.
Put another layer of crushed corn chips and then the cheese.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until crust is brown.
Serve with salsa.

title: save-a-penny casserole
directions: In a skillet, brown beef; drain.
Stir in soup, spaghetti, sauce and vegetables.
Put in an ungreased casserole dish (11 x 7 x 2-inch).
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Sprinkle with cheese and let stand a few minutes until cheese melts.

title: chicken noodle parmesan casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese in casserole dish; sprinkle cheese on top and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: best chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, and cocoa in a saucepan.
Add egg yolks, milk, vanilla, and margarine.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Pour into the baked pie shell and top with meringue.
Bake at 350° until brown on top.

title: "chalupas"(microwave)
directions: Layer the beans, lettuce, tomatoes, onions and cheese on the shells.
Then roll up and heat in microwave for about 2 or 3 minutes, until cheese is melted and beans are warm.
Can also be eaten cold.
It is just as good.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk.
Bring mixture to full rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 5 minutes over medium heat. Remove and stir in peanut butter, marshmallow cream and vanilla. Beat until well blended.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Makes 3 pounds.

title: corn flakes candy
directions: Heat sugar and syrup,
add peanut butter and stir until melted.
Stir in corn flakes
and
press
in
a
greased dish. Cool until set, then cut into squares.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Roll out like pie crust, cover with flour and double back one half over the other.
Press again with a rolling pin, again cover top of dough with flour.
Start at one end and roll dough into a roll.
Slice from end of roll in very thin slices.
Drop into boiling broth.
Do not stir, just pull apart.
Do not cover.
Boil 5 minutes.

title: brisket
directions: Sprinkle garlic powder, celery salt and onion flakes generously on brisket and place in pan.
Pour hickory smoke and Worcestershire sauce over brisket and marinate overnight.

title: doughnuts
directions: Add sugar, shortening and salt to milk.
When lukewarm, add yeast (mixed with 2 tablespoons warm ???).
Add 2 cups flour to make soft sponge.
Set in warm place to rise.
When light, add eggs, nutmeg and flour to make a light dough.
Cover and let rise until double in bulk.
Knead on floured board.
Roll to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with doughnut cutter.
Cover and let rise again. Fry in deep oil at 375°.
Drain on paper towels.
Makes 30 doughnuts.

title: pinched buns
directions: Follow roll package directions, but add 1 tablespoon sugar. When rolls are ready to roll out, cut into 2 inch rounds; place teaspoon of meat mixture in center.
Pinch ends up around meat to cover.
Place pinched together sides at bottom of greased muffin pan; let rise 30 minutes.
Cook 10 minutes; brush cooked rolls with butter.

title: sweet rolls
directions: Mix the yeast and warm water together and let set.
In large glass bowl, put boiling water, sugar and oleo or butter.
Let cool.
When cool, mix in eggs.
Add to yeast mixture.
Mix altogether and add flour.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: macaroon pie
directions: Mix beaten eggs, sugar, margarine, lemon juice and vanilla; stir in coconut.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes or until knife inserted just off center comes out clean.

title: light chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray two 8-inch round baking pans with cooking spray.
Stir flour, cocoa and baking soda; set aside.
In saucepan, melt corn oil spread and stir in sugar.
Remove from heat.
Add milk, vinegar and vanilla to mixture in saucepan; stir. Add dry ingredients; whisk until well blended.
Pour evenly into pans.
Bake 20 minutes.
Cool.
Frost.
Refrigerate.
Yields 12 servings.

title: cream cheese pinch cookies
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Roll dough; make into squares. Fill with filling.
Pinch dough over the filling so they stay together.
Bake in a 350° oven for 7 to 10 minutes, or until golden brown.
Cool; sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Enjoy.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole lightly or spray with vegetable oil spray.
Cook mushrooms and green peppers in oil until green peppers are tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Mix broth with milk.
Slowly add flour to mixture; stirring constantly. Cook until thickened.
Stir in turkey and pimento.
Mix in spaghetti.
Pour in casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese at 350° (moderate oven) until bubbly throughout, about 30 minutes.
Makes four 1-cup servings.

title: apricot pork chops
directions: Drain apricots, reserving 1/4 cup syrup.
Cut apricots in half.
In skillet, brown chops (use shortening, if necessary). Pour off fat.
Stir in soup, sour cream, reserved syrup and green onions.
Cover; cook over low heat 25 minutes or until done.
Stir occasionally.
Add apricots; cook 5 minutes more.
Serve with rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fudge
directions: Boil milk, sugar and salt for 6 minutes; stir constantly while boiling.
Pour over remaining ingredients that have been mixed together.
Beat until stiff.
Put in buttered pan.

title: pecan snacks
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 13 inch pan. Stir in garlic salt and pecans. Bake at 350° until roasted. Very different but very good!

title: crepes
directions: Place ingredients in blender container in order given. Blend 30 seconds. Stop and stir down sides. Blend 30 to 60 seconds until smooth or mix in bowl with wire whisk or mixer. First combine flour and eggs, adding liquid gradually. Beat until smooth and add other ingredients. Makes about 16 crepes. Pour in crepe machine. If you don't have a machine, pour about a 6-inch round in a nonstick skillet. Takes only a small amount of time to cook.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1/2 cup cheese and 1 cup French fried onions.
Pour into shallow 1-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until vegetables are done.
Top with cheese and onions, bake, uncovered, 5 minutes or until onions are golden.
Makes 6 servings.

title: grannie's cranberry jello mold
directions: Boil water; add Jell-O and dissolve real good.
Add the strawberries and cranberry sauce.
Add pineapple.
Place in mold or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
Goes good with turkey or ham.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt chips over low heat.
Add noodles and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: no-bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk and butter in saucepan.
Bring to a full boil and boil for 1 minute.
Add oatmeal, peanut butter, cocoa and vanilla.
Stir all together, then spoon onto wax paper.
Let cool until firm.

title: peppery pasta with feta cheese
directions: Heat oil in heavy Dutch oven over medium-high heat.
Add both bell peppers and garlic.
Saute until peppers begin to soften, about 4 minutes.
Mix in pepperoncini and basil, then tomatoes. Simmer until sauce reduces slightly, breaking up tomatoes with back of spoon, about 5 minutes.
Add pasta and toss until sauce coats pasta.
Add Feta and toss mixture to blend.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: (Mix by hand.) This is a one-bowl cake. Mix oil and sugar well. Add eggs, flour and cinnamon. Mix in the baking soda and the buttermilk. Add the apples and pecans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes in a greased and floured Bundt pan.

title: pineapple lemon punch
directions: Put all this in a gallon jug.
Finish with water

title: tandy cake
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, milk, vanilla, flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread peanut butter over warm cake.
Let cool.
After cooled, melt chocolate bar and spread over peanut butter.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: grandma lettie's banana bread
directions: Bake at 350° for at least 40 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding mix, milk, sour cream and 1/2 of the Cool Whip together.
Layer the wafers, bananas and pudding mix in a large, flat baking dish.
Cover with remaining Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: real country style omelet
directions: In an 8-inch skillet cook bacon in one tablespoon margarine until brown.
Add potatoes; saute until tender and golden.
In a bowl, with a fork, beat eggs with seasonings and parsley.
Stir in potato mixture.
In the same skillet, heat remaining margarine. Pour in egg mixture.
As eggs set at edge, using a spatula, draw this portion toward center so that uncooked portions flow to bottom.
When omelet starts to brown on bottom, divide it in half; turn each half over to brown other side.
Then with spatula, lift each half to a plate.
Serve at once.
Makes 2 generous servings.

title: party mix
directions: Mix the margarine, oil, salts and sauces.
Mix the cereal in large roasting pan.
Pour margarine mix over cereals.
Cook at 250° for approximately 2 hours, stirring every 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Cream shortening, peanut butter and sugars together.
Sift flour, soda and salt together and blend with creamed mixture.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Shape by teaspoonfuls into balls.
Roll in sugar and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and place a Hershey's Kiss on top of each cookie, pressing down so that cookie cracks around edge.
Return to oven and bake 2 to 5 minutes longer.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: blue cheese macaroni salad
directions: Combine ingredients and chill at least 1 hour.
Taste and adjust seasonings, if necessary.
Serve on a bed of lettuce or in tomato cups.
Serves about 12.

title: new banana pudding
directions: Split Twinkies lengthwise.
Place cream side up in bottom of 15x9x2 pan.
Peel bananas and slice over Twinkies.
Prepare pudding with milk.
Pour over top of bananas.
Spread to cover. Spread Cool Whip over pudding.
Cover and chill 12 servings.

title: tomato soup
directions: Cook tomatoes, celery, onion and pepper until tender; run through a sieve.
Return to stove; add other ingredients and cook until smooth and creamy.
Can process 5 minutes.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: chocolate yum yum pie
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa.
Combine with remaining ingredients and pour into the unbaked pie shell.
Bake in a preheated oven at 325° until set, about 55 minutes.
Serve cold with topping, if desired.

title: apple scotch loaf cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, oil and vanilla.
Add flour mixed with baking powder, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in nuts and apples.
Spread in well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with butterscotch chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender (may have to drain in colander).
Cook like pancakes.

title: spicy vegetable soup
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients in a large Dutch oven over medium heat.
Add spaghetti sauce and the next 6 ingredients.
Bring to a boil; cover and reduce heat.
Simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in tomatoes, chiles and vegetables.
Return to a boil.
Cover and simmer 10 to 12 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Yields 12 cups.

title: golden cornbread
directions: Beat all ingredients until smooth. Bake in 9-inch square pan at 400° for about 20 minutes.

title: bahamian macaroni
directions: In a large bowl beat eggs, add butter and vegetables (chopped fine, 1/2 cup between all 3).
Grate 2 packages of cheese on a plate.
Cook macaroni until done.
Drain, but do not rinse.
Put hot macaroni into bowl with eggs, butter, veggies.
Add in the shredded cheese and mix well until butter and cheese is melted. Add 3 cups of milk and mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13 pan.
Grate last brick of cheese and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 375 degrees.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Cook in a large saucepan.
Mix all ingredients excluding oats and vanilla.
Pour into a saucepan and stir until a full boil. Cook 1 1/2 minutes at a full boil.
Remove from heat; add quick cooking oats, vanilla and peanut butter (optional).
Spoon onto wax paper and cool.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix butter, shortening, 1 1/2 cups sugar, eggs and flour.
Roll into balls.
Mix together the 2 tablespoons each of sugar and cinnamon.
Dip the cookies into the sugar mixture.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: light fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add well beaten eggs, a little at a time!
Add flour and orange juice. Add fruits that have been sliced. Mix well. Bake in slow oven at 300° for 2 to 4 hours, depending on size of pan!

title: green tomato sandwich spread
directions: Put pepper and tomatoes through grinder and drain for 1 hour. Mix together flour and vinegar.
Add butter, cheese, salad dressing, mustard, sugar and salt.
Mix all ingredients together and boil for 20 minutes, stirring frequently.
Seal in jars while hot.

title: sausage and onion pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 425° until golden brown.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix and beat until smooth.
Form into a ball and put in fridge until firm.
Roll in 1/4 cup chopped nuts and 1 teaspoon parsley.

title: christmas salad
directions: Prepare
jello as directed in separate bowls.
Pour red jello into
x
13-inch
pan.
Chill until firm.
Pour lemon jello into bowl.
Chill just until thickened.
Beat with mixer and fold in cream
cheese, pineapple and nuts, if desired, and whipped cream.
Pour lemon mix over red.
Chill.
Pour chilled lime jello over lemon layer.
Chill.

title: raspberry pull aparts
directions: Cut dough in bite size pieces.
Put in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let rise.
Mix jello and sugars. Sprinkle over dough. Cut margarine in pieces over top. Bake at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into prepared crust.
Chill 3 hours or until set.
Top with desired amount of pie filling before serving.
Refrigerate leftovers
Makes one 9 inch pie.

title: $400 chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and brown sugar together. Add eggs and vanilla. Then add flour, ground oatmeal, soda and salt. Mix well. Grate chocolate bar into mix. Add chocolate chips and chopped nuts. Place golf ball sized mounds 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 6-8 minutes or until light brown. Makes 6-8 dozen.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Put ingredients in blender for brief time.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg or cinnamon.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then bake at 300° for 35 minutes or until it looks like a custard pie.
Makes one pie.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and oleo until fluffy.
Add eggs, beating well after each one.
Blend in flour until moist, then beat until smooth, about 2 minutes, at high speed.
Add lemon extract and lemon juice.
Fold in 7-Up.
Spoon into well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.
Cool on cake rack for 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: tuna timbal
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in buttered baking dish; bake
at
for 60 minutes.
Serve with Hollandaise Sauce or hard-boiled egg sauce.

title: porcupines
directions: Combine beef, rice, milk, onion, salt and pepper.
Make into good sized balls and put in baking dish.
Cover with soup and water.
Bake covered in 350 degree oven for approximately 40 minutes or until done.

title: mexican bean soup
directions: Place beans and water in a large soup pot.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat, cover and cook over medium-low heat for 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients and continue to cook for about 2 hours, until beans are tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cajun surprise soup
directions: Cook beef and onion until beef is lightly browned and onion is tender.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to simmer and cook for about 15 minutes.
Remove bay leaves before serving.

title: potato casserole
directions: Defrost potatoes.
Combine all ingredients with potatoes. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 12.

title: sour cream noodle bake
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain. Stir in tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 5 minutes. Combine noodles, cottage cheese, sour cream and onion in bowl; mix well.
Layer noodle mixture and ground beef mixture 1/2 at a time in nonstick 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350°
for 25 to 30 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: fruit bites
directions: Make a few days before serving.
Combine almonds, dates, sugar, egg whites and vanilla.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Heat oven to 325°.
Shape mixture into balls and top with cherry half.
Bake on greased cookie sheet 15 to 20 minutes.
Let stand 3 minutes. Store tightly covered.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: candied carrots
directions: Mix sugars and cinnamon.
Put on top of carrots.
Add juice and dot with butter.
Brown on top of stove or bake in oven (350°) as like sweet potatoes.

title: rice glorina
directions: Cook rice until tender.
Mix all ingredients into rice, except cream, and
let
stand
30 minutes.
Fold whipped cream into mixture just before serving.

title: baked beans supreme
directions: Fry bacon in skillet until crisp; remove.
Brown ground beef with onion in pan drippings, stirring until crumbly and drain. Combine beans, catsup, brown sugar, salt and pepper in a greased casserole dish; mix well.
Stir in beef mixture and bacon.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together; pour into buttered casserole.
Sprinkle 1 package dry Lipton's onion soup over casserole.
Lay pieces of cut up chicken on mixture.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: banana slush
directions: Heat water and sugar in saucepan, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Boil for 1 minute.
Refrigerate until cold.
Mix chilled mixture with pineapple juice, orange juice and lemonade concentrates and mashed bananas.
Pour into 5 (1-quart) containers; cover and freeze.
When ready to use, remove from freezer, defrost slightly and break into chunks with a fork.
Put in a punch bowl and add lemon-lime or ginger ale.

title: caramel apple cookies
directions: Combine cookie ingredients in their order in a large bowl. Roll dough 1/4-inch thick and cut apple shapes.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and insert wooden stick in each apple. Bake 8 to 9 minutes until slightly brown.
Cool about 2 minutes and remove, cooling completely.
Spread top of each cookie with glaze allowing it to drizzle down slightly.

title: honey oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix sugar, eggs, shortening and honey. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy. Gradually add oil and sugar, mixing well. Add zucchini and vanilla. Sift together in separate bowl the flour, soda, baking powder, salt and pumpkin pie spice. Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture. Mix only until moistened. Stir in pecans. Pour into 2 greased loaf pans. Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Put vegetables in pan and chicken on top.
Pour broth on top of these ingredients.
Make biscuit dough with ice water.
Cut out and place on top.
Melt stick margarine and brush on top.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: grandma birdie smith's icebox cake
directions: Boil the chocolate, granulated sugar and water together until smooth. Add the vanilla.
Cream together the butter, powdered sugar and 4 egg yolks. Stir this into the chocolate mixture. Fold all into the stiffly beaten egg whites.
Line a jelly roll pan with ladyfingers. Alternate with chocolate mixture and ladyfingers, ending with chocolate. Leave in refrigerator overnight. Serve with whipped cream.

title: chocolate covered peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together the sugar, peanut butter, margarine and vanilla; shape into balls.
Melt wax and chocolate chips in double boiler. Dip balls in chocolate, then let sit until firm, not sticky.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa together.
Cook for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add oatmeal, vanilla and peanut butter.
Drop on paper to cool.

title: holiday punch
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased pan. Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: brie and cranberry chutney melt
directions: Trim rind from top of Brie, and place on a microwave-safe serving plate.
Top with 1/3 cup cranberry chutney, and microwave at high 1 minute.
Sprinkle with bacon, and serve with crackers. Yield 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken ratatouille
directions: You will need 1 regular size (10 x 16-inch) Reynolds oven cooking bag.

title: refried beans
directions: Fill pressure cooker 2/3 full of water.
Add beans, 2 tablespoons oil and salt.
Cook for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at medium heat.

title: trumped up carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil until smooth.
