Add vanilla and pineapple.
Sift together flour, cinnamon, soda and salt.
Add to butter mixture.
Stir in carrots and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pork and beans
directions: Soak beans; cook a little, then add other ingredients.
Bake.

title: pollo con queso
directions: Remove skin and bones from cooked chicken and cube.
Combine soups, sour cream, onion, chiles and pimento for "soup mixture".

title: scalloped corn
directions: Cook butter and onion together in pan.
Add flour, salt, paprika and milk.
Cook as for cream sauce.
Add fresh or drained can corn. Add beaten egg and cook about 5 minutes.
Put mixture in casserole dish.

title: rolls
directions: Mix like biscuits. Let rise double. Punch down; roll and cut. Put in greased/oiled pan. Let rise. Bake at 350°.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Cream together 1/2 cup butter, brown sugar and flour.
Pat into well-greased and floured 8 x 8-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: egg sauce for boiled fowl
directions: Rub egg yolks, flour and butter together.
Add to hot stock slowly and let boil very slowly for about 5 minutes.
Take from heat; add whites of eggs (mashed with a fork).
Serve.

title: seaside salad
directions: Boil water, salt
and
oil; add macaroni and cook until tender (8 to 10 minutes).	Drain and cool.
Mix with remaining ingredients and
chill.
May
garnish with tomato wedge, hard-boiled egg wedge and/or parsley.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: holiday fruit salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: hershey kisses cookies
directions: Mix Eagle Brand, peanut butter, Bisquick mix and vanilla; shape into 1-inch balls and roll into sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° to 375° for 6 to 8 minutes or until lightly brown (watch carefully).
Remove from oven.
Immediately place chocolate Kiss in center of cookie.
Remove from pan and place them on wax paper until cool.
Enjoy.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook
twist
macaroni.	While
cooking, brown hamburger and onion.
When done, mix macaroni and hamburger.
Add pizza sauce, tomato paste, tomato sauce and sugar.
Mix all together and add garlic salt, onion salt and oregano.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Chop fine the onion, celery, mushroom stems and garlic.
Saute in butter. When crisp, add crackers (not too much, needs to be moist).
Fill mushrooms.
Cook at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: miniature cheesecakes
directions: You will need 24 cupcake liners.
Line cupcake pans with liners.
Place a vanilla wafer in bottom of each liner.

title: cinnamon pull apart bread
directions: Cut bread dough into thin slices, dip in melted butter and roll in cinnamon sugar.
Place in bread pan, allow to rise until double.
Bake according to bread dough instructions.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Place slices of buttered bread, buttered side up, with crusts cut off.
Place ham and cheese over the top.
Beat eggs and milk.
Pour over top.
Must sit overnight. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: colette's cinder cake
directions: Mix melted oleo with crushed Oreos, reserving 1 cup for topping. Press the rest in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. On top of this, add 1/2 gallon softened vanilla ice cream.
Spread whipped topping over ice cream. Drizzle chocolate syrup over topping and cover with remaining 1 cup Oreo mixture. Freeze.

title: ginger chicken
directions: Cut chicken in quarters.
Boil for 25 minutes.
Cool in refrigerator.
Chop chicken into serving pieces.
Mix rest of ingredients together.
Pour over chicken and serve.
tags: chicken broth from boiling of chicken

title: outrageous chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat sugar, margarine, peanut butter, vanilla and egg in medium bowl with wooden spoon until well blended and creamy.
Mix flour, oats, soda and salt; mix well and add chocolate chips. Drop by tablespoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool 1 minute before removing from cookie sheet.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix oil, eggs, sugar, vanilla and carrots thoroughly. Add salt, baking soda and baking powder, then mix in flour.
Nuts can be added last. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour in greased and floured pan.

title: chocolate caramel cake
directions: Prepare the cake mix as instructed on box.
Pour half of the batter into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Melt the caramels, evaporated milk and margarine until smooth.
Pour over baked cake.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts (optional) and 1/2 package chocolate chips.
Pour on rest of cake batter and sprinkle with nuts and rest of chips.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes. Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: sweet broiled grapefruit
directions: Cut membrane out of the center of each grapefruit half.
Cut around each section so it will be easy to spoon out when eating. Place 1 tablespoon of butter in the center of each half.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix together first 9 ingredients and press into pan.
Sprinkle chips on top and put topping over chips.

title: chili
directions: Brown and drain ground chuck and onion.
Add garlic, brown sugar, jalapeno juice, jalapenos, tomato juice and tomato sauce; simmer.
Add chili powder to taste.
If hotter chili preferred, add more jalapenos or chili powder.
Add spaghetti if desired.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Beat all ingredients together on low speed until blended. Drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: harvest vegetable casserole
directions: Place defrosted vegetables in a 9 x 12-inch dish.
Saute onion in 1/4 cup butter with salt and pepper.
Pour onion and butter over vegetables.
In saucepan, combine soup, sour cream and cheese.
Stir until cheese melts and is well blended.
Pour sauce over vegetables.
Evenly sprinkle crushed crackers over vegetables and pour remaining 1/4 cup butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: yellow cheese(soft cheese)
directions: *This can be made from nonfat powdered milk, also.

title: oven baked french fries
directions: Cut potatoes into strips.
Arrange on Teflon baking sheet, after dipping each strip into liquid Butter Buds or brush Butter Buds on potato pieces.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown; turn.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes more or until tender. Yields 4.
Low fat 0.02 g.

title: christmas salad
directions: Mix in order listed. This dessert freezes well.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes; cook. To make white sauce, brown butter and flour; add milk, salt and pepper, then stir in mushroom soup. Layer potatoes and cheese. Put sauce on top. Sprinkle with paprika. Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: sour cream apple squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine flour, brown sugar and butter at low speed until crumbly.
Stir in nuts.
Press 2 3/4 cups of crumb mixture into ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan or 40 to 45 minutes for 2 (9-inch) rounds.
Top with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: meringue
directions: Beat egg whites very stiff, stir in cream of tartar, sugar and vanilla.
Very simple and good.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sour cream, flour and spices.
Mix well.
Stir in raisins.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 325° for about 50 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve plain or with whipped cream or use the egg whites for meringue.

title: oatmeal cookies(what grandma doesn't make oatmeal cookies?)
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients, one at a time, to a soft dough.
Drop by teaspoon onto a lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake in a 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Dough will make a big ball.
Drop by tablespoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pa's 7-up cake
directions: Combine butter and sugar in a large mixing bowl. Add beaten eggs and 7-Up. Mix together. Add flour, vanilla and lemon extract. Beat until smooth. Bake at 325° for 65 minutes in a tube pan. The finished cake may be sprinkled with powdered sugar or frosted.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and cut up into little pieces.
Take 1 1/2 quart of chicken broth and mix with soup and chicken.
Put a layer of dressing in bottom of a casserole dish, then a layer of the mixture, then another layer of the dressing.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: impossible pie(coconut)
directions: Beat all together. Pour in ungreased pans (2 small pie pans work well). Bake at 400° until golden brown for 50 to 55 minutes. This pie makes its own crust and is very fast for busy women.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Wash, peel and slice finely the potatoes and onions.
Layer in buttered casserole dish, placing 1/2 can mushroom soup between middle and top layer.

title: chili dip
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Add Ro-Tel and heat on medium heat.
Mix in chili; heat.
Add cheese until melted.
Mix in cayenne pepper.
When heated and mixed thoroughly, add whipping cream and heat until blended.
Serve warm in a crock-pot.

title: pineapple cheesecake(made in spring-form pan)
directions: *(The original recipe used half these amounts, but I found a thicker crust better.
The wafers I pushed through a colander.)

title: fried green tomatoes, country style
directions: Combine egg and milk; set aside.
Mix cornmeal, flour, salt and pepper.
Dip tomato slices in egg mixture; dredge in cornmeal mixture.
Heat vegetable oil in a large iron skillet over medium heat.
Arrange tomato slices in a single layer.
Cook until golden brown on each side.
Repeat with remaining slices, adding additional oil as needed.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar together well before adding other ingredients. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes in a greased and floured pan. (I use butter and sugar in my pans.)

title: lemon pie from scratch
directions: In saucepan, mix sugar and cornstarch (mix well); set aside. Squeeze lemons; add egg yolks and pat of butter; set aside.
Over medium heat, add boiling water to sugar mixture and stir until butter has melted.
(Should be thick.)
Remove from heat and pour into cooled pie shell.
When pie has cooled, beat egg whites and sugar until peaks form.
Place on pie and brown slightly under broiler.

title: grandma miller's mincemeat
directions: Add everything except meat and heat until hot, then add meat. Put in jars and cold pack 1 1/2 hours.

title: speedy spinach mushroom caps
directions: Cut stems off mushrooms and chop, reserving mushroom caps; mix chopped stems into thawed spinach.
Dip whole mushroom caps into melted butter; shake of excess.
Place 1 teaspoon of spinach mixture into each cap.
Sprinkle each mushroom with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, until puffy and lightly browned.

title: make ahead fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit, saving juice, in a saucepan.
Mix cornstarch and sugar in a bowl; add beaten eggs and mix until smooth.
Stir this mixture into cold juice in saucepan and then heat.
Bring to a boil, stirring, until thick.
Cool slightly and then mix with drained canned fruit.
Refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, add sliced bananas.
You can also add fresh sliced kiwi fruit and strawberries.

title: hamburger vegetable lentil soup
directions: Brown hamburger until crumbly.
Add rest of ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Remove bay leaf before serving.
Soup freezes well.

title: chicken surprise
directions: Place slice of dried beef and pieces of Swiss cheese on each breast.
Roll up and place in baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for about 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, saute mushrooms in 1 tablespoon butter.
Add half a can cheese soup, remainder of cheese, milk and seasonings.
Cook until smooth; pour over chicken breasts and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: date loaf candy
directions: Cook milk, sugar and Karo to soft ball stage.
Add margarine and dates; chopped fine.
Stir until dates melt.
Beat until it begins to harden; then add nuts.
Pour all into a wet cloth and roll up.
Let set overnight.
When cold, slice end ways and roll in powdered sugar.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream grated cheese and butter together.
Add flour, pepper and salt.
Blend well.
Squeeze through a cookie press onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: blueberry salad(serves 12)
directions: Heat 2 cups of the liquid.
Dissolve jello using the 2 cups heated liquid.
Then, add remaining 2 cups liquid and chill until thick and syrupy.
Add blueberries and pineapple.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill thoroughly.

title: pot roast with vegetables
directions: Season the meat with salt and pepper.
Heat oil in Dutch oven or roaster pan; brown meat.
Add the onions and puree.
Reduce the heat to low; cover and simmer for 2 hours.
Add potatoes and carrots; cover and simmer for 30 to 45 minutes, until vegetables are soft.
Remove meat and vegetables to serving platter.
In small bowl, combine flour with water; stir into pan liquid.
Cook for 2 minutes, until gravy is thickened, stirring constantly.
To serve, put gravy over sliced meat and vegetables.

title: blueberry coffeecake
directions: Combine baking powder, flour, sugar, salt and oleo or butter and mix with pastry blender.
Add egg, beaten with milk, to first mixture, along with blueberries.
Use a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Grease sides and bottom of pan.
Spread in pan.
It is real thick.

title: chinese chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together except butter, almonds and flakes.
Put in casserole.
Melt butter in skillet; add almonds and flakes.
Sprinkle on top of casserole. Bake for 35 minutes.
This can be prepared a couple of days before serving.
Cover with aluminum foil when baking.

title: west texas spaghetti
directions: Chop green pepper, onion and garlic.
Saute with the ground beef, using a little oil to prevent sticking.
Cook evenly.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
To this is added the tomato soup, being allowed to simmer in covered pan for 30 minutes.

title: french fried peanut butter and jelly
directions: Heat butter in small Teflon skillet until hot, but not smoking.
Spread peanut butter and jelly between 2 pieces of bread.
Beat together egg and milk.
Dip sandwich in egg mixture and fry in hot butter on each side until golden brown.
May sprinkle with powdered sugar while hot.
Serve hot with a glass of milk.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix the pretzels, 3 tablespoons of
sugar and melted margarine together.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: cream cheese meat loaf
directions: Mix beef, tomato paste, eggs, Ritz crackers, onion, green pepper, salt and pepper.
Mix well. Split meat in half.
Pat half in bottom of pan.
Mix softened cream cheese, oregano and chives well. Spoon cheese mixture over the half you patted in pan.
Put remaining ground beef over top of cream cheese mixture. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: cheddar bacon puffs
directions: May add 2 finely chopped green onions or 1 teaspoon dry onion flakes.

title: green beans napoli
directions: Cook beans and drain.
Heat tomatoes with 1 teaspoon basil to boiling in a medium pan (can add a little sugar to tomatoes). Blend cornstarch with water until smooth; stir into hot tomato mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens. Boil for 3 minutes.
Fold in green beans.

title: barbecue sauce for hamburgers
directions: Add all ingredients in large kettle.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well.
Cover.
Simmer one hour on medium heat.

title: apple pie
directions: Handle dough lightly to prevent sticking, using just enough flour to do so.
Never turn or knead crust.
Press crust lightly to fit pan.
Trim with fork.

title: freezer corn
directions: In large pan, boil ingredients.
Cook 5 minutes after mixture boils.
Stir to prevent sticking.
Cool and put in freezer containers.

title: beef steak ranchero with fresh tomato salsa
directions: In a shallow glass dish, layer half the onion, garlic, coriander, jalapeno and tomato. Season the steaks on both sides with salt and place in the dish. Cover with the remaining onion, garlic, coriander, jalapeno and tomato.
Cover and refrigerate 12 hours or overnight.

title: barbecued meat balls
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and form into balls. Place in an uncovered baking dish.
To make the sauce, combine the remaining ingredients and pour over the meat balls.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: toffee butter crunch
directions: Melt butter in a large saucepan. Add sugar, corn syrup and water. Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, to hard crack stage (300°). Stir in coarsely chopped almonds and spread in well buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch metal pan quickly!
Cool.
Carefully turn out on wax paper. Spread top with 1/2 melted chocolate and sprinkle with 1/2 nuts.
After chocolate firms, cover with wax paper, invert and repeat, if necessary. Chill to firm chocolate. Break into pieces.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix the beaten egg with the brown sugar which has been blended with the flour, spices and salt.
Add pumpkin and milk.
Beat smooth.
Place in pastry-lined pie pan.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Melt butter; add flour, then stir in milk until thickened. Add corn, sugar, salt and pepper.
Cook until heated through. Take off stove and add 2 well beaten eggs and mix.
Butter a baking dish and pour mixture in.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: edna smythe's cajun rice
directions: Crumble and cook pan sausage; drain.
Add onion, bell pepper and celery and let simmer.
Add cooked rice and mix well.
Add both soups and mix all ingredients.
Salt to taste.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: humus tahini
directions: Drain canned beans, reserving liquid from 1 can.
Place beans, lemon juice, garlic, tahini paste (available at Nayphe's International Foods on May), salt and olive oil into food processor or blender.
Blend until very smooth.
If too thick for dip, add a little of the reserved liquid from beans.
Garnish with parsley.

title: raw veggie dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill an hour or so to season through. Serve with raw vegetables.

title: martha's oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Stir in vanilla and lemon extract. Thoroughly mix flour and baking soda. Add to creamed mixture, alternately with buttermilk, beating well after each addition. Pour into greased and floured Bundt or 10-inch tube pan. Bake in a 325° oven for 1 1/4 hours. Cool in pan 10 minutes. Remove to wire rack to cool completely.

title: basque fish soup
directions: In large saucepan saute onion, celery and garlic in butter until tender.
Stir in tomatoes, wine, parsley, salt, pepper and thyme.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Add fish and simmer 7 to 10 minutes, or until fish is opaque and flakes easily with fork. Makes 4 to 6 servings.
Good with crusty bread and salad of mixed greens.
You can reheat soup and add raw shrimp or more fish when soup boils.
Bring to a boil again, remove from heat and let stand 1 minute.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Cream together the first 4 ingredients.
Sift together next 6 ingredients.
Mix together.
Make into small balls and roll in sugar.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes at 350°.
Shake pan just before done so they fall.

title: "mile hi" strawberry pie
directions: Beat egg whites until light and fluffy.
Add strawberries and lemon juice and beat for a full 15 minutes on high speed of mixer. Fold whipped cream into mixture and
pile into baked, cooled crust.
Freeze.

title: chickpea one pot(side dish or vegetarian main dish)
directions: Saute onion in pot until clear. Add chickpeas, hominy and zucchini; boil until heated through. Spoon into bowls and sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Mix and cook 30 minutes.
Put into hot jars and seal.

title: green chili rice
directions: Cook rice and salt and pepper to taste. Mix in sour cream. Pour half mixture in casserole dish. Sprinkle half cheese and green chilies on top. Add another layer of rice mixture and repeat with cheese and chilies. Put a few dabs of butter on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together and chill several hours.
Shape into a ball and roll in chopped pecans.

title: taffy candy
directions: Boil to hard ball stage.
Pour onto plates and let cool until you can handle it.
Rub hands with butter before pulling taffy. When taffy is cool enough, pull apart with hands.
The more you pull, the creamier it will get.
Shape and let stand until it gets hard.

title: spinach spoon bread
directions: Prepare onions according to package.
Set aside.
Cook spinach. Drain well.
In large bowl, mix onions, eggs, spinach, sour cream, butter and salt.
Stir in corn muffin mix.
Pour mixture into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Sprinkle top of cornbread with cheese and bake 2 more minutes until cheese is melted.
Serve warm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Mix butter and crushed Oreos.
Reserve 1/4 for top.
Use remaining to make crust in a 9 x 9-inch pan or dish.
Layer on crust the ice cream, pudding and milk mixed.
Let cool.
Add the Cool Whip.
Let cool. Sprinkle remaining crushed cookies.

title: apple crisp i
directions: Bake apples in a buttered pan for 15 minutes at 400°.
Combine other ingredients.
Remove apples from oven and cover with crumbled mixture.
Bake 40 minutes more, or until top is golden brown.

title: the best coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed in 3 or 4 round cake pans.
Let cool completely.
In mixer, whip whipping cream until very fluffy. Add sugar and blend.
Punch holes in first layer of cake and add 1/4 of cream of coconut.
Smooth over cake.
Position cake on serving plate. Top with 1/4 cup coconut and some whipping cream (enough to cover layer).
Repeat with remaining cake layers.
Ice entire cake with remaining whipping cream and press coconut to cover entire cake.
Best after sitting 1 day before serving.

title: grilled onions
directions: Peel onions and rinse.
Tear aluminum foil into pieces slightly larger than onions.
Cut each onion in half and place both halves on a square of foil.
Put a pat of butter or oleo between the halves of an onion; salt and pepper to taste.
Wrap thoroughly. Continue with all onions.
Cook by placing foil packets around outside edge of grill while the meat cooks.
Onions are done when they can be pierced easily with a fork.

title: grapefruit freeze
directions: Combine sugar and water in saucepan; bring to boil.
Add mint; cover and let stand for 5 minutes.
Pour mixture through a strainer into an 8 cup container.
Discard mint.
Add grapefruit juice.
Divide mixture into two 1-quart freezer containers; cover and freeze.
Remove from freezer 2 hours before serving.
Stir until slushy.
Garnish, if desired, with fresh mint sprigs.
A refreshing drink for summer entertaining!

title: easy chicken rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cornbread stuffing crumbs, and place in buttered casserole dish.
Top with buttered cornbread stuffing crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: yankee doodle cheesecake
directions: Combine melted butter, cookie crumbs and sugar.
Press firmly into bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Chill while preparing filling.
Beat cream cheese and lemon juice in large mixer bowl until fluffy.
Set aside.

title: macaroon cake
directions: Separate eggs.
Let whites warm to room temperature (about 1 hour).
Mix at high speed.
Beat yolks with shortening and butter until light and fluffy.
Add almond extract; beat until blended. At low speed, beat in flour alternately with milk, beginning and ending with the flour.
Beat in coconut.
Beat egg whites just until stiff peaks form.
Gently fold whites into batter until well combined.
Pour into greased tube pan and bake at 300° for 2 hours.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: meat and bean hot dish
directions: Brown bacon in large frying pan.
Remove bacon; brown ground meat and onion in same pan.
Put tomato sauce, mustard, brown sugar and pork and beans into a large casserole dish.
Add meat and onion mixture and stir well.
Add molasses if desired for a baked beans flavor.
Crumble bacon on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mother's banana cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening, salt, eggs and soda.
Add bananas and sour milk, then flour.
Beat after adding each of the bananas. Bake in a medium hot oven until done, about 45 minutes.

title: spice tea
directions: Mix together well.
To serve, put 2 tablespoons in each mug of hot water.
Stir until dissolved.

title: crispix mix
directions: Cook sugar, Karo, margarine, vanilla and salt to the soft ball stage.
Pour over 1 box Crispix, pretzels and nuts or whatever you like.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.
Spread on a cookie sheet to cool.
Break apart and store in plastic bags.

title: pork chop schnitzel(john's favorite)
directions: Bread chops in flour; brown.
Place one layer in baking dish. Put a slice of lemon on each chop.
Add a slice or 2 of onion.
Do the same with the next layer.
Cover with mushrooms and just enough water to cover, along with the mushroom juice.
Add beef bouillon, cover and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: brownies
directions: Cream margarine with cocoa and sugar.
Add sifted flour and eggs.
Then add vanilla, salt and pecans.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Let cool.

title: orange chiffon pie
directions: Add 1/2 cup sugar, orange juice and salt to beaten egg yolks. Cook 2 1/2 to 3 minutes in microwave until of custard consistency. Soften gelatine in cold water; add to hot custard, stir until dissolved.
Add grated rind and lemon juice, cool.
When mixture begins to thicken, fold in stiffly beaten egg whites, to which the other 1/2 cup sugar has been added.
Pour into baked pie shell. Chill and garnish with whipped cream.

title: almond bark squares
directions: Melt almond bark or Eagle Brand vanilla candy coating squares in microwave.
Start at 2 minutes, maybe more or less.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Chill and cut in squares.

title: chiffon frosting
directions: Cook flour and milk until thick and then cool.
Cream together shortening and sugar, then add cooled flour mixture a tablespoon at a time.
Beat until smooth.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1 cup powdered sugar.

title: fresh fruitade
directions: In a 1-quart saucepan, combine tea and honey.
Bring to a boil; add juices of lemon, lime and oranges.
Bring to boil, stirring frequently, boiling about 7 minutes or until slightly syrupy.
Chill mixture.
For each serving, place 2 tablespoons syrup mixture in a chilled tall tea glass.
Add 1 cup sparkling water and ice.
Stir well.
Contains 35 calories and less than 0.1 gram fat.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Melt Cheddar cheese in a double boiler with milk.
Add garlic salt.
Serve in a fondue dish with crackers or dip chips.

title: cherry delight
directions: Combine butter, cream cheese, and powdered sugar. Mix well, add Cool Whip. Pour into a graham cracker pie crust. Top with cherry pie filling.

title: apricot coffee cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt or tube pan with vegetable shortening. In large bowl, combine all ingredients, except the last 3, which can be mixed and set aside.
Beat until smooth.
Pour half of cake batter in pan.
Sprinkle with half of topping and cut into batter.
Pour in remaining batter; top with remaining topping. Let cool in mold, upright on rack, for 15 minutes.
Invert pan on rack and shake; cake will drop out.
Allow cake to finish cooling on rack.
Dust with powdered sugar or glaze with thin icing. Garnish with pecan halves and cherries.
Cake is baked in a 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Grease or spray bottom of large casserole dish.
Mix soups and sour cream together.
Put chicken on bottom of dish, then soup mixture and cover with crackers. Then, slice one stick of margarine on the top and then crackers.
Bake at 400 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: fettuccini
directions: In large saucepan, stir soup until smooth.
Blend in milk and cheese.
Heat, stirring now and then.
Just before serving, toss hot noodles with butter.
Combine with soup mixture.
Serve with additional cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: In a large bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk, pecans, butter and flavoring.
Mix well. Stir in remaining ingredients. Pour into ice cream freezer container. Freeze according to manufacturing instructions.
Freeze leftovers.

title: quick chinese chix sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Marinate 24 hours or more.

title: cheesy pita pizza
directions: Lightly brush bread with 1 tablespoon of dressing.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until brown.
Brush bread with half of the remaining dressing.
Top with cheese and pizza toppings. Drizzle with remaining dressing.
Bake 1 to 2 minutes or until cheese melts.
Cut into 6 wedges.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Blend shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat in flour, soda, salt and bananas.
Fold in pecans.
Grease and flour a cake pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 250° to 300°.
Let set in pan 10 to 15 minutes before taking out.

title: sunburst salad
directions: Fold all ingredients together and chill.
Serve.

title: candied pecans
directions: Place butter in a 1-quart casserole.
Microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir in sugar, cinnamon and cloves.
Microwave on High for 1 to 2 minutes or until sugar is dissolved.
Stir in nuts until well coated.
Microwave on High for 4 to 5 minutes.
Spread out on waxed paper to cool.

title: monkey bread
directions: Place pecans in Teflon Bundt pan.
Set aside.
Cook brown sugar cinnamon and butter or margarine until sugar melts.
Set aside.
Cut buttermilk biscuits into quarters.
Coat quarters in mixture of 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and 1/2 cup sugar.
Place coated pieces in pan on top of pecans.
Pour sauce evenly over the top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Turn upside-down on large plate.

title: meat filled jumbo shells
directions: Saute beef, sausage, onion and garlic until meat is well browned.
Drain off fat.
Add red pepper, salt, pepper, Italian seasoning, sweet basil, Parmesan cheese, bread crumbs, egg and wine.
Mix together.
Cook shells according to package directions. Drain shells well.
Fill each shell with meat filling.
Spread a layer of sauce on bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Place shells, open side up, in a single layer in the pan.
Cover with sauce.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese and bake at 350° for about 35 minutes until hot.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: oyster snack crackers
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Let stand 1 hour before eating.

title: peanut patties
directions: In heavy 3-quart saucepan, combine first 4 ingredients.
Cook over low heat 1
hour.
Remove from heat. Add the next 3 ingredients. Stir well. Quickly drop by spoonful onto wax paper.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Follow directions on box of macaroni and cheese. Add soup, tuna and pimentos.
Mix and pour into a casserole dish.
Cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: toffee treasure cake
directions: Generously grease and lightly flour 9 or 10-inch Bundt pan.* Combine sugar with cinnamon; set aside.
In large mixing bowl, combine remaining ingredients except nuts, candy bars and melted butter.
Blend at low speed until moistened; then beat 3 minutes at medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Spoon 1/2 of batter into prepared pan.
Sprinkle with remaining cinnamon-sugar mixture, then with nuts and crushed candy bars.
Pour melted butter over batter.

title: artichoke hearts
directions: Mix and bake in
buttered
casserole
for 20 minutes at 350°. Good with pita crackers.

title: pecan pie cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Thaw pecan pie according to pkg. directions but not completely (I find it cuts better partially frozen). Cut evenly into 20 thin slices, keeping wedges intact, and set aside. Stir together cracker crumbs, sugar, butter and cinnamon; press mixture onto bottom and 1 1/2 inches up sides of a 10 inch springform pan. Arrange 10 pecan pie wedges in a spoke design in prepared pan, placing 1 cut side of each wedge on crust with narrow end towards center of pan. Reserve remaining pecan pie wedges for another use. Beat cream cheese until smooth; add eggs, 1 at a time, beating until blended after each addition. Add sour cream, half-and-half, and vanilla; beat until blended. Fold in confectioners sugar and flour. Carefully pour cream cheese mixture evenly over pecan pie wedges in pan, making sure wedges remain in place. Arrange pecan halves evenly around edge. Bake at 325° for 50 minutes. Turn off oven, and let cheesecake stand in oven 1 hour. Remove to a wire rack, and let cool completely. Chill at least 8 hours or overnight before serving.

title: sweet onion pie
directions: Prepare pie crust sheet according to package directions for a filled one-crust pie, using a 9-inch pie plate.
(Refrigerate remaining crust for later use.)
Bake at 450° for 9 to 11 minutes, or until lightly browned.
(If crust puffs up, gently press back to bottom and sides of pan with the back of a wooden spoon.)
Cool completely.

title: no bake peanut butter cookies
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to boil; remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter.
Add cereal.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: tasty early peas
directions: Melt margarine or butter in small saucepan.
Stir in honey and pecans.
Heat peas; drain.
Pour honey mixture over peas and serve.
tags: LeSueur very young small early peas

title: caramel nut crunch
directions: Heat oven to 325°. Butter jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1 inch). Heat brown sugar, corn syrup, margarine and salt in a 3 qt. saucepan over medium heat, stirring constantly until sugar is dissolved, about 5 minutes. Remove from heat. Stir in cereal and nuts until well coated. Spread in pan and bake 15 minutes. Cool until slightly firm, 5 to 7 minutes. Loosen with metal spatula. Let stand until firm, about 1 hour. Store in covered container. Makes about 8 cups.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in deep dish crust (9-inch).
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Bake at 500° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake 30 minutes or until inserted knife blade comes out clean.

title: canned dill pickles
directions: Bring above ingredients to a boil; add pickles a few at a time to gently heat. Put hot pickles in hot jars and cover with boiling brine. Put dill on top of packed pickles and seal. A piece or two of garlic in each jar also makes a nice flavor. Let rest about 2 weeks before sampling.

title: pumpkin roll-up
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jellyroll pan.
Line with wax paper; grease and flour the wax paper.

title: strawberry cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, flour and salt.
Gradually stir in milk.
Bring to boiling, stirring constantly.
Lower heat; cook until thick.
Stir a little of the hot mixture into egg; return to remaining hot mixture.
Bring just to a boil, stirring constantly. Cool, then chill.
Beat well; fold in whipped cream and vanilla. Pour into baked, cooled 9-inch pie crust.
Slice 2 1/2 cups strawberries in half, reserving a few perfect whole berries for center; arrange berries atop filling.
Cover with strawberry glaze.
Refrigerate until serving time.
Top with whipped cream.

title: butternut mints
directions: Mix Crisco and butter into confectioners sugar until it is small pieces.
Add flavoring and water. (Mixture is ready when it does not stick to your hands and feels like play dough.)
If sticky, add more sugar.
Shape or mold into mints.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: In a large bowl, mix Ricotta or cottage cheese, 1 cup of the Mozzarella cheese, egg, spinach, salt, oregano and pepper.
In greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, layer 1/2 cup sauce, 1/3 of the noodles and half the cheese mixture.
Repeat layers.
Top with remaining noodles and cover with remaining sauce.
Sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella cheese.
Pour the water AROUND the EDGES. Cover tightly with foil.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until bubbly.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; put in tomato paste, canned tomatoes (chopped), salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle generously with oregano.
Simmer.
Cook lasagna noodles in boiling water. Take container of cottage cheese and mix in one egg.
Drain noodles when tender.
Put a little sauce in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Put a layer of noodles, then 1/2 of cottage cheese.
Spread over noodles.
Shake Parmesan to cover, then one package of Mozzarella, then half of sauce.
Repeat.
Mozzarella on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° uncovered.

title: german torte dessert
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on the box and spread into 2 greased 9 x 13-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Combine cream cheese, pudding and milk together.
Spread over the cooled cake, then layer with pie filling.
Put on layer of Cool Whip.
Shave the Hershey bar with vegetable peeler and put over the top.

title: rotel potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in peel until done.
Melt the cheese; mix with Ro-Tel.
Cut potatoes into chunks; pour Ro-Tel dip over them.

title: easy chops and rice
directions: Cook chops in oil in a large skillet until browned.
Spoon off the fat.
Remove chops and set aside.
In the same skillet, combine soup and water.
Heat to boiling.
Return chops to skillet.
Cook 10 minutes over a low heat until chops lose all their pink, stirring often.
Serve over a bed of hot rice.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix cream cheese with 1 can crabmeat (do not drain) and second can crabmeat/liquid to desired thickness.
Season to taste with anything you desire, such as garlic, salsa, salt, pepper, etc. Garnish with paprika.

title: white bean soup
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients in a large saucepan.
Mash slightly with potato masher.
Stir in water and cook over low heat until thoroughly heated.
Meanwhile, saute onion and carrot in butter until tender and add with ham to bean mixture.
Cook over low heat for 10 minutes or until thoroughly heated, stirring occasionally. Makes 4 servings.
May be doubled easily.

title: boiled oatmeal cookies
directions: In a bowl, combine the oats, nuts and coconut; set aside.
In a boiler, combine the first 4 ingredients and bring to a brisk boil, stirring well until it boils.
Boil 1 minute.
Pour the mixture over the ingredients in the bowl.
Add the vanilla and mix well.
Put out by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: marvelous macaroons
directions: Combine coconut, sugar, flour and salt in mixing bowl.
Beat egg whites until stiff in separate bowl.
Stir in egg whites and almond extract.
Mix well.
Drop from teaspoon onto lightly greased baking sheet.
Garnish with candied cherry halves, if desired.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes or until edges are golden brown.

title: ribbon salad
directions: Dissolve lime jello in 1 cup boiling water. Add 1/2 cup cold water. Pour into a 10 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan or a large mold. Chill until partly set.

title: sausage balls
directions: Let cheese and sausage get to room temperature.
Mix together cheese, sausage and Bisquick.
Form into balls and bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Toss broccoli, cheese, bacon and onion in bowl.
Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar together.
Pour over vegetables and mix.
Refrigerate.

title: coated peanuts
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Put sugar, water, flavoring and peanuts in medium saucepan.
Boil over medium heat about 5 minutes, stirring constantly, until most of the syrup is sticking to the peanuts.
Spread thinly on lightly greased cookie sheet and cook in oven 1 to 1 1/2 hours, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cook until peanuts taste barely done.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Mix powdered sugar, condensed milk, coconut, chopped pecans, margarine and vanilla.
Form into small balls; chill until cool. Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in top of a double boiler over hot water.
Dip balls into chocolate mixture.
Place them on wax paper to dry.
Makes 100 pieces or more.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Melt chips and sweetened condensed milk in bowl in microwave or in a double boiler on stove.
Mix well.
Pour into aluminum foil lined 8 x 8 pan.
Cool and cut.

title: skillet dinner
directions: Brown hamburger in a 10-inch skillet.
Drain.
Slice onion over hamburger.
Slice potatoes over onion.
Add green beans and optional vegetables.
Add stewed tomatoes, salt and pepper. Cover.
Cook to high heat, then simmer for 30 minutes or until potatoes are fork done.
Serves 6.
Excellent leftovers.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli until soft and mix in all ingredients.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well cream and Cheddar cheese.
Add mayonnaise, rum or sherry, Worcestershire and salts.
Add pimento and olives.
Chill 1 hour.
Roll into ball.
Roll ball in chopped dried beef.

title: tamale dip
directions: Add all ingredients together.
Mix well.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: In a bowl, combine soup, sour cream, flour and garlic salt. Stir in hash browns and cheddar cheese.

title: punch
directions: Add all ingredients except ginger ale.
Stir well.
Pour in ginger ale before serving.
Amount of sugar may be decreased or increased.
Makes 1 1/2 gallons.

title: chicken rolls
directions: With sharp knife, cut around edges of rolls and pull out bread.
Break into small pieces.

title: swedish nuts
directions: Toast nuts in a 325° oven until light brown.
Fold sugar and salt into egg whites; beat until stiff peaks form.
Fold in nuts.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Combine oats and buttermilk; let stand 1 hour.
Add sugar, oil and egg to oat mixture; mix well.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt in a large bowl.
Make a well in center of mixture. Add oat mixture to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened. Spoon into greased muffin pans, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Yield:
12 muffins.

title: butter knots
directions: Cut biscuits in quarters, roll until pencil thin and tie in a knot.
Mix rest of ingredients.
Bake biscuits as directed on package, but don't brown.
After baking, marinate in spices and oil and drain.

title: layers of fluff
directions: Line a
9 x 13-inch pan with 1 layer of unsalted saltines. Mix as directed the vanilla instant pudding and pour over crackers.
On top of pudding, spread a layer of Cool Whip.
Place second layer of crackers over Cool Whip.
Mix as directed the chocolate pudding and pour over crackers.
Add top layer of Cool Whip and garnish with chocolate sprinkles.
Refrigerate until set.

title: hot fudge for ice cream
directions: Add first 3 ingredients and cook to a boil, then add 2 tablespoons of butter.
Pour on top of ice cream.

title: cinnamon rolls with caramel frosting
directions: Mix milk, yeast and sugar, then add all ingredients and mix well.
Let rise once, then roll out.
Spread on softened butter; sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Roll up and cut into 1/4-inch pieces.
Place on buttered pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes. While rolls are cooking, prepare frosting.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mash boiled potatoes; add salt and margarine.
Fold in the browned onions.
Spread into a sprayed casserole until smooth. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour, until it has a brown crust on top. Serves 6 to 7.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and drain; add tomatoes, tomato paste, basil, salt, garlic and water, and simmer for 30 minutes.
In bowl, beat eggs; add cottage cheese, parmesan cheese, parsley and black pepper.
Cook noodles according to directions on box, drain and rinse.
In large (9x13-inch) glass baking dish layer noodles, cottage cheese mixture, mozzarella, then meat sauce.
Repeat the layers and sprinkle with additional parmedan cheese, if desired. Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes, or until bubbly.
Let sit for at least 15 minutes before serving.

title: punch
directions: Mix first five ingredients and freeze.
When frozen, it looks like slush or icey.
When ready for use, put in punch bowl and pour pineapple juice over it and break up frozen mixture.
Add ginger ale immediately before serving.

title: apple pie
directions: Butter pie pan well.
Peel and slice as man apples as necessary to fill pie pan.
Place apples in buttered pan without crust.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.

title: pepper-cheese bread
directions: In large mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in hot water.
Add half the flour, then egg, sugar, salt, soda and sour cream.
Blend for 1/2 minute with mixer on low speed, then blend for 2 minutes on high speed.
Stir in rest of flour, cheese and pepper.
Divide dough evenly in two 1 pound coffee cans
(well greased).
Let rise in a warm place for 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chipped beef balls
directions: Use 3/4 of chipped beef inside ball; use remaining beef to coat balls.
Mix cheese, Worcestershire sauce, Accent and onion; add 3/4 of chopped beef.
Mix well and form into balls or rolls (any desired size).
Coat with remaining beef.
Chill well.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix together in a bowl all ingredients, except cheese.
Fold mixture into flour tortillas and top with cheese.
Spread remaining ingredients over all.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350° in a 13 x 9-inch dish.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large mixing bowl.

title: crabmeat spread
directions: Combine cream cheese, lemon juice and seasonings; mix until well blended.
Add crabmeat and radishes.
Mix lightly. Serve with crackers.

title: tofu salad
directions: On a large platter, spread ingredients in layers in the following order: tofu, salmon, tomato, onion, bean sprouts, watercress and 1/4 of the green onions.
In a saucepan, combine salad oil and garlic; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add soy sauce and the remaining green onions; mix well.
Pour dressing over salad; serve immediately.
Makes 8 servings.

title: tuna dip
directions: In a small bowl, break tuna into little pieces.
Add sour cream and dressing mix.
Stir until blended.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown turkey or beef and onion and drain.
Add stewed tomato, tomato paste, water, sugar, parsley flakes and basil to cooked meat.
Mix together cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese, parsley flakes and oregano.

title: hot dog specials("big" recipe for kids)
directions: You will need tinfoil.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Grease glass baking dish.
Lay chilies on bottom.
Put Mozzarella cheese or Jack cheese on top of chilies.
Blend eggs, milk, flour, salt and pepper.
Pour over chilies.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: salmon spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and roll in pecans, if desired. Keep in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Great on all kinds of crackers.

title: sherry's butter cream frosting
directions: Cream together well margarine and Crisco.
Add sugar and flour, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Add milk alternately with flour. Add vanilla.
Beat at high speed for 15 minutes.

title: world's best chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In large bowl, combine sugars. Add butter. Cream with sugar. Add vanilla and eggs. Add rest of ingredients. Mix well. Add chips and nuts (if desired). Drop by teaspoon. Bake 10 to 12 minutes. Cool 1 to 2 minutes.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Break spaghetti in half; cook in boiling water until done. Drain while warm.
Combine eggs and Parmesan with spaghetti.
Pour into greased pie plate and pat mixture up and around sides with a spoon.
Melt butter.
Add onion; saute until limp.
Stir in sour cream with onion and spoon over spaghetti "shell."
Brown sausage and beef in skillet; drain off fat.
Add tomato paste and water; simmer for 10 minutes.
Spoon meat over sour cream mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: rainbow popcorn balls
directions: Bring corn syrup and sugar to boil.
Add Jell-O.
Pour over popcorn and round into popcorn balls.

title: chicken pan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl, except margarine. Pour into prepared 9-inch pie dish. Dot with 1/2 stick margarine on pie before placing top crust. Place top crust and crimp. Cut slits in crust (4 to 6). Bake at 350° until golden brown, approximately 45 minutes.

title: chili rellenos bake
directions: In a large skillet, crumble together the beef and chorizo or sausage.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until meat is browned. Add onion and garlic.
Cook until onion is limp.
Drain off fat. Line a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with half of the chilies.
Top with 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Add the meat mixture and top with remaining chilies.
Set aside.

title: fudge sundae pie
directions: Have baked pie crust shell ready.
Put milk, chocolate pieces and salt in 1-quart saucepan.
Stir over heat (low) until chocolate melts completely and mixture thickens.
Take off heat. Stir in marshmallows until melted and mixture is smooth.
Cool to room temperature.
Spoon half of ice cream into the pie crust and then one-half the chocolate mixture.
Repeat with rest of ice cream and chocolate.
Top with pecans if desired.
Freeze until firm, about 5 hours.

title: bread sticks
directions: Mix and knead 5 to 10 times.
Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut in 3/4-inch strips.
Melt 1/3 cup butter in
x 13-inch pan. Roll strips in butter and place in same 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° about 20 minutes.
May make up
to
hours ahead and let rise. Yields 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: a happy church family recipe
directions: Take Love and Loyalty, mix it thoroughly with Faith.
Blend it with Tenderness, Kindness and Understanding.
Add Friendship and Hope.
Sprinkle abundantly with Laughter.
Bake it with Sunshine. Serve daily with generous helpings.
Study to show yourself approved, worthy to mix the ingredients to feed a fellow member, brother and sister.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mash berries.
Add sugar and flour.
Cook slowly until thick, stirring enough to prevent burning.
Put remainder of berries, whole or slice if large, into pie crust.
Cover with cooked mixture, cooled.
Chill.
Serve with Cool Whip or whipped cream at least once each season.

title: golden squash fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Spoon mixture into hot greased skillet in patty form.
Cook over medium heat for 10 minutes or until nicely browned.
Turn and cook another 8 to 10 minutes. Serve warm.
They are also good cold.

title: goop (play)
directions: Mix food coloring with water (if color is wanted).
Mix water with cornstarch; stir.
Gooey mix; fun to play with.
Refrigerate leftover mix.

title: cheese ball
directions: Have serving dish ready for finished ball.

title: venison stroganoff
directions: Flour and brown meat in skillet.
Add mushrooms and onions and brown slightly.
Add beef broth.
Cover and cook 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Gradually add the sour cream and cook 5 minutes over low heat.
Serve over chow mein noodles.
Serves 4. Preparation Time:
1 hour.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Allow cream cheese, sour cream and butter to come to room temperature.
In a large bowl, blend together all ingredients except eggs.
Beat eggs into mixture one at a time, mixing well after each one.
Pour into greased spring-form pan.
Cover bottom and sides with aluminum foil and put in larger pan partially filled with water and bake in 370° oven for 1 hour.
Cool and remove from pan.

title: butter pecan bars
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and pat into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix the cream cheese, eggs and confectioners sugar and pour over crust. Sprinkle the pecans over the filling.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate chip mini muffins
directions: Cream butter and vanilla.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy. Add dry ingredients; alternate with milk.
Add 12 ounces mini morsels.
Bake at 350° until sides are brown, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: super bundt cake(coffee cake)
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients thoroughly.
In another bowl, mix sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Grease and flour a Bundt or angel pan. Alternate layers of mixture and cinnamon mixture.
Swirl a knife through mixture 2 or 3 times.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cinnamon swirl salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin and candies in boiling water.
Stir in applesauce.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in nuts.
Turn into 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Beat together cream cheese and milk and mayonnaise.
Spoon atop salad.
Swirl through to marble.
Chill until firm.
Cut into 9 squares.
This is especially good in fall.

title: chop suey
directions: Brown meat in greaseless pot.
Add celery and onions.
Cook at low heat 30 minutes.
Add vegetables and sprouts.
Cook on low heat for 4 to 5 hours.
Add soy sauce to make a nice color.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Thicken with cornstarch if needed. Serve over white rice and top with heated canned chow mein noodles.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: chocolate swirl bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups of the flour and the yeast.
In a saucepan, heat and stir the milk, sugar, margarine or butter and salt until warm (120° to 130°) and margarine almost melts.
Add to flour mixture; mix well.
Add the eggs.
Beat with an electric mixer on low speed for 30 seconds, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat on high speed for 3 minutes. Using a spoon, stir in as much of the remaining flour as you can.

title: spaghetti carbonara
directions: Fry salt pork until crisp like bacon, being careful not to burn.
In large metal bowl mix eggs and butter and warm over heat until butter is melted but eggs are still uncooked.

title: chicken with yogurt curry(microwave)
directions: Finely chop onion.
Place in a microwave-safe dish, just large enough to snugly hold chicken.
Sprinkle with ginger and seasonings.
Cover with wax paper and microwave on High for 2 to 3 minutes, until soft.
Arrange chicken on top of onion, thicker ends facing outer edge of dish.
Cover with waxed paper. Microwave for 3 to 4 minutes.
Turn chicken and microwave for 3 to 4 more minutes.
Let stand, covered, for 2 minutes.
Stir in yogurt.
Garnish with toasted almonds, coconut or slivered apricots, if desired.
Excellent served with rice.
Serves 4.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Combine ingredients in large mixing bowl; mix well.
Pour batter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch or Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: tex's chili
directions: Brown meat in Dutch oven.
Add garlic, onion, salt and comino seed.
Cook 5 minutes.
Stir in chili powder.
Add tomato sauce and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Add water and simmer, covered, over low heat 30 minutes.
Add 2 to 3 cans red kidney beans.
Cook uncovered an additional 30 minutes.

title: apple pie
directions: Combine apples in mixing bowl with sugar, flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, lemon juice and allspice.
Place in 9-inch pie pan lined with pastry.
Dot apple filling with butter.
Put on top pastry; trim and crimp the edge.
Cut 3 vents on top of pie crust.
Bake in a 450° oven for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake about 30 minutes more.

title: chicken and stuffing bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook stuffing according to directions. Arrange chicken breasts in corners of large baking dish.
Place cooked stuffing down center of dish.
Pour gravy over chicken and stuffing. Cover with tinfoil.
Bake 15 minutes.
Uncover and bake another 10 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Place crescent rolls flat on cookie sheet, pinching seams together, forming a crust.
Bake according to directions.
Cool completely.

title: sour mixed pickles
directions: String the beans and cook until green color has left. Cut corn from the cob and cook 5 minutes. Chop cabbage.
Mix all vegetables together.
Place in clean quart jars. Place 1 tablespoon of salt, 1 teaspoon sugar and 1 teaspoon salt in each jar. Cover with boiling water and seal.

title: "aunt patty's pumpkin bread"
directions: Mix sugar and eggs.
Gradually add baking powder, baking soda, salt, spice, oil and water.
Mix well.
Add flour and pumpkin, alternating, one cup at a time.
Mix.

title: prism or rainbow cake
directions: Slice cold cookie dough 1/4-inch thick.
Arrange slices on 2 (12-inch) pizza pans, almost touching.
Cut remaining slices into small pieces to fill in holes.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes; cool.

title: chili dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in microwavable dish.
Pour Hormel chili over top of cream cheese.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese. Microwave on High for 3 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: seafood salad
directions: Combine seafood and celery in bowl.
Mix mayonnaise, onion, salt and pepper.
Pour over seafood and celery; toss.
Cover; chill at least 2 hours.

title: foolproof oven stew
directions: Grease bottom and sides of 3-quart casserole.
Arrange layers of roast, onion, celery, carrots and potatoes in casserole. Combine salt, sugar, tapioca, tomato juice and Kitchen Bouquet in a bowl; mix well.
Pour over top, do not stir.
Bake at 250° for 3 1/2 hours.
Remove from oven.
Add peas and bake for 30 minutes longer.
Remove from oven and mix well.
Cover casserole with foil before baking.

title: pigs in blanket
directions: You will need 20 to 30 toothpicks.

title: broccoli-cheese-rice casserole
directions: Cook onion in margarine slowly.
Cook rice.
Cook broccoli (follow directions on box).
Add all ingredients together.
Put in buttered dish.
Heat until Cheez Whiz melts.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix and pour dressing over mixture when served. To stretch, just add more ingredients or double recipe.
Don't add dressing to mixture and let stand or lettuce will wilt and the Fritos will become soggy.
You may add hamburger meat that has been browned and drained.

title: sex-in-a-pan
directions: Mix pecans, flour and butter and put in greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°, then cool.

title: frozen fruit dessert
directions: Blend and freeze until set; like ice cream.

title: nacho dip
directions: Spread refried beans in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown ground turkey in frying pan, drain if necessary.
Add taco seasoning and cook according to package directions.
Layer evenly over beans. Spread nacho soup over all.
Alternate dollops of sour cream and salsa over dip.
Sprinkle with chopped olives and Cheddar.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: dropped sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco; add egg, vanilla and Milnot, stirring well.
Add dry ingredients.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Add small amount of sugar on top of each cookie.
Bake 10 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites with salt until foamy.
Gradually add sugar and continue beating until stiff peaks form.
Fold in vanilla (and food coloring if you wish).
Fold in chocolate and nuts.
Drop onto foil lined cookie sheet; place in preheated oven at 350°. Turn oven off immediately and do not open oven door for 6 hours or overnight.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In
a
1/2 quart casserole dish, stir together soup, milk, soy
sauce	and pepper.
Mix in beans and 1/2 of onions. Bake, covered,
in
a 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Remove cover; stir. Top with remaining onions.	Bake 5 minutes more.

title: creamy turkey tetrazzini
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine; add broth and cream cheese.
Stir over low heat until cream cheese is melted.
Add remaining ingredients except Parmesan cheese; mix lightly.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 300° until light brown.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Place potatoes in colander to let drain; squeeze excess moisture from potatoes. Combine sour cream, soup and butter; mix well.
Add salt, onion and cheese; mix well.
Blend in potatoes. Place mixture in shallow 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle buttered corn flakes on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 50 minutes or until golden brown and bubbling.

title: sugared walnuts
directions: Boil sugar, cinnamon, salt and milk together, stirring to a soft ball stage (236° on candy thermometer).
Remove from heat. Add vanilla, nuts and stir until creamy.
Turn out quickly onto waxed paper.

title: haystacks
directions: Empty noodles in bowl.
Heat chips until dissolved.
Pour over noodles.
Pour in peanuts; stir to mix.
Drop by spoonful on wax paper.
Wrap individually in Saran Wrap.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent roll dough on cookie sheet.
Bake and cool. Mix first 3 ingredients and spread over cooled crescent rolls. Top with choice of vegetables (broccoli, cauliflower, celery, carrots, olives, etc.)
Add shredded cheese to top.
Does not keep well!

title: spring salad
directions: Pour water over Jell-O and marshmallows and stir until dissolved.
Chill this until syrupy.
Mash cheese with vinegar until smooth.
Add pineapple and mix.
Add nuts and chill.
When Jell-O is syrupy, combine together and chill.

title: irresistible peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine peanut butter, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Add egg.
Beat until blended.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Mix until well blended. Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten slightly in crisscross pattern with fork.
Bake for 7 to 8 minutes or until set and just beginning to brown.

title: minnehaha sauce
directions: Blend together in top of double boiler the butter, brown sugar, heavy cream, and lemon rind and juice.
Cook over boiling water, beating constantly, until sauce is creamy froth.
Serve with freshly cut fruit.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Sift dry ingredients; cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and molasses.
Stir flour mixture, shape into ball.
Roll in additional sugar.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Place chicken in large dish.
Pour soup over chicken.
Mix Pepperidge Farm dressing, eggs, onions and milk.
Pour this over soup.
Pour chicken broth over dressing to 1/2 inch over top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: melt away cookies
directions: Cream together butter (margarine) with sugar.
Add flour.
Mix by hand well.
Stir in nuts (nuts must be chopped well, the smaller the better).
Chill for about 2 hours, then roll in little balls (about 3/4 teaspoon) of cookie dough.
Preheat oven 10 minutes at 350°.
Put cookies on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Cook for 20 minutes.
When cookies are done and still hot, roll them in confectioners sugar.

title: divinity candy
directions: Cook sugar, water and syrup until it spins a thread. Gradually add this to the beaten egg whites.
Beat continuously. Beat until stiff enough to drop on buttered cookie sheet.
A cup of chopped pecans can be added to the mixture before placing on the cookie sheet.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix ingredients together and put in 1 gallon ice cream freezer.
Fruit may be added to this for different flavors.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions; drain well and set aside.
Combine cream cheese and butter; beat at medium speed of an electric mixer until smooth.
Stir in spinach.
Spoon into a lightly greased 1-quart casserole; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Cover and bake at 350°
for 20 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick oleo in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add cracker crumbs. Mix and pat over bottom of pan.
Mix sugar, eggs and 2 sticks oleo and beat for 15 minutes.
Pour over crust.
Slice bananas and arrange on top of filling. Top with pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip on top of pineapple.
Sprinkle with nuts and cherries.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: spicy apple bars
directions: Mix together.
Spread in greased 9 x 13 inch pan.
Bake in moderate oven, 375° for 25 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Cut in squares and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini and onions until soft; drain into another bowl. Combine soup and sour cream.
Pour over zucchini and onions; pour in stuffing mix and mix well.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in 350° oven. I bake it in a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.

title: nut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Add 3 cups flour, baking powder and salt.
Add vanilla.
Mix remaining cup flour with fruit and nuts.
Stir into batter.
Pour in greased and paper-lined tube pan.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours.
Let cool in pan.
My family prefers this to regular fruitcake.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix brown sugar, sugar, vanilla, cream cheese and Bits 'O Brickle.

title: holiday squares
directions: Combine brown sugar, eggs and margarine in a pot.
Place over low heat until sugar melts, stirring constantly.
Remove from stove.
Combine flour and baking powder and add to mixture.
Add vanilla and pecans and stir well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan (greased and floured) and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cool and cut into bars.

title: cranberry sauce with port
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, heat cranberries, port, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, and cloves to boiling over high heat, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat to medium and cook, uncovered, stirring occasionally, until most cranberries pop, about 10 minutes. (Mixture will thicken as it chills.)
Spoon sauce into serving bowl; cover and refrigerate until well-chilled, about 3 hours or up to 4 days.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: banana bread
directions: Bake at 350° up to an hour, if needed.
Makes about 2 loaves.

title: buttercream easter eggs
directions: Let cream cheese and butter come to room temperature.
Cream together in a large bowl. Add sugar, salt and vanilla.
Mix and knead with your hands until modable consistency.
If too dry, add a few drops of milk; if too wet, add more sugar. Shape mixture into small egg shapes or balls. Chill in refrigerator.
Dip chilled eggs into melted chocolate.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Wash fillets, blot dry, spray pan with Pam.
Place fillets on pan.
Pour lemon juice over fillets.
Salt and pepper, sprinkle oregano over fillets.
Broil until brown on top.
Then flip over and season again with lemon juice, salt, pepper and oregano. Total cooking time about 15 minutes.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Cream the cream cheese; add condensed milk and cream together. Add lemonade and Cool whip and beat in electric mixer until fluffy. If using pink lemonade, you will probably need a little red food coloring. Put into crust.

title: seven layer cookie
directions: Melt and pour butter over bottom of a 10 x 10-inch pan. Sprinkle crumbs over butter.
Add ingredients in order.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool before cutting into squares.

title: spinach soup
directions: Combine soup mix and water.
Simmer 4 minutes.
Add drained spinach and garlic to soup.
Bring to a boil and stir in beaten eggs.
Serve topped with grated cheese.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cool cooked potatoes; peel and grate coarsely.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over potatoes. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup more grated cheese and bake a few minutes more.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain, then add eggs, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper and garlic salt. Spread in bottom of 13 x 9 pan. Sprinkle half of Mozzarella cheese over top. Spread cottage cheese over this.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly together.
Press in loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: hawaiian banana nut bread
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients; stir in pecans.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add to flour mixture, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spoon batter into
2 greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean; cool in pans and let cool on wire racks.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: squash casserole
directions: Stew squash and onion in salted water until tender.
Drain, mash and add butter and a dash of black pepper.
Pour one-half of mixture into buttered baking dish.
Cover with cracker crumbs. Sprinkle with poultry seasoning and slivered almonds.
Repeat layers.
Dilute mushroom soup with milk and pour over top. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and place in medium oven until cheese is lightly browned.

title: railroad cornbread pie
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain and return to pan.
Add soup, water, corn, pepper and seasoning; mix well. Simmer for 15 minutes.
Put in baking dish.
In another bowl, combine cornmeal, sugar, flour, salt, baking powder, egg, milk and oil; mix well and pour onto mixture.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake for 20 minutes.

title: corn bread cake
directions: Mix all together.
Put into 9 x 13 greased pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: easy brisket (cranberry)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and pour over brisket, using enough water to cover.
Cover and bake for 2 1/2 hours.
Slice while warm and return pieces to juices in pan to absorb flavor.
Cook more if meat is not done completely.

title: picnic fruit punch
directions: Put
concentrates in a 1-gallon picnic jug.
Add water, soda and ice cubes to fill.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves; set aside.
Cut shortening into flour with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Sprinkle cold water (1 tablespoon at a time) evenly over surface; stir with a fork until dry ingredients are moistened. Roll about 2/3 of pastry into a 14 x 10-inch rectangle.
Fit pastry into lightly greased 10 x 6 x 2 baking dish.
Spoon in blackberry mixture.
Roll remaining pastry out and cut into strips.
Arrange strips over blackberry filling in lattice pattern.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pineapple punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and freeze in freezer.
Remove from freezer 1 to 2 hours before needed.
Serve slushy.

title: oven roasted green beans with garlic
directions: Preheat the oven to 400 degrees.
Coat a 13 x 9 inch baking pan with cooking spray.
Rinse beans and trim off tough ends. Place beans in the baking pan.
Peel the onion and cut into 1/4-inch rings.
Separate the rings and scatter them over the beans.
Peel the garlic.
Cut the cloves in half and scatter over the onions.
Drizzle with oil.
Sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper.
Bake uncovered for 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes. Transfer beans to a serving bowl.
Drizzle with vinegar and stir well.
Serve hot or at room temperature.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Soften cream cheese; mix with other ingredients and put in pie shells.
Keep refrigerated or put in freezer.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: Fry bacon crisp and crush into bacon drippings. Add vinegar, onions, sugar and salt. Cook 5 minutes and stir in cabbage. Simmer on medium another 10 minutes.

title: bananas and nuts
directions: Cook over medium heat until slightly thick.
If you cook too long, it will get lumpy.
Spread on sliced bananas and roll in crushed peanuts.

title: grilled potatoes
directions: Put potatoes in aluminum pan (disposable kind).
Add onions and butter.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover pan with foil. Place pan on grill and cook for 20 to 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender and browned.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together, saving enough Cool Whip to put on top of each pie.
Pour into pie crusts.
Spread each pie with 1/2 can of frosting and top with remaining Cool Whip. Refrigerate.
Enjoy!!

title: frozen fruit medley(fat-free)
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Pour into mold or large dish and freeze until firm.
Let stand at room temperature for 15 minutes before serving.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: In skillet cook bacon crisp; set aside.
Chop onion and slice zucchini; add to bacon grease.
Cook until tender; drain grease. Add tomatoes and salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil, pour into casserole dish.
Add cheese.
Cook, uncovered, 15 to 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: pastry
directions: Mix flour, salt and sugar.
Cut in shortening with a pastry blender until crumbly.
Add cold water and stir gently with fork until it forms a ball and leaves sides of bowl.
Roll out on lightly floured pastry cloth or between two sheets wax paper. Line pan, flute edges.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and slice eggplant into 1/4-inch slices.
Combine salt and flour.
Dip eggplant into egg-milk mixture, then into salt-flour mixture.
Melt butter in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish. Layer eggplant, onion and tomato sauce alternately.
Sprinkle with oregano and cheese.
Bake at 350° to 375° for approximately 40 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer ingredients in order; do not toss.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.
Toss just before serving.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Set aside several whole shrimp.
Chop remaining shrimp.
Mix all ingredients and garnish with whole shrimp.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix together.
Place in pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until apples are soft.
May use top crust, if desired.

title: pepper steak
directions: Pound steak to 1/4-inch thickness; cut into 1/4-inch strips. Sprinkle with paprika; set aside. Brown meat in skillet in butter. Add garlic and broth. Cover and simmer 30 minutes. Stir in onions and green pepper. Cover; cook 5 minutes more.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer ingredients
in
the order given in a 9 x 13-inch dish. Cover tightly with Saran Wrap.
Refrigerate 24 hours or overnight. Will last and stay fresh for at least a week.

title: tomato-carrot soup
directions: Saute green onion in oil in medium size saucepan over medium heat for 3 minutes. Add garlic.
Saute 2 minutes.
Add carrot, plum tomatoes, chicken broth, basil, salt and pepper.
Bring to boiling. Reduce heat. Simmer, covered, 15 minutes or until carrots are tender.

title: 4-layer delight
directions: Combine oleo, flour and nuts.
Mix well (it will be stiff). Spread in the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Cool.

title: fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk; cook over medium heat until mixture reaches a soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a greased pan and cool.

title: country fried chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken pieces.
Beat milk with water and eggs.
Soak chicken in milk mixture for 10 minutes.
Mix flour and paprika in heavy paper bag.
Drain chicken, then shake pieces in bag until all are well coated.
Heat oil in a Dutch oven to 360°; shake excess flour from chicken.
Fry, turning, until brown on all sides, about 20 minutes.
Drain on paper towel.
Serve hot or cold.

title: swiss steak with red gravy
directions: Saute onion slices in oil in large skillet.
Remove onions and brown steak in same oil.
Drain.
Add onions back to pan and cover with tomato soup, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 1 to 2 hours until tender.
Stir occasionally to keep from sticking.
Tomato soup becomes the gravy when meat is removed.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Grease a 9 x 9-inch pan with butter.
Melt the stick of butter in a saucepan over low heat.
Put graham crackers in large baggie and crush with a rolling pin.
Combine all ingredients except the chocolate.
Press into pan.
Melt the chocolate in microwave or double boiler.
Spread over mixture.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: open crock pickles
directions: Boil together the water, vinegar, pickling salt, alum and pickling spice.
Put dill on bottom, in between and on top of 5-quart ice cream pail.
I put the brine on hot.
They are ready to eat in a few days.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Tear lettuce into small pieces.
Put in a 9 x 12-inch glass dish.
Layer rest of ingredients in order given.
Add sugar to mayonnaise; spread over top as you would frosting.
Top with grated cheese.

title: apple squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cake mix and butter until crumbly.
Reserve 2/3 cup for topping.
Add brown sugar and cinnamon to topping.
Press remaining mixture into bottom of pan. Slice apples and put on top of cake mix.
Blend sour cream and egg. Spread over apples.
Spread remaining topping mixture over sour cream mixture.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Bake at 325° for 25 minutes or until brown on top.

title: beer biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Grease muffin tins and fill 1/2 full. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
May be reheated if any are leftover.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients together.
Stir in sugar completely. Next, stir in coconut.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Freeze balls for 30 minutes.
Melt 1/3 almond bark in double boiler.
Dip 1/3 coconut balls in melted bark.
Drain excess and place on wax paper.
Repeat process with another 1/3 almond bark.
Add desired food coloring.
Dip another 1/3 coconut balls.
Drain excess and place on wax paper.
Repeat process with last 1/3 almond bark and desired food coloring.
Makes 60 to 70 balls.

title: maryland fried chicken
directions: Combine flour, poultry seasoning, salt and peppers in a bowl. Whip eggs in another bowl.
Crush crackers in a third bowl.
Coat each piece of chicken in flour, then eggs, cracker crumbs and again in flour.
Pour oil into frying pan.
Heat to about 350°.
Add chicken, cover and fry for 15 minutes.
Turn chicken; pour white Worcestershire over chicken.
Cover and cook 10 to 15 minutes or until chicken is cooked through.

title: mandarin salad
directions: Combine and set aside.

title: cracker jackers
directions: Saute the peanuts.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook until candy consistency.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook strawberry juice, sugar, flour and jello until thick. Cool and add berries.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with whipped topping.

title: mother-in-law butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Mixture is very soft.
Add egg, cream and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix flour mixture with butter mixture.
Chill dough.
Roll dough very thin, 1/4 of dough at a time.
Cut out cookies.
Place on greased cookie sheet and decorate.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add brown sugar and barbecue sauce.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Press biscuits out flat and place in muffin pan.
Fill each biscuit with meat mixture.
Cook at 375° for 8 minutes.
Take out and sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top. Put back in oven until cheese is melted.

title: mustard
directions: Mix ingredients and bring to a boil.
Takes about 5 minutes. Add a dash of Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco sauce.
Excellent to eat with ham.

title: chicken parmesan(low calorie recipe)
directions: Dip chicken breasts in imitation eggs and coat with bread crumbs (prefer homemade crumbs rather than store bought).
