Spray frying pan with vegetable spray and fry chicken breasts.
Empty 1/2 tomato sauce into ovenproof casserole.
Place chicken; spread remaining sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake in oven or microwave until cheese is melted and hot.
Bake in 350° oven or about 10 minutes in microwave.
One chicken breast equals 150 calories.

title: avocado dip
directions: Peel, pit and mush avocados.
Combine cream cheese and milk. Blend until smooth.
Add avocados, lemon juice and Bleu cheese mix. Blend until smooth.
Refrigerate.

title: cherry nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into large tube pan. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Dip chicken pieces in margarine; roll in mixture of chips (or corn flakes), garlic salt and pepper.
Place pieces, skin side up, not touching, in greased large shallow baking pan.
Sprinkle with remaining butter and crumbs.
Bake at 375° about 1 hour or until done.
Do not turn.
Serves 4.

title: new potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes until tender; cool. Cut potatoes into quarters and put in a glass casserole dish. Cut Velveeta into cubes and mix with mayonnaise. Spread over potatoes; salt and pepper. Crumble bacon over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: sausage ham jabalaya
directions: Brown sausage and ham in Dutch oven.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook, uncovered, 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. Cover and simmer 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove bay leaf.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken divan
directions: Line a 9 x 12-inch dish with broccoli pieces.
Top with chicken pieces, shredded, and grated cheese.
Spread soups and mayonnaise over chicken.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: yams and apple casserole
directions: Layer yams and apples.
Add cinnamon to taste.
Layer other ingredients.
Bake for 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Cover.
Top with marshmallows; return to oven until brown.
Watch carefully!

title: chicken casserole
directions: Chop chicken breast.
Mix together stuffing, broth, margarine, celery, onions and mayonnaise.
Spread 1/2 of mixture in a greased 8 x 11 1/2-inch casserole dish.
Next, spread the cut up chicken on top of mixture.
Top with remaining stuffing mixture.
Beat egg and milk together and pour evenly over the casserole.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Before baking, spread cream of mushroom soup on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Top with cheese and bake until cheese melts.

title: donuts
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Add sugar and beat well.
Add milk and shortening and mix well.
Sift dry ingredients together and combine with liquid mixture.
Roll out on floured surface to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut into circles and cut small hole in the middle.
Fry in deep oil at 375°, turning once when underside is golden in color.
Remove with slotted spoon and roll in granulated sugar.

title: frozen salad
directions: Mix together the sugar and cream cheese.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix all together.
Put in freezer.

title: hawaiian salad(good as salad or dessert)
directions: Mix oleo, flour, brown sugar and pecans well.
Press firmly in bottom of 8 x 12-inch dish sprayed with Pam.
Bake 10 mixture at 325°.
Let cool.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients and pour into baking dish.
Pour melted butter over crushed Ritz crackers; toss, then put on top of casserole.
Bake 40 minutes or until top is golden brown in 400° oven.

title: blueberry sweeter muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in a mixing bowl. Add remainder of ingredients except berries and mix together with fork or pastry blender. Fold in well drained berries. Fill cups 2/3 full. Bake in moderate hot oven at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 12 medium sized muffins.

title: overnight salad
directions: Make one layer of each ingredients in the order listed.
Cover tightly with Saran Wrap and set overnight in refrigerator.

title: vacuum cleaner cookies
directions: Combine margarine, cake mix and 1 egg.
Stir until moist.
Pat mixture into bottom of a well-greased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan. Beat 2 eggs lightly. Beat in cream cheese and powdered sugar. Stir in coconut and nuts.
Pour over mixture in jelly roll pan, spreading evenly. Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown. Cool pan on rack.
Makes 4 dozen bars.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream together butter or oleo, sugar and salt.
Add cheese and eggs.
Beat well; add and beat in vanilla and flour.
Spoon mixture into 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: poultry hawaiian(low-fat)
directions: Saute onion and garlic in vegetable oil.
Stir in carrots, green pepper and celery.
Add chicken broth.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Blend soy sauce and cornstarch until smooth in a separate container.
Add pineapple liquid; blend.
Add liquid mixture to vegetable mixture.
Cook, stirring often, until sauce thickens.
Boil 5 minutes.
Stir in pineapple, mushrooms, water chestnuts and poultry.
Cover and heat slowly.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: bojangles style rice
directions: Brown sausage; pour off drippings.
Add other ingredients, except rice; bring to a boil.
Add rice; cook for approximately 20 minutes, or until rice is cooked.
Use large frypan.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 450° for 25 minutes.
Will fill large #10 skillet or 3-corn stick pans.

title: fiesta tortilla roll-ups
directions: Stir cream cheese until smooth. Stir in picante sauce and onion. Top each tortilla with about 1/4 cup cheese mixture. Spread to edge. Top each with spinach, 1/2 slice turkey and 2 teaspoons pimento. Tightly roll up like a jelly roll. Place seam side down in a large shallow dish. Cover and refrigerate at least 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies (2)
directions: Mix sugar, shortening, margarine & eggs, until fluffy or well blended.
Add milk, vanilla, salt, soda, oatmeal, flour and chocolate chips.
Bake at 375° for 8-10 minutes. Makes large batch.

title: vegetable pasta salad
directions: Combine salad dressing, garlic, dill and salt; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Chill several hours or overnight before serving.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix flour, sugar and eggs together, then melt butter.
Mix in peanut butter; mix all together.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: rhubarb custard crunch
directions: Mix together and pour in a greased 8 x 11-inch cake pan.
Beat egg and milk;
pour over first mixture.
Dot 2 tablespoons butter over rhubarb.

title: cheese ball
directions: Allow cheeses to soften to room temperature.
Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl and blend until smooth.
Refrigerate about 30 minutes.
Shape into one large ball or three smaller balls.
Roll in chopped nuts.

title: bundt cinnamon butter cake
directions: Mix brown sugar and cinnamon in a small bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients in a separate bowl.
Layer some of cake mixture, followed by 1/2 of the cinnamon mixture, and repeat until all is used up.
Bake at 350 degrees for about one hour.

title: party mix
directions: Mix salad dressing mix and dill weed together in a large bowl. Add Corn, Rice or Wheat Chex, oyster crackers and pretzels (or use any combination that you like) and mixed nuts.
Toss well.
Drizzle oil over mix.
Stir gently.
Place mixture in a large grocery sack. Fold bag to close and let stand for 2 hours.
Shake bag every 10 minutes for an hour.

title: cajun shrimp gumbo
directions: To make roux, heat oil in a large cast-iron kettle, if available.
When very hot, but not smoking, add half the flour. Stir constantly with a wire whisk.
Add remaining flour.
Stir rapidly with whisk until dark and smooth.

title: potato casserole
directions: Place thawed hash browns in a 13 x 9-inch (or larger) baking dish.
Combine next 7 ingredients and pour over hash browns. Sprinkle corn flake crumbs evenly on top. Drizzle 1/4 cup margarine over corn flake crumbs and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hide and seek meatballs
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; mix well.
Add beef and mix well until well blended.
Form into small balls.
Brown on all sides and put in casserole.
Drain off all but 3 teaspoons of fat and saute onion, then add applesauce, horseradish, tomato, basil, salt and pepper.
Pour over meatballs.
Top with pastry.
Serves 6. Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate cobbler
directions: Melt the butter and pour in a 9 x 13 Pyrex dish. Mix flour with 1 1/2 cups sugar and 4 tablespoons cocoa in a bowl. Stir in milk and vanilla. Pour this mixture into the dish. Sprinkle pecans on top of the batter. Then mix the 2 cups sugar and 4 tablespoons cocoa together (I have found that it mixes a lot easier in a Ziploc sandwich bag). Sprinkle this mixture over the batter. Pour 2 cups hot water over all. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve warm with ice cream or Cool Whip or serve cold. It is wonderful either way.

title: mexican dish
directions: Brown ground meat; drain off excess fat.
Add taco seasoning and do as directed on package.
Add remaining ingredients; put in baking dish.
Spread cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: strawberry jello salad(serves 15)
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add cold water and frozen berries.
Stir until thawed.
Add cream cheese; cut in small pieces.
Mold.
Serve with a little whipped cream.

title: indian pudding
directions: Scald milk; save out 1/2 cup.
Add meal and cook 20 minutes. Add sugar and other ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour in uncovered casserole.
Stir twice, then add remaining 1/2 cup milk.
Bake 30 minutes longer.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: very easy cake
directions: You will need a Bundt cake pan.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute onion and pepper in oil.
Add chicken; mix well.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste and 3 paste cans of water.
Add remaining ingredients except spaghetti and season with salt.
Simmer slowly for 1 hour.
Serve over cooked spaghetti and Parmesan cheese. Serves 8.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix dry pudding into whipped cream.
Add pineapple with juice, marshmallows and nuts.
Mix well and refrigerate.
Serve cold.

title: 30-minute chicken vegetable soup
directions: Combine broth and water in a 3 to 4-quart saucepan.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Add potatoes; cover and cook 5 minutes.
Add chicken, carrot and celery; cover and cook 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 5 minutes or until tender.

title: sugar-free pumpkin pie
directions: Mix in order.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°. Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 45 minutes or until when knife is inserted it comes out clean.

title: magic salad
directions: Stir cottage cheese and jello together.
Mix well.
Add Cool Whip and continue to fold over and over.
Toss in marshmallows and fruit; serve.

title: meatball soup
directions: This is a full-flavored Italian specialty featuring pasta, garbanzo beans and spinach.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add taco seasoning.
Spread refried beans in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Spread hamburger mixture over beans.
Sprinkle 1 cup of cheese over hamburger.
Pour picante sauce over cheese, top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Serve with taco chips.

title: tomato and beef macaroni
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Stir in stewed tomatoes, macaroni, dressing and desired vegetable.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake at 350° to 400° until cheese bubbles for 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: grandpa craig's roquefort cheese dip
directions: Soften butter and cheese 1/2 hour before starting.
Blend all ingredients, adding cream a small amount at a time.
When adding cream, add small amount if dip is desired as a spread or larger amount if the dip is desired for vegetables.
Scoop into bowl. Garnish with paprika or parsley.
Serve with crackers or vegetable strips.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Combine vinegar, sugar, mustard, salt and garlic or onion juice in blender.
Add oil very slowly, blending constantly so you will get a thick dressing that will not separate easily.
Add poppy seed to barely mix into the dressing.
Refrigerate before using.
Will keep for several weeks.
Make only one recipe at a time.

title: round steak casserole
directions: Season round steak lightly with garlic salt, salt and pepper. Cut into serving pieces and place in crock-pot with sliced onion, separated into rings.
Add potatoes and beans.
Top with tomato soup and tomatoes.
Cover and cook on low for 8 hours.
Remove cover last half hour if there is too much liquid.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Drain all cooked meats on paper towels. Press crescent rolls on ungreased cookie sheet or pizza pan.
Press up sides of pan and seal perforations.
Layer meats on crust.
Layer hash browns and cheese.
Beat together the eggs, milk, salt, pepper and Parmesan cheese.
Pour over entire pizza.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes. Bake at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: italian easter cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time and continue to beat well.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add gradually to creamed mixture and mix well.
If dough is too dry, add 1 to 3 tablespoons milk.
(It depends on egg size.) Pick dough about the size of a walnut and make a ball.
Place 2-inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes until set.
Do not allow to get brown as this makes them hard.
Dough should be sticky which makes them soft. Ice with icing (tinted pink and some light green).
Dip in sprinkles and let dry.

title: lemon cream pie
directions: Mix lemonade and Eagle Brand milk about 2 minutes with electric mixer.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Mix 2 minutes.
Pour into 2 precooked and cooled pie shells.
Graham cracker pie shells may be used.
Refrigerate.

title: chocolate chip coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until well mixed.
Add vanilla and eggs, one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with sour cream.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain (3 cups).
Stir in butter and Parmesan cheese and beaten eggs.
Form this mixture into a "crust" in a buttered 10-inch pie pan.
Spread cottage cheese over the bottom crust.
In skillet cook meat, onion and green pepper until veggies are tender and meat is brown.
Drain off fat.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste and spices.
Heat.
Spoon mixture into spaghetti crust.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and bake 5 more minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Combine ingredients; pour into unbaked pie crust and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cap'n crunch cookies
directions: Melt bark.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Allow to cool.

title: swiss chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Beat until smooth.
Put into sprayed cake pans.
After cake cooks, cut cakes in half.
Frost cake.

title: taco ring
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Combine meat, cheese, taco seasoning and water. Arrange crescent triangles in a circle on a 13-inch baking stone with bases overlapping in center and points to outside. Spoon meat mixture over rolls. Fold points of triangle over filling and tuck under base at center (filling will not be completely covered). Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown. Place bell pepper in center and fill with salsa. Mound chopped lettuce, onions and tomato around pepper. Garnish with sour cream.

title: spiced pecans
directions: In small saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in sugar and spices and mix well.
Pour over pecans in large pan, 9 x 12 or 13-inch, and mix well to coat.

title: fruit sherbet
directions: In food processor or blender, blend juice, egg yolks and yogurt.
Pour into container and freeze until center is mushy (almost frozen).
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Blend with yogurt/juice mixture.
Cover and freeze.

title: bean pot
directions: Brown and drain ground beef and onions.
Add soup, pork and beans, salt, pepper and chili powder.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes; serve in soup bowls with crackers.

title: easy-mac
directions: Put it in a bowl.
Put in the "mikeuwave."
Cook it for 3 minutes and wait for it to cool.

title: seafood kabobs
directions: Cut all vegetables into 2-inch chunks.
Peel and devein shrimp. Cut swordfish into 2-inch chunks.
Alternate vegetables and fish on 4 skewers.
Marinate in olive oil, garlic and fresh parsley for 1 hour.
Broil for 10 minutes.
Remove skewers, keeping shape.
Serve over Saffron Rice.

title: chili popcorn
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter flavor Crisco in heavy 3-quart saucepan
with lid. Add popcorn. Pop according to directions on popcorn container (7 to 8 cups popcorn is needed; if not enough, pop more).

title: veggie pizza
directions: *Carrots, broccoli, cauliflower, bell pepper, onion, mushrooms, etc.

title: old-fashioned cherry cobbler
directions: Combine sugar, butter, flour, baking powder and evaporated milk.
Mix well.
Spread batter in 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf dish.
Spread cherry pie filling over batter.
Pour hot water over pie filling.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: icebox cake
directions: Melt chocolate in
double
boiler.
Add
sugar
and hot water. Stir and remove from heat.
Separate eggs.
Add 1 yolk at a time to
chocolate mixture.
Blend well after each yolk. Beat well.

title: pinto beans and ham hocks
directions: Cook ham hock until tender.
Put pinto beans together with meat in broth along with more water if needed, adding pepper, salt and sugar.
Boil hard for 1 1/2 hours, then turn heat down and cook until liquid is slightly thickened and beans mash easily with fingertips.

title: muffins
directions: Sift flour once, then sift again with baking powder, salt and sugar.
Combine egg, milk and margarine.
Combine wet ingredients with dry ingredients.
Stir until dry ingredients are moist.
Pour in greased muffin tins.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes. Yields 10 to 12 muffins.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt chocolate in boiling water; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Also, add melted chocolate and vanilla.
Stir until smooth.
In a small mixing bowl, sift together the flour, soda and salt; add dry ingredients to creamed mixture slowly.
Lastly, add buttermilk and blend all very well.
Pour into a greased and floured pan.
Bake until done.

title: mandarin torte
directions: Tear angel food cake into small pieces and place in large bowl. Dissolve jello in hot water and pour over angel food cake; stir. Add orange sherbet to mixture and stir until sherbet is dissolved. Fold in Cool Whip until mixed well.
Drain mandarin oranges (may reserve a few for garnish, if desired).
Stir in and pour in 9-inch spring-form pan.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: steak and potato scallop
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut steaks into serving size chunks. Dip in seasoned flour, brown on both sides, in hot oil in frying pan.
Remove steaks and set aside.
Add leftover flour to skillet and brown well.
Add water enough to make gravy. Simmer.
Add more seasonings as desired.

title: italian meat balls
directions: Mix and make into meatballs.
Bake on cookie sheet at 400° about 12 to 15 minutes, until nicely browned.
Turn over once.

title: no bake cocoa puff bars
directions: Mix butter, peanut butter, honey and chocolate chips in a saucepan.
Melt.
Add peanuts and Cocoa Puffs cereal.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut in squares.

title: eclair cake
directions: Beat pudding, milk, & sugar until smooth. Fold in cool whip. Place a layer of graham crackers on the bottom of a 9 x 13 baking dish.

title: dutch apple cake
directions: Sprinkle apples with cinnamon and 5 tablespoons sugar.
Set aside.
Grease and flour tube pan.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients except the apple mixture.
In tube pan, start with a layer of batter, then a layer of apple mixture; six layers in all, ending with apples on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: chicken fricassee
directions: Heat oil and goya sofrito.
Rub chicken with garlic, oregano and adobo.
Saute chicken in oil until browned.
Add peppers, onion, cilantro, tomato sauce and wine.
Simmer 5 minutes, then add potatoes and carrots.
Cook until chicken is done and vegetables are soft, about 1 hour.
Periodically check liquid level and add a little water, if necessary.
Serve with white rice.

title: muscadine pie
directions: Beat egg yolks. Add sugar, flour, butter, milk and muscadines. Cook over low heat until it thickens; stir occasionally to keep from sticking. Pour in pie shell and bake at 350° until done.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and freeze in 9 x 13-inch pan. Cut into squares about 10 minutes before serving.

title: smoked sausage casserole
directions: Saute butter, onion and sausage in skillet.
Add potatoes, water, broccoli, carrots and cheese.
Simmer until done.

title: microwave cashew chicken
directions: Heat oil in 3-quart casserole on High for 2 to 3 minutes. Combine chicken, garlic, soy sauce, sherry, cornstarch and ginger. Put ingredients in oil and cook on High 4 to 5 minutes.
Stir twice during the 4 to 5 minutes.
Add green pepper (broccoli) and cashews.
Cook, covered with plastic wrap, on High 3 to 5 minutes or until chicken and vegetables are tender.
Stir and let stand 3 minutes before serving.
Serve with favorite brand of rice.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt butter in medium saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients and beat well.
Pour in greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool well to cut into wedges. If hot, spoon out.
Serve with ice cream.

title: pinto bean cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening: add egg.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add creamed mixture.
Stir in beans, apples, raisins, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour 15 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: green bean surprise
directions: In saucepan, over medium heat, melt and saute margarine, onions, beef bouillon and mushrooms.
Cook until onions are tender.
Add beans and water chestnuts; cook over medium heat for 30 minutes to blend flavors.

title: dip
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and let set overnight to blend flavors.

title: mom's easy baked stew
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray a deep roasting pan with cooking spray. Layer ingredients by first placing meat, then vegetables in pan. Sprinkle with onion soup mix. Then pour cream of mushroom and tomato soups over the vegetables. Cover pan tightly with foil and bake for 3 hours. Serve over rice. Don't open foil while cooking and do not stir.

title: punch
directions: Bring to boil the water and sugar and cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Very sweet, can use less sugar.

title: crepes
directions: In a bowl, combine flour and salt.
Beat eggs with milk in a separate bowl.
Add mixture to dry ingredients, beating vigorously.
Using a tablespoon, drop batter, 2 tablespoons at a time, on a hot greased griddle.
Cook for 2 minutes, until brown, then turn.
Cook other side until brown.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Yields 12 crepes.

title: ricotta cheese cake
directions: Follow box directions to mix cake.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan.
Mix sugar, Ricotta cheese, vanilla and eggs together.
Do not stir.
Just pour into center of cake.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: "forge" cheesecake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients with electric mixer until smooth. Pour into graham cracker crust.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: eight layer mexican dip
directions: In a large casserole dish (9 x 13-inch baking dish), make a layer of bean dip. Combine avocados and guacamole dip and layer on top of bean dip. Combine mayonnaise, sour cream and taco mix. Stir well.
Use mayonnaise mixture as the next layer.
Layer with cheeses next, followed by onions and tomatoes. Top with olives. Serve with king size Fritos or tortilla chips.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mince shallots, green olives, capers and hard cooked egg very finely.
Add this to the mayo, Dijon and sweet pickle relish.
Mix thoroughly.
Add lemon juice to thin.
Sugar to taste, parsley to garnish.
Yields 1 1/3 cup.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Drop by ice cream scoop on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with flour-dipped glass, 6 to a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes only.

title: orange slice cake
directions: In a bowl, stir together the pecans, dates, candy, cherries and coconut.
Pour melted butter over mixture; stir well.
Let stand while preparing cake batter.

title: chili rellenos squares
directions: Layer cheeses and chilies in a greased 8-inch baking dish, starting and ending with cheese.
In a bowl, beat the eggs.
Add milk and flour; pour over cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until set.
Cut into small squares.
Serve warm.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain grease.
Put sausage in casserole dish.
Layer rice, soup, cheese and bread crumbs in dish.
Pour melted margarine over the top.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until cheese is melted well.

title: hot cheese and sausage dip
directions: Cube cheese and melt in crock-pot or double boiler.
Add sausage and peppers.
Mix well.

title: breakfast muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into greased muffin tins. Bake at 400° for 12 to 14 minutes. Makes 12 muffins.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Pour over while hot.
Use the amount of green pepper and onion to suit you in proportion to the amount of cabbage you have.
Keep covered and refrigerated and it will keep indefinitely.

title: italian frittata (omelette)(quick meal using leftover spaghetti)
directions: Mix together eggs.
Add salt, pepper, oregano and basil.
Add spaghetti and Parmesan cheese.
Put in heated pan with a little olive oil.
Brown on bottom.
Then put under broiler to finish top.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease oblong pan (13 x 9 x 2-inches). Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in pan and bake until golden brown, approximately 25 to 30 minutes.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in oleo until tender.
Mix cooked rice and broccoli (steamed), then add sauteed onion and celery and mix thoroughly.
Next, add the 2 cans of soup and mix.
Add Cheez Whiz to mixture.
Pour all into a casserole bowl.
Bake in a 400° oven until bubbly.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix 1/3 of the sugar with the bananas.
Mix 1/2 cup shortening with the other 2/3 cup sugar.
Add rest of the ingredients.
Bake at 325° in a loaf pan for 1 hour.

title: taffy apple dip
directions: Mix ingredients and serve with apple slices.

title: fudgemallow candy
directions: Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter over low heat.
Remove from heat and add raisins and marshmallows.
Pour into foil lined 8-inch square pan.
Chill.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix sauerkraut, carrots, green pepper, onion and pimiento.
In a jar or small bowl, combine sugar and oil. Pour over vegetables; mix well.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 8 hours.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time. Beat well.
Sift flour several times with soda.
Add alternately with buttermilk.
Add flavoring.
Bake at 350° in tube pan or in large sheet pan.

title: dijon dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients; stir with a wire whisk until blended. Cover; chill at least 1 hour. Serve over salad greens. Yield: 1 2/3 cups.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix boiling water and oats and let stand for 20 minutes. Cream together shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Add oats mixture.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Bake in a greased sheet pan at 275° for 35 to 45 minutes.
While still warm, put topping on cake and return to oven to broil for about 5 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt butter.
Add milk and flour, blend well.
Add beaten eggs and add sugar, salt and pepper.
Blend all real well, then add both kinds of corn.
Put in casserole dish and bake at 325° for 1 hour, making sure corn is set as a pudding.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: calico beans
directions: Drain pinto, Great Northern, lima, kidney and butter beans. Saute bacon and onion; remove.
Reserve some bacon grease.
Fry hamburg, breaking into small pieces.
Add beans, bacon and onion. Mix together remaining ingredients; add to previous ingredients. Place in casserole and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Add all ingredients together; put into buttered casserole.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: no-peek chicken
directions: In a roast pan with lid, put rice on bottom.
Place chicken on top of rice.
Mix cream of chicken, cream of mushroom soup and milk together.
Pour over chicken, sprinkle on top the package of onion soup mix.
Place lid on roaster.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.
Do not lift lid before baking time is over.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Soften cheese.
In a blender, add cheese and shrimp sauce. Chill and dip.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together.
Put browned mixture on paper towels to drain.
Pour grease from pan and wipe.
Return mixture to pan.
Add other ingredients and stir.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve on hamburger buns.
Makes 8 sloppy joes.

title: tortilla espanola(spanish omelette)
directions: Amounts vary depending on size of ingredients, pan and personal preferences.

title: snow pudding with custard sauce
directions: Soften gelatin in the cold water.
Add 1 cup of sugar, the salt and boiling water; stir to dissolve gelatin and sugar.
Add lemon rind and juice.
Chill until partially set.

title: squash dressing
directions: Combine the ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Heat juice from all fruit and canned fruit used with 1/2 cup sugar.
Cool.
Beat 2 eggs, 1/4 cup cream and 1 teaspoon flour. Mix with juice and sugar mixture and cook until thick on low heat. Cool in refrigerator overnight.
Pour over fruit.

title: baked chicken supreme
directions: Combine rice, celery, onion, carrot, parsley, butter and seasonings.
Mix lightly.
Spoon mixture into greased 3-quart shallow baking dish.
Top with chicken pieces.
Combine soup, salad dressing and milk until well blended.
Pour over chicken. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cocoa.
Add mayonnaise, water and vanilla and mix together. Put in a 9 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: tallerini
directions: Brown meat in Dutch oven.
Add onions and let wilt.
Cut olives in halves.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
(Bake in casserole dish.)

title: chewies
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 9x13 greased cake pan.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients together.
Add eggs and beat again. Add remaining ingredients.
Place small balls on greased cookie sheets; flatten slightly with fork.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Makes about 50 large cookies.

title: make ahead pie crust
directions: Cut up all to look like small peas.
Put in gallon jar.
Use 3/4 cup pie dough per shell.
Add 1 tablespoon cold water at a time.
Mix lightly, then roll.
Store extra in cupboard during cool months or in refrigerator during warm months.

title: rice balls
directions: Mix meat and rice.
Add eggs, onions and peppers.
Pour 1/4 cup of tomato juice to moisten.
Add sugar to tomato juice and fill with water to 2 cups.
Make meatballs.
Place in skillet and pour juice over.
Cook, turning once, about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: icebox cheese cake
directions: Combine graham crackers and margarine in an 8 x 16-inch dish. Microwave until margarine melts.
Stir, then pat 3/4 of mixture in bottom of dish.
Save the rest to sprinkle on top of the cake.

title: peanut patties
directions: Cook sugar, Karo, milk and peanuts to a soft ball stage. Remove from heat; add other ingredients and beat until smooth. Drop by spoonfuls on a buttered cookie sheet or waxed paper.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into small chunks.
Do not peel.
Place in a plastic bag (I use a clean grocery bag, but check for holes first) and add other ingredients. Shake and use hands on outside of bag until well coated.
Place in large baking pan and bake at 375° for 45 minutes until done.
I spray with Pam first. Also, if you use more potatoes and want a more oniony taste, increase oil and use 2 packs soup mix.

title: microwave scrambled eggs in a mug
directions: In a 12 ounce microwave-safe mug, microwave the butter on High for 45 seconds to 1 minute or until melted.
Add the eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Stir or whip with a fork.
Microwave on High until eggs begin to set, stirring to break the eggs apart once during cooking time.
Remove eggs while they are still soft and moist.
Let stand 1 to 2 minutes or until eggs are set.
If desired, sprinkle with shredded cheese and crumbled cooked bacon during standing time.
Makes 1 serving.

title: oven roasted vegetables
directions: Cut vegetables in small chunks.
Put into Ziploc bag.
Pour in olive oil and soup mix.
Shake until vegetables are coated well. Place in shallow baking pan and bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: fruit dip
directions: Allow cream cheese to soften, then whip it with Marshmallow Creme until smooth and fluffy.
Use as a dip for strawberries, grapes, slices of apple or pears or other fruit.

title: black walnut pound cake
directions: Mix ingredients; put in tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Do not overcook.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix vanilla pudding following directions on box.
Layer in punch bowl:
1/2 cake (crumbled), 1/2 vanilla pudding, 1/2 of cherry filling, 1/2 pineapple, 1/2 Cool Whip, 1/2 coconut and 1/2 nuts.
Repeat layer.

title: squirrel muligan
directions: Place in large crock-pot.
Add juice to discretion.
Remember, the rice will absorb some liquid.
Cook for several hours until done.

title: broccoli and ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion in skillet, stirring until ground beef is crumbly; drain.
Cook broccoli using package directions; drain.
Combine soup with milk, garlic powder, salt and pepper in bowl; mix well.
Layer ground beef, rice, soup, broccoli and cheese 1/2 at a time in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until heated through.
Serve with ambrosia, rolls and iced tea.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: cheese pretzels
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add honey, salt and sugar. Stir well.
Add flour and mix well.
Knead.
Roll into long sticks and shape into pretzels.
Brush with beaten egg for crisp pretzel. Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: tangy party balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Gently roll into firm, small balls (1 1/2-inch).
Set aside. Prepare sauce.

title: 7 layer casserole
directions: Place these ingredients in layers in a 2-quart baking dish with tight fitting cover.
Place the rice and whole kernel corn in layers.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour 1 can tomato sauce and 1/2 can of water over the first 2 layers.
The next layers will be the onion, green pepper and the ground beef.
Pour second can of tomato sauce and 1/4 can of water over all.
Cover meat with the bacon.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake about 30 minutes longer.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: In large microwave-safe dish, melt Velveeta cubes.
Stir every 30 seconds; be careful not to scorch.
Once cheese is melted, add milk, a little at a time.
Keep stirring until smooth.
Microwave another 30 seconds.
Add picante salsa; stir until blended.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.
Can be refrigerated and reheated.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and shape into balls.
Melt chocolate and paraffin.
Dip balls into chocolate.

title: golden treasure pie
directions: Combine pineapple, sugar, cornstarch and water in small saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Blend sugar and butter, flour, cheese, vanilla and salt until smooth.
Slowly add eggs and milk to cheese mixture, beating constantly.
Pour pineapple into crust, spreading evenly.
Gently pour custard over pineapple, being careful not to disturb first layer.
Bake at 425°
for 15 minutes, then at 325°
for 45 minutes longer.

title: olive cheese balls
directions: Mix first three ingredients together.
Mold approximately 1 teaspoon dough around each olive and shape into ball.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Chill one hour or more.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: ice cream delight
directions: Mix all 3 ingredients together.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover with plastic wrap and freeze.
Cut into squares to serve. Rich, but delicious.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients in medium size casserole and cook (season to taste) for 30 to 40 minutes, uncovered.

title: barbecue slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in refrigerator in an airtight container.
Keeps for months.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken, celery, onion, soup, mayonnaise, chopped eggs, lemon juice, almonds and cheese.
Sprinkle some grated cheese and cracker crumbs on top.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.
Freezes well.

title: fudgsicles
directions: Mix well and freeze.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut meat into serving pieces.
Roll each piece of meat in flour mixed with salt and pepper.
Brown each piece of meat in hot grease or oil.
Place browned meat in casserole or small roasting pan. Drain the grease from the pan where meat was browning, leaving the drippings.

title: taco dip
directions: Fry hamburg; add taco mix.
After blending, add beans.
Let simmer.
Put Cheddar cheese on top and let melt.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer about 1 hour.
Add cooked spaghetti, if desired.

title: zucchini pie casserole
directions: Saute zucchini and onion in margarine for 15 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Line 8-inch pie pan with crescent rolls. Pour in mixture of zucchini.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly; add sugar, lemon juice, lemon extract and vinegar.
Mix well.
Add melted margarine, stirring until well mixed.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 to
40 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine flour, sugar, salt and pepper.
Mix corn and well beaten eggs.
Add flour mixture.
Stir in butter and cream mixture.
Add Tabasco sauce; stir thoroughly.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Stir from bottom once or twice during first 30 minutes.

title: impossible chicken and broccoli pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Layer chicken, broccoli and cheese in greased 9-inch pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients (except topping) 15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with mixer. Pour into baking dish.
Bake 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with topping. Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.

title: ritz pecan pie
directions: Beat egg whites until they start to stiffen.
Slowly add sugar, baking powder and vanilla.
Continue beating until stiff, but not dry.
Carefully fold in coarse crumbs and pecans.
Grease and lightly flour a 9-inch pie pan and fill with mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool and top with slightly sweetened whipped cream flavored with ___ . Combine 3 Ritz crackers (crushed), 2 tablespoons toasted pecans (chopped), 1 tablespoon sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Sprinkle over whipped cream.

title: easy baked chicken
directions: Spray 2-quart baking dish with vegetable cooking spray. Arrange chicken, bone side down, in dish.
Sprinkle with garlic powder and pepper.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken delicious
directions: Place 8 slices beef on rectangular casserole dish.
Place chicken on top of each beef slice.
Put another beef slice on top of each chicken piece.
Blend soup and sour cream well and pour over meats.
Bake, uncovered (or with pierced foil cover) at 325° for 1 hour or so.

title: macaroni and beef bake
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Rinse in cold water and drain. Brown beef, onion and pepper in skillet. Stir in flour. Add tomatoes and cook until mixture thickens. Stir in
cheese, seasonings and macaroni. Spoon into buttered casserole. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes until hot and golden brown.
(I usually sprinkle more cheese on top before baking.)

title: brownies
directions: Beat eggs until foamy; add sugar and mix well.
Melt margarine, then add Choco Bake to margarine.
Add margarine/chocolate mixture to the sugar and eggs.
Mix well.
Add flour.
Add vanilla and nuts; mix well.
Bake at 350° in a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan for approximately 30 to 35 minutes. They are done when a toothpick comes out clean.
Let cool and then sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except butter and put in well-greased casserole pan. Cut butter into chunks and place on top of mixture. Bake for 1 hour in 300° oven.

title: coconut roll
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine.
Add egg, powdered sugar, marshmallows, walnuts and vanilla.
Shape into a roll in coconut. Put in freezer.
Slice.

title: cream cheese tart pastry
directions: Blend cheese, butter and flour with pastry blender; add water. Chill.
Pinch off piece the size of large marbles.
Roll into a ball, place in muffin tin and press around sides and in bottom. Prick bottom and sides.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Fill with favorite pie filling.

title: crazy cake
directions: Sift the flour, cocoa, baking soda, sugar, salt and baking powder into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch cake pan.
Make three holes in the mixture and into the first hole put the vanilla, into the second hole put the vinegar and into the third hole put the melted shortening.
Pour the hot water over the whole mixture and mix until smooth.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes, or until firm to the touch.
Frost with favorite frosting.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Saute minced onion, butter and shredded cabbage.
Place the rest of the ingredients in a large pan.
Add sauteed mixture to pan and allow to cook until done.
You may want to change some amounts as I made this by trial and error, but it tastes real good.

title: butterballs
directions: Mix well.
Roll in small balls and bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: kourabiedes(greek)
directions: Beat butter and sugar until creamy, about 15 minutes.
Add egg yolk, flavorings and almonds, beating until well blended.
Remove from beater and gradually add sifted flour to make a soft dough.

title: punch
directions: Dilute frozen juices as directed on cans.
Combine with all ingredients (except sherbet).
Float scoops/chunks of sherbet on top.

title: peanut butter pinwheels
directions: Boil potato with the jacket on.
When potato is done, peel and mash into a cup.
Makes about 1 cup of potato.
Mix potato and powdered sugar until it makes a stiff dough.
Roll out dough on wax paper.
Spread peanut butter on rolled-out dough.
Roll up like a jelly roll and cut off into pinwheels.
Makes 24 to 30 Peanut Butter Pinwheels.

title: easy peanut butter pie
directions: Blend all ingredients well with mixer except the Cool Whip. Fold in the Cool Whip.
Put in pie crust and freeze.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together raisins, shortening, sugar, eggs and milk. Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: dinosaur stew
directions: Cut the dinosaur into bite size cubes (be sure to allow enough time for this, about a week).
Simmer in gravy over fire for 3 days.
Add salt and pepper.

title: sloan's christmas punch
directions: Mix jello with 2 cups of the hot water and mix sugar with 3 cups of the hot water.
Mix rest of ingredients except ginger ale. Mix ginger ale in just before serving.

title: chocolate eggless cake
directions: In one bowl, mix water, oil and vinegar.
In another bowl, mix the flour, sugar, salt, soda and cocoa.
Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix the first five ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well and refrigerate at least two hours before baking.
It may be kept in the refrigerator for two weeks at this stage.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil chicken breasts in salted water with onion and celery for 40 minutes.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry.
Cut chicken in bite size pieces.
Place broccoli in a greased casserole, next the chicken and top all with sauce.
Top sauce with grated cheese and crumbs or dressing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: danish meat loaf
directions: Have pork and beef ground together.
Combine meat, egg, onion and seasonings.
Add flour and beat using electric mixer, until thoroughly blended and fluffy.
Add milk slowly, 1 tablespoon at a time, beating well.
Shape into a long loaf in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Refrigerate until cold. Makes about 24 thin slices.
Serve on light rye, pumpernickel or egg bread.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Mix together the two ingredients.
Press into 8-inch square pan.
Bake 5 minutes; cool.

title: peanut butter cream pie
directions: Crust:
Melt 1 stick butter; remove from heat.
Stir in 1 cup flour.
Mix well.
Add the chopped pecans.
Pat into a 10-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool before filling.

title: marble chiffon cake
directions: Sift
together
flour,
1 1/2 cups sugar, baking powder and salt.
Make
a
well
in the center of the dry ingredients and add in
this order:
salad oil, egg yolks, cold water and vanilla. Beat
until
satin smooth.
In a large bowl beat egg whites with cream of tartar until very stiff peaks form.
Pour egg
yolk batter
in
thin
stream over entire surface of egg whites, gently
folding
to blend.
Remove 1/3 of batter to a separate bowl.
Blend
together
boiling water, 2 tablespoons sugar
and Hershey's chocolate.
Gently fold chocolate mixture into
the
1/3 portion
of
batter.
Spoon
half of the light batter
into
an ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Pour in half of chocolate batter. Repeat layers with remaining batters.
With a narrow spatula, swirl gently through batters to form marbled pattern.
Bake in slow oven (325°) for 55 minutes.
Raise oven to 350°
and
bake 10
minutes
longer.
(Cake
is done if it springs
back when you touch the surface lightly.) Invert cake over
pop
bottle in pan; cool.
Then frost with your favorite chocolate frosting.

title: barbecue baked beans
directions: Saute onions and peppers until onion is transparent.
Add chopped ham, molasses, brown sugar, mustard, chili powder, salt, barbecue sauce and catsup, mix well.
Add to pork and beans and pour in 9 x 12-inch oblong pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: chicken cutlets
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray cookie sheet with nonstick cooking spray. Dip chicken in margarine or butter and coat with remaining ingredients.
Place in pan and bake 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.

title: greek cookie balls
directions: Mix butter, sugar and vanilla.
Gradually stir in flour and nuts.
Chill 1/2 hour.
Shape into marble size balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 17 minutes until firm but not brown.
While hot, roll cookies in confectioners sugar.
Cool.
Roll again in sugar.

title: shirley's biscuits(our very own strawberry social biscuits)
directions: Blend together the first 4 ingredients.
Add milk, stir and roll or pat out on floured board; cut.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: tamale balls
directions: Combine all ingredients together and form into firm small balls.
(If not firm enough, add a little more cornmeal.) Drop into Sauce.
Simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour. Stir gently so as not to break up the balls.
Some prefer to lay in pan in oven and simmer in sauce.

title: frozen caramel cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese and sweetened condensed milk until blended. Spoon in Cool Whip topping and blend.
This mixture will be divided into fourths.
Spread one fourth of mixture in bottom of each pie shell.
Sprinkle pecans and heavily drizzle caramel topping on top. Divide the remaining mixture between the two pies and spread on top.
Sprinkle with pecans and heavily drizzle caramel topping on top.
Freeze.
Serve slightly softened.

title: custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Brush crust with egg whites to seal before you add the liquid.

title: apricot salad
directions: Mix jello according to directions.
When beginning to gel, add marshmallows, bananas and crushed pineapple.
Let set.

title: chicken divan
directions: Place cooked broccoli in shallow baking dish. Top with sliced chicken. Sprinkle with cheese. Combine soup, mayonnaise, and lemon juice. Pour over the chicken. Sprinkle bread crumbs on top, along with additional shredded cheese, if desired. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through. May use low-fat soup, cheese and mayonnaise if desired.

title: candied apples
directions: Mix ingredients.
Boil constantly until mixture thickens. Test in cold water.
When mixture tests brittle, add red food coloring.
Turn to low heat and dip apples.

title: paradise pudding
directions: Put pie filling in bottom of baking dish. Add pineapple. Sprinkle 1/2 of the coconut on top.
Sprinkle cake mix over this. Melt butter and mix well with pecans and rest of the coconut. Pour on top of the cake mix and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Reduce heat 25° for glass dish.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together and use with any kind of fruit.

title: seafood quiche
directions: Prebake pie shell 10 minutes.
Mix together the other ingredients; place in pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: turtles
directions: Bake pecan halves with one caramel on top of each pecan in 300° oven for 7 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Place one square of Hershey bar on top of each.

title: mexicali tacos
directions: Brown the hamburger, onion and green pepper.
Add taco seasoning and stir completely.
Add soups.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes. Serve in taco shells with shredded lettuce, diced tomatoes, shredded cheese and sour cream.

title: grilled herbed corn
directions: In small bowl, combine first six ingredients.
Spread 1 tablespoon over each ear of corn.
Wrap individually in heavy-duty foil.
Grill, covered, over medium coals for 10 to 15 minutes, turning frequently.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: lime mist salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water and cool.
Mix remaining ingredients in blender.
Fold all together and put in mold.
Refrigerate.

title: cheese cake
directions: Blend cream cheese and cottage cheese together.
Add sugar, lemon juice, vanilla and eggs and blend together.
Add remaining ingredients to mixture.

title: chinese pork and rice casserole
directions: In a food processor, finely chop ginger and garlic.
Add scallions; coarsely chop.
Remove from the processor; set aside. In the same processor work bowl, coarsely chop the carrots; remove and set aside.
Add the Chinese cabbage; coarsely chop.
In a large skillet, warm 1 tablespoon of the sesame oil over medium-high heat until hot but not smoking.
Add the ginger, garlic, scallions and ground pork; stir-fry, breaking up the meat, until the pork is no longer pink, about 5 minutes.

title: fluffy peanut butter pie
directions: In a medium bowl, beat cheese until soft and fluffy; beat in sugar and peanut butter.
Slowly add milk, blending thoroughly. Fold Cool Whip into this mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle with nuts, if desired.
Chill.

title: creamy chowder
directions: Cook, salt and boil potatoes.
Drain, reserving water.
Dice potatoes, about 2 cups.
In large saucepan melt butter; stir in celery.
Saute until tender.
Add corn, potatoes, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt, basil and pepper.
Cover; heat 10 minutes.
Add milk and reserved potato water, if needed to make 1 2/3 cups.
Heat.
Makes 6 servings.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Saute onions in oil until yellow.
Remove from skillet.
Add meat cubes to skillet.
Sprinkle with flour and brown meat thoroughly.
When meat is well browned, add 1/4 cup bouillon and 1 cup wine, marjoram, thyme, oregano, salt and pepper.
Cover pan tightly and simmer over low heat about 2 hours, gradually adding remaining bouillon and wine.
Add onions and mushrooms which have been sauteed in butter.
Cook 20 to 30 minutes longer, until meat is tender.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Good!!

title: yorkshire potato pudding
directions: Boil and mash potatoes.
Combine bouillon cube, hot milk, butter, salt and pepper.
Beat into potatoes.
Reserve 1 1/2 tablespoons of the beaten egg and beat the remainder into the potatoes.
Pile into a buttered 9-inch cake pan and brush with reserved egg.
Sprinkle with paprika and broil until the top is browned.
Cut into wedges to serve.
Serves 8.

title: wild rice salad
directions: Toss ingredients.
Serve with Wild Rice Dressing.

title: christmas delight
directions: Melt the chocolate and paraffin together.
Keep warm as you dip the chocolates.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix jello in hot water until dissolved.
Add pineapple and pie filling.
Chill until firm.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Melt shortening.
Cool slightly.
Beat melted shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, beating after each.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.

title: mexican eggs
directions: Beat eggs and sour cream until frothy.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° until soft-set (5 to 7 minutes).
Spoon taco sauce over egg mixture.

title: strawberry preserves(strawberries are debbie's favorite fruit.)
directions: Mix well and with a bubble blower, make bubbles.

title: cheese cake
directions: Place ingredients in order given in large mixing bowl.
Beat with electric mixer.
Start on low-medium and finish on high, 10 minutes.
Batter should be smooth and liquidy.

title: scalloped hash browns
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in an oblong casserole. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: dessert
directions: Mix the flour, chopped nuts and oleo for the crust.
Pat in the bottom of Pyrex dish; bake for 15 minutes, until brown.

title: lemon mousse(lo-cal)
directions: Blend together egg yolk, gelatin, cornstarch and lemon juice. Add boiling water and rind.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour mixture into saucepan; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Simmer until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat; stir in Equal.
Chill.

title: persimmon fudge
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients to 236° on candy thermometer; beat a bit until creamy.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour out onto greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let cool.
Enjoy!

title: santa claus cookies
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Sift flour with spices, salt and soda. Add alternately with sour cream to the creamed mixture.
Add nuts. Knead together well. Shape into several loaves.
Wrap in wax paper and chill in refrigerator overnight (will keep for weeks in freezer!).
Slice and bake in a 375° oven or until browned.
I sprinkle the chilled loaf with red or green sugar before baking.

title: chicken rellenos
directions: Mix cracker crumbs, chili powder and cumin in shallow dish and set aside.
Pound each breast to 1/4-inch thick.
Top with 1/4 cup cheese, 1/2 teaspoon of chili powder and 1/2 teaspoon pimientos.
Roll chicken from short edge and secure with toothpick.
Coat with flour, eggs, then crackers.
Place in dish or on cookie sheet and drizzle with butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve with salsa.

title: judi's chocolate cake
directions: Mix ingredients in the order given.
Add a little more liquid if mixture is too stiff.
Oil and dust with flour three 8 or 9-inch pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until bouncy to touch.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: In a large skillet over medium heat, saute onion, celery and broccoli in oleo for 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir in soups and milk until smooth.
Place rice in a greased
8-inch square baking dish.
Pour cheese mixture over; do not stir.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: scalloped corn
directions: In cooking bowl, mix egg and milk together.
Add can of creamed corn and drained can of regular corn.
Stir in muffin mix. Bake in oven for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, oil, flour, salt, apples and vanilla. Mix well and pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
When cool, ice with frosting.

title: french beans and onion casserole
directions: Break cheese in little pieces.
Mix all ingredients together and place in casserole pan.
At 350°, cook 30 minutes, then add Durkee French onion rings on top last 5 minutes and lightly brown.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding beaten egg whites last.
Fry in deep hot fat using a wire basket.
To fry on a griddle, add 1/2 cup more milk.
Will make 18 fritters.

title: diet workshop salmon loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in loaf pan or casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let set for 10 minutes before serving.

title: quick and easy nutty cheese bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch rectangular baking pan.
For base, stir together in a medium bowl until well mixed the dry cake mix, melted butter or margarine and 3/4 cup pecans or walnuts.
Press mixture evenly into the bottom of prepared pan.

title: creamy chicken 'n shells salad
directions: Prepare dinner as directed on package.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Chill.
Add additional salad dressing before serving if desired.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and mix thoroughly. Sift dry ingredients together.
Using low speed of mixer, add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk and vanilla, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Add mashed bananas and nuts.
Mix lightly.
Pour in greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Drain tuna and add to noodles.
Add cream of mushroom soup and milk.
Pour into casserole dish. Add mushrooms, if desired. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit pie
directions: Cream margarine and sugar, add eggs (mix).
Add milk and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325°.

title: kentucky chess pie
directions: Cook filling in a double boiler until creamy.
Pour into pastry shell which has been lightly baked.
Place in a moderate oven and bake until firm.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix all sour cream with Hidden Valley Ranch.
Refrigerate while you prepare remaining.
Season chicken.
Fry onions in lemon juice. Cook until done, not overdone.

title: new england clam chowder(makes 8 cups)
directions: Saute the salt pork very slowly.
Remove and reserve the scraps.
Add the minced onions, celery and the clams to the grease.
Stir and cook slowly for about 5 minutes.
Heat and stir in the remaining liquid.
Add 2 cups raw, diced potatoes.
Cover the pan and simmer the chowder until the potatoes are done, but somewhat firm.
Add the pork scraps and 3 tablespoons butter. Simmer for 3 minutes more.
Add heated milk or half and half cream.
Don't boil.
Serve with oyster crackers.

title: sauerkraut
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Place bacon in pan.
Add cold water to cover.
Bring to a boil; simmer for 1 minute.
Drain.
Line dish with bacon slices.
Add kraut in center and onion in the middle. Add juniper berries, garlic and caraway seed.
Add sherry on top. Cover; bring to boil on stove, then bake in the oven for 2 1/2 hours.
Take lid off; bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: broccoli and chicken
directions: Cook broccoli as directed and line bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Cook chicken breasts in boiling water (or microwave) for 10 minutes and debone.
Place over broccoli.
Mix soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice; pour over chicken.
Put grated cheese on top.

title: popcorn
directions: You've just got to cook it.
And then you sit on the couch and you eat it.

title: peanut butter and  jelly mini muffins
directions: In a large bowl, mix flour and sugar. In a small bowl, beat the eggs, yogurt, peanut butter and oil on low speed until smooth; stir into the dry ingredients just until moistened. Fill greased or paper lined miniature muffin cups half full. Top each with 1/4 tsp. jelly and the remaining batter. Bake at 400° for 10-12 minutes.

title: carnation milk pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening with sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating between each.
Gradually add flour and milk.
Add salt.
Add flavoring.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: *I mix together 1 1/2 loaves of cubed bread, 1/2 pound melted margarine, 2 chopped onions and poultry seasoning.

title: meat balls in sour cream
directions: Mix the ground chuck, bread, egg, 1/2 package onion soup mix, mushrooms, salt, pepper and garlic thoroughly.
Make into small balls. Brown lightly in margarine.
Place in baking dish. Cover with the sour cream mixed with the remaining 1/2 package soup mix. Bake in a 325° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sin
directions: First Layer:
Mix flour, pecans, sugar and margarine.
Pack in bottom of 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Cool.

title: potato casserole
directions: Spread potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients, except bread crumbs.
Pour over potatoes.
Top with buttered bread crumbs. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Put in layers in order given into glass bowl.
Mix sour cream, dressing mix and Miracle Whip.
Pour on top of salad.
Add crumbled bacon and chopped egg on top, then sprinkle with fresh ground pepper.

title: country kitchen cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix; knead well.
Let rise.
Roll out.
Spread with butter, cinnamon and brown sugar.
Roll, cut and let rise again.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Frost, if desired.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Cook onions in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain water.
In saucepan, melt 2 tablespoons butter; blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk.
Cook and stir until very bubbly, then reduce heat and blend in cream cheese.
Place broccoli in casserole dish and pour sauce over it and stir well. Top casserole with sharp cheese.
Melt 2 teaspoons butter and pour over casserole, then sprinkle bread crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cheezy potatoes
directions: Butter casserole and add a layer of sliced potatoes.
Cover with a layer of bacon, crumbled, and a layer of cheese.
Continue layers until all ingredients are used.
Melt 1 stick of margarine and pour over casserole.
Bake at 350 for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: In a bowl, combine soup, milk, vegetables and tuna.
Fold in noodles.
Pour into greased crock-pot.
Cook on low for 7 to 9 hours (high 3 to 4 hours).

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix soups and Cheez Whiz in a large casserole dish.
Add broccoli.
Stir in 1/2 can onion rings; sprinkle the top of casserole with the other half.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon squares
directions: Combine butter, 10x sugar, salt, 2 cups flour in bowl.
Press mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 minutes or until light brown.
Cool slightly.
Combine remaining ingredients, 1/4 cup flour, 2 cups sugar, eggs, lemon juice.
Mix all together.
Pour over baked crust.
Sprinkle coconut over lemon mixture and bake for another 25 minutes or until set.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: molded shrimp spread
directions: Turn soup into saucepan and heat over low heat.
Blend in cream cheese and beat until smooth and dissolved.
Soften gelatin in water; add to soup mixture, stirring until dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Stir in celery, onion, mayonnaise and shrimp; season with salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into 1-quart ring mold and chill until set.
Unmold onto serving plate and garnish as desired.
Serve with crackers.

title: easy hors d'oeuvres
directions: Melt 1/2 pound butter.
Saute onion and chopped mushrooms in 1 tablespoon butter.
Saute for 2 minutes and remove from heat. Season with salt and pepper.
Add softened cream cheese.
Stir in spices.
Let stand.
Cut crusts off bread and spread mixture on bread slices.
Make 3 layers of bread (with mixture in between like sandwich).
Butter both sides of outside slices with melted butter. Cut into 6 pieces, carefully putting on a buttered cookie sheet. Bake at 350° until toasty brown.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix honey and butter in a saucepan. Heat over low heat until blended.
Stir occasionally.
Mix nuts and popcorn in a large bowl.
Slowly pour honey-butter over popcorn, stirring as you pour.
Mix well so all is covered. Spread single layer on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350° or until crisp.
Store in covered container.

title: beulah's macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain.
Add magarine to hot macaroni and stir until melted.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into casserole dish.
Add tomato juice so that it just barely covers macaroni.
Put in 350° oven until tomato juice is heated through.
Add sliced Cheddar cheese on top. Put back in oven until cheese melts.
Stir well.

title: picklin' pig cake
directions: Mix together cake mx and mandarin oranges.
Then add eggs and oil, mix well with mixer.
Bake in 2 or 3 layer pans at 325° for 25 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Let cool.

title: lettuce and egg salad
directions: Chop lettuce and eggs together; toss lightly.
Place on salad plate.
Pour on your favorite dressing.

title: sugar cream pie #2
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients well and pour into unbaked pie shell. Melt the 2 tablespoons butter and pour over filling.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 45 to 50 minutes more.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add remaining ingredients and mix until blended.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan and bake at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: oreo delight
directions: Melt margarine	and
pour
in
long
pan.
Crumble Oreo cookies and put
in
margarine.
Press down.
Mix cream cheese and 1 Cool Whip
with
10x sugar.
Put on top of cookies.
Mix puddings with milk and
pour
on top.
Put (8 ounce) Cool Whip on top of this
and sprinkle with more cookie crumbs.	Refrigerate about 2 hours.

title: baked beans with franks
directions: Mix all ingredients together except bacon.
Put into 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with bacon strips.
Bake 20 minutes or until heated through.

title: black iris muffins
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients blending until smooth.
In a separate bowl, combine dry ingredients and mix well.
Then add wet to dry ingredients together.
Makes 18 medium muffins.
Bake at 350°
until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: caramel corn
directions: Combine brown sugar, corn syrup, butter and salt.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture reaches 260°. Remove from heat and stir in baking soda.
Pour mixture over popped corn in large roasting pan.
Stir until well coated.
Bake for 1 hour at 200°, stirring 3 or 4 times.
Store in airtight container.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add cold water.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Chill until firm.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: upside-down lasagna
directions: In large skillet, brown meat, onions and garlic.
Drain.
Add tomato sauce, paste, water, salt and pepper.
Simmer, covered, 30 minutes.
Cook macaroni and spinach in separate pans according to package directions.
Drain.
Cool both.
Add beaten eggs and parsley to spinach; stir.
Combine meat mixture, spinach and macaroni in large baking pan and stir until blended.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: polenta
directions: Bring water to a boil in a 10-inch skillet (nonstick).
This can be part chicken broth, white wine or any flavoring such as seasoning packets.
Add corn meal and stir until all liquid is absorbed.
Smooth out with the back of a spoon.
Lower the heat and cook for 1/2 hour.
When the edges pull away from the side of the pan, shake the skillet.
If the Polenta moves, it is cooked. Invert a plate or wooden board over the top of the skillet and turn it over.
Cut into wedges and top with tomato sauce and cheese.

title: refrigerator cucumber slices
directions: In a large container, combine cucumbers and onions. In a large bowl, combine the remaining ingredients, stirring until the sugar is dissolved. Pour over cucumbers and onions. Mix well. Cover and chill overnight. May be refrigerated for up to 2 weeks. Yields about 2 1/2 quarts.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Melt chocolate in milk.
Add sugar and corn syrup.
Cook slowly, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Bring to boiling; cover and cook 3 minutes.
Uncover and cook to soft ball stage (236°), stirring frequently.
Remove from heat; add butter and cool to lukewarm (110°) without stirring.
Add vanilla and beat vigorously until very thick and no longer glossy.
Quickly spread in a greased pan.
When firm, cut in squares.
Makes 2 dozen pieces.

title: homemade salad dressing
directions: Bring vinegar and sugar to boil.
Add eggs, cornstarch and mustard mixed together.
Cook until thick and add 1 teaspoon of salt.
Thin with partially whipped cream to desired consistency.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, eggs, milk, sugar, 1/2 cup butter and vanilla in bowl; mix well. Spoon in baking dish. Mix remaining ingredients in bowl and sprinkle over mixture. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: geech'ee stew
directions: Bring salted water to a boil over an open fire in a large pot. Put in 1 potato per person.
Boil 10 minutes.
Add 1 onion per person and boil another 10 minutes.
Add 1 ear of corn per person and boil another 10 minutes.
Add 3 links of sausage per person and boil another 10 minutes.
Add 1/2 pound shrimp per person and boil 5 to 10 minutes longer.
Pour off water and serve.
Great for R. A. Campouts.

title: cherry supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Spread 1/2 of pie filling in bottom of pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Reduce oven to 350°.
In small bowl, beat cream cheese with sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Pour over hot pie filling.
Bake 25 minutes.
Center will be soft.
Cool completely and spoon rest of pie filling in center and sour cream around outside.
Refrigerate.

title: tangy cabbage slaw
directions: In a large bowl, break noodles into small pieces:
set seasoning packet aside.
Add coleslaw mix almonds and onions.
In a small bowl, combine the oil, vinegar, sugar and contents of seasoning packet.
Pour over coleslaw mixture and toss to coat; serve immediately.	Refrigerate leftovers.	Yields 6 servings.

title: sausage breakfast pie
directions: Fry sausage in medium skillet.
Crumble and drain.
Divide in half and put in each pie shell.
Do the same with the cheese.
Add onion and green pepper to the eggs, then pour into pie shells. Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool, then serve.
Great warmed up, too!

title: broiled eggplant with salsa
directions: Baste sliced eggplants with olive oil on both sides and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake or broil 2 to 3 minutes on both sides, until supple (do not burn).
Chop soy Mozzarella cheese and garlic cloves.
Combine with the organic salsa.
Spoon 1 to 2 teaspoons of salsa, soy cheese, garlic mixture into sliced, boiled eggplant.
Roll up into round shape and place in ungreased baking dish.
Add remaining salsa on top.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes, until bubbly.

title: grape-nut pudding
directions: Cook Grape-Nuts and milk in a double boiler for 15 minutes. In a baking dish, combine the sugar, eggs and butter.
Beat together.
Pour in hot Grape-Nut and milk mixture.
Stir until blended.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix together and set in refrigerator overnight.

title: more beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Cook beef and onion in cooking oil until meat is browned.
Add tomato sauce, corn, green pepper and chili powder to meat mixture and cook 10 minutes.
Put a layer of noodles in a 2-quart casserole dish, then a layer of meat mixture.
Bake for 20 minutes at 325°.
Add shredded cheese and bake until melted.

title: baked artichoke dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, then spoon into a lightly greased one-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, or until bubbly. Serve hot with bagel chips or melba toast.

title: key lime pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add lime rind and juice. Spoon in ice cream, stirring until melted and smooth.
If necessary, chill until mixture will mound.
Spoon into crust. Chill until firm, about 2 hours.
Garnish with whipped topping if desired.
Serves 8.

title: ponakaka(swedish dessert similar to baked custard)
directions: Mix rennet tablet in small amount of water to dissolve (about 1 tablespoon); set aside.
In large pan, heat milk until a little more than warm to touch.
Beat flour, sugar, vanilla and eggs and stir into milk.
Pour into a large bowl.
Add rennet mix; stir well, then let stand until sets or feels firm to touch, about 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Bake in greased large casserole dish.
You may use this for setting time.
Also start cooking at 400° for 15 minutes, then lower temperature to 375°.
It will rise in the middle and later fall, this is to be expected.
Done when can insert knife in the middle and come out clean.
Can be served with ice cream hot or cooled and refrigerated.
Good both ways.

title: quiche
directions: Put 1/2 of the cheese mixture into unbaked pie shell. Add ham or bacon and then rest of cheese mixture.
Mix together the heavy cream, milk, eggs, mustard, nutmeg, salt and pepper. Add to above. Top with 1 tablespoon butter. Bake 45 minutes at 350° or until custard sets. Serve with salad.

title: molasses ginger cookies
directions: Mix and refrigerate overnight.
Roll out and cut into shapes with cookie cutters.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: ma's ice cream
directions: Mix all together and freeze until firm.

title: grape nut bread
directions: Mix ingredients together and place in a loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: walnut squares
directions: Mix flour, sugar and butter.
Pat it in 8-inch square pan and bake at 350° until light brown.
Mix remaining ingredients and put in baked crust.
Bake until light brown and toothpick comes out clean.
Frost top with powdered sugar icing; cut in squares.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Melt shortening in saucepan with warm milk.
Put in large mixer bowl; add yeast, eggs, sugar and salt.
Mix.
Add small amounts of flour to make soft dough.
Remove beaters; add more flour until dough can be handled.
Knead.
Shape into rolls. Place in two Pam sprayed 9 X 13 pans.
Let rise.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Note:
*May add potato flakes, mashed potatoes, or wheat germ as part of the flour.

title: chicken with capers and tarragon
directions: Season flattened chicken with salt and pepper.
Saute in heavy skillet in vegetable oil.
Cook for 2 minutes on each side or until lightly browned.
Discard oil.
Add cream, capers, tarragon and lemon juice.
Bring liquid to a boil and continue to cook over high heat, stirring constantly, until volume is about half.
Remove from heat and add butter.
Spoon sauce over each chicken breast and serve immediately.
It cannot be made ahead and/or frozen.
Serves 4.

title: catfish cove slaw
directions: Boil the sugar, vinegar, oil, mustard, celery seed and salt. Pour over slaw and refrigerate 3 to 4 hours.

title: easy scalloped tomatoes
directions: Combine and spread in buttered 8-inch square pan.
Dot top with butter and bake at 350° for about 3/4 hour.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Press biscuits onto greased cookie sheet until bottom is covered.
Pour eggs over biscuits until biscuits are covered evenly.
Sprinkle sausage and cheese over top.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: homemade pretzels
directions: Mix yeast and water in a bowl.
Add sugar and table salt.
Add flour; mix well.
Put the dough on some waxed paper on a table; knead it until smooth.
Cut off pieces; make them into shapes you like.
Dough should be about 1/4-inch thick.
(If too thick, they will be doughy; if too thin, they will be too brittle.)
Place them on a cookie sheet.
Brush the pretzels with a beaten egg, then sprinkle with coarse salt.
Cover the complete top of the pretzel with egg.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes, or until they are golden brown, then eat them!!

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Soak bread crumbs in water.
Cook onion in margarine until light brown.
Mix meat, eggs and onion.
Season to taste with salt, pepper and a dash of nutmeg.
Add parsley.
Roll into small balls; lightly flour.
Cook until brown, about 20 minutes.

title: round steak sauerbraten
directions: Cut meat in 1-inch squares.
Brown meat.
Remove meat and add gravy mix with water.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except noodles.
Return meat to skillet.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally. Serve over cooked noodles.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: ladyfinger cheese cake(portuguese)
directions: Beat heavy cream in a bowl until thick.
In separate bowl, mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
When well mixed, add to thick cream and mix well.
In spring-form pan, stand ladyfingers around edge and lay a layer along the bottom.
Pour in half of the mixture, then add another layer of ladyfingers.
Top with topping of your choice (example:
strawberries, cherries or pineapple). Preparation time:
25 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Cut stove off and leave pie in stove to set.

title: fry bread
directions: Blend dry ingredients together.
Add water slowly, mixing with hands.
When dough
is sticky enough to require oil on the hands, it is just right.
Don't make the dough too stiff.
Break off a ball the size of golf balls.
Pull it or roll it to 5-inch circle.
Make 2 or 3 holes in the dough for even cooking.
Place in hot oil in frypan.
Brown lightly on both sides.
Serve hot with butter and honey.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken breasts for 1 1/2 hours and reserve broth.
Skin, bone and cut up chicken into small pieces.
Put in casserole. Blend mushroom soup and sour cream and pour over chicken.
Mix stuffing according to directions, but substitute reserved chicken broth for water.
Put this over soup mixture.
Cover the casserole and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 or more.

title: dee's cheese and jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and stir in pineapple and sugar.
Fold in the rest of ingredients.
Spoon into container and chill.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Melt butter or margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add graham cracker crumbs and 2/3 cup sugar.
Press down smooth.
Beat cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar, eggs and vanilla until creamy.
Pour over crust.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Cool for 2 hours.
Top with blueberry pie filling.
Chill before serving.

title: camp cazadero granola
directions: Mix salad oil,
honey and vanilla; heat until bubbling, stirring a lot.
Mix
remaining
ingredients
well,
then
add liquid and mix completely.
Spread
in
a
greased
jelly roll pan.
