Bake in 325° oven
for
15 to 30 minutes or until brown. If this is too sweet, the total sugar could be reduced.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients except potatoes until smooth.
Add potatoes and mix until well blended.
Pour onto hot, well-greased pan.
Brown on both sides and serve.
Makes 10 to 12 pancakes.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add beaten eggs, melted margarine, Karo and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add pecans if desired.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° until knife inserted comes out clean, about 45 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Cover.
Let set 24 hours in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 8 to 10, 12 with small portions.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut green peppers in half lengthwise.
Remove seeds and membranes.
Mix ground beef, tomato sauce, rice, egg, oregano, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Spoon into pepper halves.
Place on roasting rack and cover loosely with wax paper.

title: atomic cheese dogs
directions: Place hot dogs in microwave for 30 seconds.
Place hot dogs in roll for 20 seconds in a microwave.
Put cheese strips on hot dogs in the roll and microwave the whole thing until cheese melts or dog is done.

title: fruit punch
directions: Put in 8-quart pan.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes. To serve, strain punch and float orange slices on top.

title: potato fritters
directions: Use leftover mashed potatoes or boiled potatoes.

Add onion, flour and salt. Mix well. Put oil in skillet. When hot, spoon potato mixture into pan and fry until golden brown, turning once. If using mashed potatoes, add a little milk until you can mix well with a spoon.

title: my jewish brisket
directions: On a large piece of heavy foil, place the brisket.
Sprinkle the brown sugar, onion soup mix and garlic powder over the brisket.
Drizzle the ketchup over all.
Fold the foil securely around the brisket, leaving an airspace.
Place in shallow roasting pan.
Bake at 325° for 3 to 3 1/2 hours or until brisket is tender.
Transfer brisket to a warm platter and slice.
Skim fat from sauce and serve sauce with brisket slices.

title: speedy pate
directions: Blend all ingredients and spoon into crock or bowl.
Chill several hours.

title: country style chicken pie
directions: Place onions and 1 can chicken broth in large pot.
Over medium heat, bring to a slow boil.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add carrots and cook for 20 minutes.
Stir in broccoli and mushrooms; remove from heat.
Let stand until needed.

title: extra peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening and peanut butter until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Blend in syrup and milk.
Shape in 2-inch roll; chill.
Slice about 1/4-inch thick. Place half the slices on ungreased cookie sheet.
Spread each with 1/2 teaspoon peanut butter and seal edges with a fork.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.
Cool slightly; remove from cookie sheet.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: loquat compote
directions: Drain the loquats and reserve syrup.
Add wine to the loquats, marinate for 15 minutes.
Pour loquat syrup into a saucepan, heat to boiling point and boil to reduce to half the volume.
Combine the marinated fruit with the syrup, add the liqueur, stirring well.
Add almonds.
This can be served as a dessert or side dish with curry, fish, pork or poultry.
Serves 4.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Heat spaghetti sauce, tomato sauce, water, mushrooms, beef, oregano and basil in saucepan.
Combine Ricotta, 2 cups Mozzarella, Parmesan cheese and parsley.
Pour 3/4 cup sauce in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Arrange 3 pieces uncooked pasta lengthwise over sauce.
Pour 1/2 cup sauce over pasta; spread with 1/2 of cheese mixture.
Cover with 1/2 sauce.
Repeat layer.
Top with remaining pasta and sauce; sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 60 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining 1 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Let stand for 10 minutes or return to oven for 5 minutes, until cheese melts.

title: salmon tuna loaf
directions: In a large mixing bowl, break up salmon and tuna into small bits. Add all other ingredients and mix thoroughly. For best results, mix with your hands. Mold into one large loaf or two small loaves. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to one hour.

title: fancy mashed potatoes
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add to the potatoes along with all other ingredients except paprika.
Put into lightly buttered dish.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Refrigerate overnight. Remove 15 minutes before baking.
Uncover.
Bake at 350° until well heated.

title: hamburger tortilla dip
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add salt and pepper.
Mix chiles, taco sauce and soups together.
Start with a layer of Doritos in casserole, then a layer of hamburger, layer of soup mixture and top with layer of cheese.
Continue until all are gone.
Bake at 350° for about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: garden pasta
directions: Drain marinade from artichokes into a 9 or 10-inch skillet. Add onion and press garlic into mixture; simmer until softened. Add tomatoes, bay leaf, Italian herbs, salt and basil.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Uncover and continue cooking until sauce thickens slightly, about 10 minutes.
Add artichokes (cutting larger ones in halves), and simmer for a few minutes longer. Remove bay leaf and add parsley.
Meanwhile, cook noodles in boiling, salted water just until tender.
Drain and toss with butter and cheese.
Serve with the artichoke sauce and sprinkle with additional cheese, if desired.
Makes 3 or 4 servings.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, brown sugar and shortening. Add vanilla, salt and eggs. Sift and measure flour. Add soda, baking powder, oatmeal, Rice Krispies, coconut and nuts. Mix well. Form into small balls. Bake 12 minutes at 375°.

title: barbecue pizza
directions: Mix ingredients into a dough.
Spread on a greased pizza pan. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: sour cream pie
directions: In mixing bowl, beat eggs well; stir in sour cream.
Add corn syrup, vanilla, sugar, salt and butter; mix well.
Stir in pecans. Pour into pastry shell.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven until the crust is brown and filling is slightly puffy, about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: goblick(kids love the feel of this)
directions: Add water and a little bit of cornstarch at a time to form a slimy, semi-runny mixture.
Form it into a ball in your hand and then open your hand and let it run through your fingers; repeat. To keep fresh, store in an airtight container in the fridge.

title: seafood salad
directions: Toss all together and put on serving dish.
(I have a dish that looks like a fish.)

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken, save broth.
Take meat off bones and layer in casserole.
Put onion, cheese and crushed Doritos on top of chicken. Heat soups, broth and Ro-Tel tomatoes until blended. Pour over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fresh cauliflower-broccoli salad
directions: Separate broccoli and cauliflower into small flowerets.
Toss with peanuts and bacon bits.
Add dressing just before serving.

title: jellied cranberry-orange salad
directions: Grind the cranberries and the oranges (including rind) in a food mill or processor.
Add the sugar, nuts and pineapple; stir well.
Dissolve the gelatin in the hot water; add the cold water and stir well.
Add gelatin to cranberry mixture.
Turn the mixture into a 1 1/2-quart mold and chill until set.
Serve on lettuce leaves with a small garnish of mayonnaise.
Serves 8.

title: "sparkling" peach punch
directions: Place baking sheet in freezer until it's cold.
Then use ice cream scoop to form frozen yogurt into balls; place balls on baking sheet.
Return to freezer until serving time.
Cover yogurt balls and baking sheet with foil.
Use vegetable peeler to peel fresh peaches.
Cut peaches into thin slices on cutting board. Place peach slices and lemonade concentrate in food processor or blender.
Cover and whirl until smooth.
Pour peach mixture into punch bowl and add pineapple-orange juice, sparkling water and frozen yogurt balls.
Stir gently.
Makes about 17 cups.

title: hamburger goulash
directions: Brown ground meat, onion and bell pepper.
Drain.
Make gravy with flour, salt, pepper, garlic powder, milk and hot water.
Add potatoes, cut in circles.
Cook until potatoes are about half done.
Add ground meat mixture.
Simmer until potatoes are done.

title: russian spiced tea
directions: Mix and use two rounded teaspoonfuls per cup of boiling water. Store in a glass jar.

title: corn light bread
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake in a greased loaf pan in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Yield:
1 loaf.

title: scalloped corn for a crowd or potluck
directions: Mix flour, sugar and milk.
Add beaten eggs and butter.
Blend in corn.
Bake in large casserole.
Stir a couple of times while baking.
Bake at 400° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour, butter, and pecans and press into a buttered 9 / 13 dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 or 20 minutes.
Cool.
Mix 1 cup of cool whip, sugar and cream cheese and spread over crust. Mix both puddings with 3 cups of milk and beat until slightly thickened.
Spread over the cream cheese layer.
Top with the rest of cool whip.
Chill for several hours or overnight before serving.

title: asparagus with sour cream
directions: Cook asparagus in a small amount of salted water until tender. Drain.
Serve with sour cream; garnish with egg yolk.

title: holiday sweet potatoes
directions: You will need a food processor or blender.

title: pound cake
directions: Beat the first 6 ingredients for 3 minutes.
Add 3/4 cup milk and the vanilla; beat for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Stir dry ingredients together in a large bowl.
Add the remaining ingredients and stir until well mixed.
Fry on hot oiled griddle.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Place in a pie plate. There is no crust.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Turn down to 350° and bake until done.

title: spicy mexican corn
directions: Drain picante sauce; reserve liquid.
Set vegetable mixture aside.
Measure reserved liquid.
Add water, if necessary, to measure 1/2 cup.
Combine corn and reserved liquid in a saucepan. Cook, uncovered, over medium heat, stirring occasionally, about 5 minutes or until corn is tender.
Add picante sauce and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 minute.
Spoon into a serving bowl.
Sprinkle with cheese, covering until cheese melts.
Yields 2 1/2 cups.
Contains 153 calories (18% from fat, 2/3 cup serving).

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: Mix together. Spread onto flour tortillas. Roll, put on plate and let chill. Slice.

title: ayers meat loaf
directions: Wet and crumble toast into large bowl with meat and all other ingredients.
Form in pan.
Spread ketchup over top.
Pour 1/2-inch water into pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: mama's pineapple skillet cake
directions: Beat egg whites.
To beaten egg yolks, add sugar, then pineapple juice and dry ingredients alternately. Add vanilla. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into large cast-iron skillet lined with melted butter, brown sugar and pineapple slices.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean in the middle. This can be doubled and baked in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan; will have to bake a little longer.

title: smothered chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in 3-quart casserole dish. Cover chicken with onion, bell pepper, mushrooms and soup.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Ten minutes before removing, add
the cheese.
Serves 3.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Let stand for 7 hours in bowl in fridge.
Whip after out of fridge and then frost your cake.
Keep any leftover cake in fridge.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Combine refried beans with enough salsa to be spreadable, but not runny. Spread mixture on a large serving plate with a rim to contain the mix.
Combine the sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning. Spread on top of the beans.
Peel, pit and puree avocados.
Season to taste with lemon juice, salt and pepper (or use prepared guacamole). Spread mixture on top of sour cream layer.
Sprinkle scallions, tomatoes, cheese, jalapenos and olives (if you like them!) on top of the guacamole.
Serve with lots of white corn tortilla chips!

title: taco dip
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in mixer and spread thinly on a large plate or pizza pan.
Garnish with lettuce, tomatoes, and Cheddar cheese.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into ungreased 8-inch pan.
Indent 3 holes with spoon in dry ingredients.
Into 1 hole, pour oil, vinegar into another and vanilla into the third.
Pour water over all and stir with fork until all is thoroughly mixed.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: baked seafood salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bread crumbs.
Place in a greased baking dish and sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: monterey chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, combine chicken cubes, taco sauce, onion, chilies, corn, rice water and olives.
Spoon into ungreased 9 x 13 inch baking dish.
In a medium bowl, combine taco shell pieces and cheese.
Sprinkle over chicken mixture.
Bake 40-45 minutes or until top is golden brown.
Garnish suggestions: sliced green onions and sour cream.

title: edible play dough
directions: In a mixing bowl, add peanut butter, honey and dry milk.
Mix with hands.
Make shapes and decorate with marshmallows and raisins.
(You can use your imagination and decorate with a variety of foods.)
Kids love making this and it's great for a rainy day.

title: pam's taco salad
directions: Layer first 7 items over shredded lettuce (medium head).
Mix the Thousand Island dressing, sugar, reserved tablespoon of taco seasoning and hot taco sauce.
Add on top of layered ingredients and toss right before serving.

title: pesto-potato-sausage salad
directions: In large skillet, combine potatoes with enough salted water to cover.
Heat to boiling; simmer until tender (about 12 minutes). Drain; place in large bowl.
Halve sausage lengthwise; cut crosswise into 1/2-inch diagonal slices.
In same skillet used to cook potatoes, saute sausage over medium-high heat until browned (about 10 minutes).
With slotted spoon, transfer to bowl with potatoes; add tomatoes.

title: denver biscuits
directions: In saucepan, bring milk to a boil and let cool.
Add yeast to milk and then add enough flour to make a thick batter.
Let rise 1 hour.
Add mashed potatoes, sugar, softened lard, baking powder, baking soda, salt and more flour, as you would to make light bread.
Let rise again, then roll out.
Cut with biscuit cutter. Let rise again.
Bake in 350° oven until brown.

title: orange cookies
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Add eggs and continue to cream until thoroughly mixed.
Add dry ingredients
alternately with sour milk and 1/2 cup orange juice to the creamed mixture.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water, then add 2 cups cold water. After Jell-O begins to jell, stir in strawberries.
Pour this in 9 x 13-inch dish.
When completely jelled, top with Cool Whip.

title: ellen's fruit cake
directions: Sprinkle 1 tablespoon flour over fruit and mix well.
Cream the butter and sugar.
Dissolve soda in boiling water.
Slowly add vanilla, eggs and flour and mix well.
Pour the stiff batter over the fruit and mix well with hands.
Grease pans and line bottoms with brown paper.
Bake 2 1/2 hours at 250°.
Makes 3 to 4 loaves.

title: rave reviews coconut cake
directions: Blend the cake mix, water, eggs and oil in a large mixing bowl. Beat for 4 minutes at medium speed. Stir in coconut and nuts. Pour into 3 pans (greased and floured). Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes. Allow to cool for 15 minutes and then remove from the pan and cool on a rack. Ice with Anna's Frosting.

title: sweet and sour green beans
directions: Cook bacon until crispy.
Brown onion in bacon grease, then drain off grease.
Place onion, bacon, sugar, vinegar and catsup in saucepan.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add green beans and sauce to casserole dish.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: rose ann's pound cake
directions: Cream together cheese, butter and sugar for 20 minutes.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour, salt, vanilla and lemon extract. Pour into greased and floured Bundt cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Test with a straw for doneness.

title: asparagus strudel
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, saute asparagus and onion in butter 2 to 3 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Stir in next 7 ingredients and 1 beaten egg.
On floured surface, roll out pastry to a 10 1/2 x 11 1/2-inch rectangle.
Place asparagus mixture lengthwise along center of pastry.
Brush 1/3 of beaten egg along empty edges.
Overlap sides to cover filling.
Seal.
Place seam side down on baking sheet.
Brush with remaining egg.
Cover with dill sprigs.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes until golden.
Cool 5 minutes.

title: orange walnut fudge
directions: Line an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan with foil so it extends over edges.
Butter the foil.
Mix powdered sugar and cocoa in medium bowl; set aside.
In a pan, combine margarine, milk and orange peel.
Cook over medium heat until boiling, stirring constantly, until margarine is melted.
Remove from heat and cool slightly. Stir in powdered sugar and cocoa mixture.
Add walnuts, pour into prepared pan.
Cut while still warm into 1-inch squares.
Chill in refrigerator until firm. Makes approximately 30 pieces.

title: choco-chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Bake at 375°.
Beat together margarine and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla and beat.
Stir in flour, baking soda and salt and mix well.
Add oatmeal and chocolate chips.
Roll into balls using about a teaspoonful.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Do not press down balls.
This makes the cookie hard.
Bake for 9 to 11 minutes.
Kids love these soft, chewy cookies.

title: helen's stuffed mushrooms
directions: Mix, stuff and broil until bubbly.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add corn, sour cream and melted margarine. Stir together.
Add muffin mix, salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over top.
Bake at 350° or until done.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut peppers into halves lengthwise; remove seeds and wash. Combine ground beef, rice, onion, salt, pepper and 1/4 can tomato sauce.
Pile meat mixture lightly into pepper halves.
Place in large baking dish.
Top each pepper with remaining tomato sauce. Cover dish tightly.
Bake in oven for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Cream the shortening, margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add dry ingredients, one tablespoon at a time, alternating with milk. Add vanilla and fold in pineapple.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Put into a cold oven. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. Cool cake for 10 minutes and remove from pan. Frost with Pineapple Icing.

title: cavatini
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Add garlic, onion and green pepper.
Cook until tender, stirring frequently; drain.
Stir in pepperoni, mushrooms and spaghetti sauce.
Combine noodles and macaroni.
Layer noodle mixture, cheese and ground beef mixture, alternately in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake in 375° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until bubbly.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly with sugar, salt, Karo syrup and melted butter. Add pecans. Pour into unbaked pastry shell. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Cool.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: In a large bowl, place lettuce, celery, pepper, onion, peas, Parmesan cheese and mayonnaise (spread like icing), sugar (over all), grated Cheddar and bacon.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate at least 8 hours.
Toss before serving.

title: chicken and broccoli pie
directions: Rinse broccoli under cold water to thaw; drain.
Mix broccoli, 2 cups of the cheese, chicken and onion in pie plate.
Beat milk, eggs, Bisquick, salt and pepper until smooth.
Pour into pie plate. Bake until knife inserted in middle comes out clean, about 25 to 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and bake again until cheese melts.
Cool 5 minutes.
Bake in 400° oven.

title: lemon sauce for cakes and puddings
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add boiling water; cook until thick. Add butter, flavoring and nutmeg.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Place rice, onion soup mix and water in a 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Arrange chicken and cover with celery and mushroom soups. Cover and bake 1 hour.
Remove cover and bake another hour.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook hen; cool and remove meat from bones.
Cut into bite-size pieces.
Let chicken broth come to a low boil.
Mix flour, egg, shortening, salt and water to make a smooth ball.
Divide into two parts.
Roll out thin on floured board and cut in 2 to 3-inch strips.
Add separately to boiling broth.
Reduce heat and add chopped, boiled egg; salt and pepper to taste.

title: old-fashioned bean soup
directions: Thoroughly wash beans.
Place in pan, cover with water and bring to a strong boil.
Turn off and let set for 1 hour.
Drain. Place beans in a large kettle, cover with water and cook until beans begin to get tender.
Then add potatoes, onions, celery, tomato juice, sugar, salt and pepper.
When all ingredients are done, mash the soup with a potato masher until all ingredients are mashed.
Turn the heat to low and continue to cook.
The soup can be served at this point, but it is better if it simmers for a long time.
Absolutely delicious.

title: oreo crunch
directions: Mix together the crushed cookies and melted butter; spread in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread ice cream over cookies.
Pour syrup over ice cream and freeze.
Before serving, top with Cool Whip, nuts and cherries.

title: skillet pizza
directions: Cook ground beef and onion.
Spread dinner rolls into large skillet.
Spread 1/2 jar pizza sauce over rolls.
Spread ground beef and onion.
Spread 1/3 cup bell pepper, pepperoni, ham, etc. Add rest of pizza sauce.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Cook on top of stove very slowly, until crust is brown and cheese is melted.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: In a casserole dish slice potatoes in rounds.
Lay in bottom of dish.
Slice onions on top of that; pour soup undiluted over that.
Add extra mushrooms, if desired.
Lay pork chops over soup. Slice cabbage in strips and put on top.
Slice butter over cabbage, cover and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: spanish beans
directions: Mix ingredients in a medium saucepan; bring to a boil on low heat.
Simmer until base is thick; add water according to your preference of juice.
Serve alone as a side dish or over white rice. Serves 3 to 5 people.

title: sparkling cranberry punch
directions: Mix cranberry juice cocktail and lemonade concentrate in punch bowl.
Just before serving, stir in sparkling water.

title: french brown rice
directions: Melt butter in 2 1/2 to 3-quart casserole. Add beef consomme, French onion soup and seasoning from rice.
Add plain rice, long grain and brown rice and mushrooms.
Stir.
Cook uncovered at 325° for 1 hour until all the water is absorbed. Serves 10 to 12.
Easy to prepare.

title: cherry pie salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: easy company chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts between plastic wrap.
Pound lightly until 1/4-inch thick.
Place ham and Swiss slices in middle of each chicken breast.
Roll and place in casserole.
Mix cream of chicken soup with sherry.
Pour over chicken.

title: famous oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars, egg, water and vanilla.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
(Can add 1 cup nuts or raisins or chocolate chips or coconut.)
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add corn and green chilies.
Pour 1/2 into a greased 8-inch skillet.
Sprinkle cheese over.
Pour in rest of batter.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: Beat butter with wooden spoon in a bowl until creamy. Gradually beat in sugar until smooth.
Beat in flour, salt and vanilla; mixture will be stiff.
Pinch off small pieces of dough with moistened fingers; roll into 1-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 13 to 14 minutes, until bottoms are golden.
Do not let tops brown. When done, roll in 10x sugar.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press both cans of crescent rolls onto cookie sheet.
Bake until brown.
Mix sour cream, cream cheese and dressing mix. Spread on cooled crust.
Top with your choice of cut up vegetables, such as: broccoli, green pepper, carrots, onions and cauliflower.
Then top with shredded cheese.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook noodles by directions on the bag. Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Pour in a baking dish and bake 45 minutes.

title: old-fashioned rice pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Bring water to boil.
Stir in rice and salt.
Cover and simmer until all water is absorbed, about 30 minutes.
Add milk and boil gently, stirring occasionally, until mixture thickens slightly, about 5 minutes.
Combine eggs, sugar and vanilla in bowl.
Gradually stir in rice mixture.
Pour into a greased casserole.
Place casserole in a pan containing 1-inch hot water.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Remove briefly from oven and mix slightly, but well, to distribute the rice in the custard.
Sprinkle cinnamon, if desired, on top of mixture at this time.
Return to oven and bake an additional 30 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Serve warm or chilled.

title: frozen salad
directions: In mixer, mash bananas; add next 4 ingredients.
Stir in pineapple and nuts.
Add food coloring.
Spoon into 9 or 10-inch pan and freeze.
Serve on lettuce.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add melted Crisco, beaten egg and buttermilk.
Pour into an iron skillet and bake 1 hour or until done.
Pour 1/2 stick margarine over bread.

title: smokey barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer 7 to 10 minutes.

title: apple pie
directions: In a food processor, combine the flour and 1/4 teaspoon salt. Process for a few seconds, then add 6 tablespoons butter.
Add shortening and process until the mixture resembles a coarse meal. Sprinkle 3 tablespoons ice water over the mixture and process about 20 seconds.
Pinch some of the dough between your fingers. If it is dry and does not hold together, add 1 tablespoon more of water and process briefly until dough begins to form a ball.
Do not overprocess.

title: fried fresh corn
directions: Fry, stirring often, about 30 minutes.
When corn is tender, add chunk of butter.

title: favorite corn and  meat hot dish
directions: Brown meat with green pepper, onion and celery.
Let simmer 10 minutes. Drain fat from mixture.
Cook macaroni rings according to directions on package. Drain.
Add to meat mixture with the corn, soup and salt.
Bake in a large casserole 1 hour at 300°.
Serves 15. Garnish with parsley.

title: carrot salad
directions: Combine carrots and raisins.
Mix mayonnaise, honey, lemon juice and cinnamon.
Toss gently.

title: english sparrow or blackbird pie
directions: Place meat on rack; salt and pepper. Strip with thin sliced salt pork or fat back.
Add a pinch of thyme, savory and marjoram. Slice garlic very thin and sprinkle over meat.
Add 2 quarts of bouillon.
Add bay leaf and chilies.
Add vegetables, apple slices and onion slices on meat.
For a thin roast, cook 1 1/2 hours.

title: sweet potato, banana or pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs well.
Slowly add soda, salt and baking powder.
Add pumpkin, bananas or sweet potatoes (mashed). Now add flour, spices and raisins and nuts.
Bake in greased loaf pans, 1 large or 2 medium size.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: ham and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Spread in ungreased pan (9 x 13-inch).
Layer ham and cheese over broccoli.
Beat remaining ingredients with beater until smooth.
Slowly pour over cheese. Bake uncovered 1 hour at 350°.

title: corn pudding casserole
directions: Mix in a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 425° until brown and bubbly crust appears for about 35 minutes.

title: congealed cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve raspberry gelatin in boiling water.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese well with the drained pineapple juice.
Add the package of clear gelatin.
Mix in pineapple, cranberry sauce and nuts.
Add the cooled raspberry gelatin to the mixture.
Chill until firm.

title: wonderful spiced tea mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together well. Store in airtight canister indefinitely. Boil water and add 2 rounded teaspoonfuls for 1 cup and 3 rounded teaspoonfuls for a mug.

title: ham and broccoli pie
directions: Sprinkle bottom of pie shells with half of the Swiss cheese. Mix all other ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with remainder of cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: toffee bars
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and vanilla.
Add flour and nuts.
Mix well.
Press into ungreased jelly roll pan.
Sprinkle on chocolate chips.
Press down into mixture.
Bake 20 minutes for softer bar and 25 minutes for crisper bar at 350°.

title: jello pretzel dessert
directions: Mix pretzels, butter and 3 tablespoons sugar in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake in a 400° oven for 8 minutes. Cool.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain and bone salmon.
Flake into a bowl.
Add bread, celery, onion, salt, pepper, egg and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Make white sauce by mixing margarine, flour and salt into a microwavable bowl and cook on high for 1 minute.
Stir in milk. Microwave on high for 3 minutes, beating with a whisk after every minute.
Mix into salmon mixture.
Bake in greased casserole in a 350 degree oven for 30 minutes.

title: gooey
directions: Combine cake mix, butter and egg; pat into well-greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine the cream cheese, confectioners sugar and eggs.
Beat for 3 minutes.
Pour over cake mixture; bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: date pudding
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until light.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt into egg mixture.
Stir in dates and walnuts.
Pour into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in pan of hot water in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serve warm.
Top with whipped cream.
Makes 6 servings.

title: quick drop cookies
directions: Mix together sugar, cocoa, milk and oleo.
Boil for 1 minute in medium pan.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter, vanilla, uncooked oats and nuts.
Stir only enough to blend.
Drop by spoon on waxed paper.
Let set about 30 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Undercook broccoli and lima beans as directed on packages. Season as usual.
Drain well.
Combine soup, sour cream and water chestnuts.
Add to cooked vegetables and put in long shallow baking dish (7 x 11-inch).
Top with Rice Krispies which have been sauteed in margarine.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Serves 10.

title: chocolate topped oatmeal bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Blend first 4 ingredients until crumbly. Press mixture into ungreased 9 x 13 inch pan. Bake 15 to 20 minutes until light golden brown. In saucepan, combine chocolate pieces and peanut butter. Cook over low heat stirring constantly until chocolate pieces are melted. Spread over bars. Chill; cut into bars. Store in refrigerator. Yields 2-3 dozen bars.

title: creamy chicken noodle soup
directions: Melt butter in a Dutch oven over medium heat; add onion and saute until tender.
Stir in chicken and next 9 ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 45 minutes.
Stir in milk, return to simmer.
Remove from heat; let stand 10 minutes.
Sprinkle each serving with cheese.
Yield: 12 cups.

title: norwegian wheat bread(norsk hvetelbrod)
directions: Heat milk and butter to scalding.
Pour in a large bowl and cool to lukewarm.
Stir in yeast.
Sift 7 cups flour, sugar, cardamom and salt and add to milk, mixing well.
Add wheat germ. Turn dough onto floured board and knead in the other cup of flour, if needed.
Place in buttered bowl and let rise to double.
Punch down; let rest 15 minutes.
Divide dough in half and shape into 2 loaves.
Let rise to double and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Melt butter; add sugar, flavoring and eggs.
Mix well.
Add nuts and pour into uncooked pie shell.
Cook 19 minutes at 400 degrees then 35 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: pea salad
directions: Moisten the first 4 ingredients with mayonnaise; add salt. Refrigerate.
Just before serving, add potatoes, almonds or noodles.
I prefer the shoestrings.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Mix all the ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 60 minutes.
Let cool before cutting.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: chocolate peanut butter bars
directions: In a large bowl, mix graham cracker crumbs and sugar.
Melt peanut butter and 3/4 cup margarine together; pour over cracker crumbs and sugar and mix thoroughly.
Press into the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and 1/2 cup margarine together; spread over peanut butter layer.
Cool to room temperature before cutting into bars.
Refrigerate.
Easy and delicious!

title: lemon muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottoms only or use muffin cups. Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and lemon peel.
Mix well.
In separate bowl, combine milk, oil and egg.
Add wet ingredients to dry ingredients; stir until moistened.
Fill muffin cups about 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 22 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: no-salt dried herb blend
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Crush a few tablespoonfuls at a time in mortar with pestle.
Store in a shaker or tightly covered container.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Warm ingredients so they can mix well.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 325° for glass, 350° for other type of dish for 1 hour.

title: cheese pizza(setting:  high)
directions: Prepare pastry for 1 crust pie as directed on package, except do not roll out.
Press pastry firmly and evenly against the bottom and up the sides of an ungreased 10 x 1 1/2-inch Pyrex pie plate.
Do not press on the rim of the pie plate.
Prick the bottom and sides with a fork.
Microwave, uncovered, for 2 minutes; turn dish a quarter turn.
Microwave again about 2 minutes until the crust is dry and flaky.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup of cheese over the pie shell.
Add any toppings you selected.
Spread pizza sauce over the toppings.
Sprinkle the remaining cheese on top.
Microwave, uncovered, for 5 minutes; turn the dish a quarter turn.
Microwave again 3 to 4 minutes, until the mixture bubbles around the edge.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump undrained pineapple into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan (spread evenly and be sure to fill corners of pan).
Dump pie filling over pineapple and spread evenly.
Sprinkle dry cake mix on top, covering pie filling completely.
Drizzle melted butter over cake mix; sprinkle with nuts, if desired.
Bake at 350° until browned (approximately 1 hour); serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate overnight.
Save a few florets and egg slices for top.

title: bran apple muffins(low-fat, no sugar)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray 2 1/2-inch muffin cups with nonstick baking spray.

title: easy scalloped potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes; chop onions and put in casserole.
Mix soup and milk together and pour over potatoes and onions.
Put about 4 tablespoons of butter on top.
Bake in covered dish at 350° for 1 hour.
Take lid off for the last 15 minutes.
